LongDisplayString.name: LongDisplayString

OperStatus.name: OperStatus
OperStatus.description: Available operational states for the object (e.g. VPN, Virtual Router, Virtual Interface, etc.). This is used to provide additional granularity beyond that provided by RowStatus.

OperState.name: OperState
OperState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row.

PerfCurrentCount.name: PerfCurrentCount
PerfCurrentCount.description: A counter associated with a performance measurement in a current 15 minute measurement interval. The value of this counter starts from zero and is increased when associated events occur, until the end of the 15 minute interval. At that time the value of the counter is stored in the first 15 minute history interval, and the CurrentCount is restarted at zero. In the case where the agent has no valid data available for the current interval the corresponding object instance is not available and upon a retrieval request a corresponding error message shall be returned to indicate that this instance does not exist (for example, a noSuchName error for SNMPv1 and a noSuchInstance for SNMPv2 GET operation).

PerfIntervalCount.name: PerfIntervalCount
PerfIntervalCount.description: A counter associated with a performance measurement in a previous 15 minute measurement interval. In the case where the agent has no valid data available for a particular interval the corresponding object instance is not available and upon a retrieval request a corresponding error message shall be returned to indicate that this instance does not exist (for example, a noSuchName error for SNMPv1 and a noSuchInstance for SNMPv2 GET operation). In a system supporting a history of n intervals with IntervalCount(1) and IntervalCount(n) the most and least recent intervals respectively, the following applies at the end of a 15 minute interval: - discard the value of IntervalCount(n) - the value of IntervalCount(i) becomes that of IntervalCount(i-1) for n >= i > 1 - the value of IntervalCount(1) becomes that of CurrentCount - the TotalCount, if supported, is adjusted.

PerfTotalCount.name: PerfTotalCount
PerfTotalCount.description: A counter associated with a performance measurements aggregating the previous valid 15 minute measurement intervals. (Intervals for which no valid data was available are not counted)

OrionIfIndex.name: OrionIfIndex
OrionIfIndex.description: ifIndex for the interface table of the mib-2 is redefined here. The 32-bit integer is organized as below to easily locate an interface in an Orion box. +---------+----------+-------------+-----------------+----------------------+ |Reserved | | | | | |(always0)| slot # |port # | channel # | subif # | |1-bit | 5-bits |6-bits | 8-bits | 12-bits | +---------+----------+-------------+-----------------+----------------------+ In the case of channelized and un-channelized DS3 blades, subif #4095, refers to the PPP/CiscoHDLC interfaces encapsulted on a channel/port. If the encpsulation is Frame Relay, subif 16-4094 refers to Dlcis' an the subid #4095 refers to the Dlcmi on a channel. Whereever one of those components of ifIndex(slot/port/chan/subif) doesn't make sense, it should be Zero. For example, in the case of an ethernet blade, only the slot and port are the valid fields. Other will be zero. So, the interfeaces in an Orion box are sorted in their order of presence with respect to the slot,port,channel and subif compoinents.

AtmVcIdentifier.name: AtmVcIdentifier
AtmVcIdentifier.description: The VCI value for a VCL. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by atmInterfaceMaxVciBits defined in ATM-MIB.

AtmVpIdentifier.name: AtmVpIdentifier
AtmVpIdentifier.description: The VPI value for a VPL or VCL. The value VPI=0 is only allowed for a VCL. For ATM UNIs supporting VPCs the VPI value ranges from 0 to 255. The VPI value 0 is supported for ATM UNIs conforming to the ATM Forum UNI 4.0 Annex 8 (Virtual UNIs) specification. For ATM UNIs supporting VCCs the VPI value ranges from 0 to 255. For ATM NNIs the VPI value ranges from 0 to 4095. The maximum VPI value cannot exceed the value allowable by atmInterfaceMaxVpiBits defined in ATM-MIB.

AtmServiceCategory.name: AtmServiceCategory
AtmServiceCategory.description: The service category for a connection.
AtmServiceCategory.reference: ATM Forum Traffic Management Specification, Version 4.0, af-tm-0056.000, June 1996.

SPPBaudRate.name: SPPBaudRate
SPPBaudRate.description: The baud rate of a Status Panel port.

SPPLoopbackStatus.name: SPPLoopbackStatus
SPPLoopbackStatus.description: The loopback status of a Status Panel port.

SPPModemStatus.name: SPPModemStatus
SPPModemStatus.description: Indicates whether a modem is connected to a Service Panel port.

EvLogLevel.name: EvLogLevel
EvLogLevel.description: This specifies the level of detail for the event log.

EvLogArea.name: EvLogArea
EvLogArea.description: This is a bitmap where each bit represents the area that the event log belongs to. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ trap 0 emergency 1 system 2 authentication 3 application 4 protocol 5 ipsec/ike 6 link 7 configuration 8

MplsLabel.name: MplsLabel
MplsLabel.description: Represents an MPLS label. Note that the contents of a label field are interpreted in an interface-type specific fashion. For example, the label carried in the MPLS shim header is 20 bits wide and the top 12 bits must be zero. The frame relay label can be either 10, 17 or 23 bits wide depending on the size of the DLCI field size and the top 22, 15, or 9 bits must be zero, respectively. For an ATM interface, the lowermost 16 bits are interpreted as the VCI, the next 8 bits as the VPI and the remaining bits must be zero. Also note the permissible label values are also a function of the interface type. For example, the value 3 has special semantics in the control plane for an MPLS shim header label and is not a valid label value in the datapath.
MplsLabel.reference: 1. MPLS Label Stack Encoding, Rosen et al, draft- ietf-mpls-label-encaps-04.txt, April 1999. 2. Use of Label Switching on Frame Relay Networks, Conta et al, draft-ietf-mpls-fr-03.txt, Nov. 1998.

MplsLsrIdentifier.name: MplsLsrIdentifier
MplsLsrIdentifier.description: The Label Switch Router (LSR) identifier is the first 4 bytes or the Router Id component of the Label Distribution Protocol (LDP) identifier.

MplsLdpIdentifier.name: MplsLdpIdentifier
MplsLdpIdentifier.description: The LDP identifier is a six octet quantity which is used to identify an Label Switch Router (LSR) label space. The first four octets encode an IP address assigned to the LSR, and the last two octets identify a specific label space within the LSR.

MplsLdpLabelTypes.name: MplsLdpLabelTypes
MplsLdpLabelTypes.description: The Layer 2 label types which are defined for MPLS LDP are generic(1), atm(2), or frameRelay(3).

MplsLdpGenAddr.name: MplsLdpGenAddr
MplsLdpGenAddr.description: The value of an network layer or data link layer address.

MplsAtmVcIdentifier.name: MplsAtmVcIdentifier
MplsAtmVcIdentifier.description: The VCI value for a VCL. The maximum VCI value cannot exceed the value allowable by atmInterfaceMaxVciBits defined in ATM-MIB. The minimum value is 32, values 0 to 31 are reserved for other uses by the ITU and ATM Forum. 32 is typically the default value for the Control VC.

InterfaceIndexOrZero.name: InterfaceIndexOrZero
InterfaceIndexOrZero.reference: RFC 2933: Internet Group Management Protocol MIB

PwVcIndex.name: PwVcIndex
PwVcIndex.description: Virtual Circuit Index. Locally unique index for indexing one of several MIB tables associated with a particular VC.

PwVcInstance.name: PwVcInstance
PwVcInstance.description: Virtual Circuit Instance. Use in conjunction with PwVcIndex when it is required to have more than one instance of a particular VC. The primary application for instances is APS where there are primary and backup VCs.

PwVcID.name: PwVcID
PwVcID.description: Virtual Circuit Identifier. Uniquely identifies a VC locally. Also uniquely identifies a VC at its end points.

PwGroupID.name: PwGroupID
PwGroupID.description: An administrative identification mechanism for grouping a set of service-specific pseudo-wire services. May only have local significance

SnmpAdminString.name: SnmpAdminString
SnmpAdminString.description: An octet string containing administrative information, preferably in human-readable form. To facilitate internationalization, this information is represented using the ISO/IEC IS 10646-1 character set, encoded as an octet string using the UTF-8 transformation format described in [RFC2279]. Since additional code points are added by amendments to the 10646 standard from time to time, implementations must be prepared to encounter any code point from 0x00000000 to 0x7fffffff. Byte sequences that do not correspond to the valid UTF-8 encoding of a code point or are outside this range are prohibited. The use of control codes should be avoided. When it is necessary to represent a newline, the control code sequence CR LF should be used. The use of leading or trailing white space should be avoided. For code points not directly supported by user interface hardware or software, an alternative means of entry and display, such as hexadecimal, may be provided. For information encoded in 7-bit US-ASCII, the UTF-8 encoding is identical to the US-ASCII encoding. UTF-8 may require multiple bytes to represent a single character / code point; thus the length of this object in octets may be different from the number of characters encoded. Similarly, size constraints refer to the number of encoded octets, not the number of characters represented by an encoding. Note that when this TC is used for an object that is used or envisioned to be used as an index, then a SIZE restriction MUST be specified so that the number of sub-identifiers for any object instance does not exceed the limit of 128, as defined by [RFC1905]. Note that the size of an SnmpAdminString object is measured in octets, not characters.

IKERadiusAcctUserType.name: IKERadiusAcctUserType
IKERadiusAcctUserType.description: Specifies the type of information included in the RADIUS accounting-request user-name attribute sent by IKE.

csOrionSystemFwVer.name: csOrionSystemFwVer
csOrionSystemFwVer.description: The fw version used by Orion

csOrionSystemMajorVer.name: csOrionSystemMajorVer
csOrionSystemMajorVer.description: The version for a Orion as a system.

csOrionSystemTempStatus.name: csOrionSystemTempStatus
csOrionSystemTempStatus.description: This object identifies the current temperature status within the Orion system. If this object has the value normal(1), the temperature is within the normal range. If the status is hot(2), the temperature is above the normal range and measures should be taken to bring the temperature down.

csOrionSystemReset.name: csOrionSystemReset
csOrionSystemReset.description: The software reset. It is an action object such that when set to 'reset' will reset all the blades. Setting it to 'none' has no effect, and when it is retrieved the value will always be 'none' .

csOrionSystemTime.name: csOrionSystemTime
csOrionSystemTime.description: To set the system date & time with the standard format specified by RFC 2579. Below is the date-time specification. (Display Format: YYYY-MM-DD,HH:MM:SS.ss,+/-:HH:MM) field contents range ----- -------- ----- 1 year* 1999..2098 2 month 1..12 3 day 1..31 4 hour 0..23 5 minutes 0..59 6 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 deci-seconds 0..9 8 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 hours from UTC* 0..13 10 minutes from UTC 0..59 * Notes: - the value of year is in network-byte order - daylight saving time in New Zealand is +13 For example, Tuesday May 26, 2000 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 2000-5-26,13:30:15.0,-4:0 Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

csOrionSystemVersionNum.name: csOrionSystemVersionNum
csOrionSystemVersionNum.description: The system version number applies to the IPSX system as a whole. This number has the format: a.b.c.d where 'a.b' is major release number, 'c' is the patch nubmer, and 'd' is the internal release number.

csOrionSystemShutdown.name: csOrionSystemShutdown
csOrionSystemShutdown.description: The software shutdown. It is an action object such that when set to 'shutdown' will stop the file-system of all the blades. that when set to 'shutdown' will stop the file-system of all the blades. Setting it to 'none' has no effect, and when it is retrieved the value will always be 'none' .

csOrionSystemControlBladeFailOver.name: csOrionSystemControlBladeFailOver
csOrionSystemControlBladeFailOver.description: When set to 'failover', the master control blade switches over to stand-by control blade. Setting it to 'none' has no effect, and when it is retrieved the value will always be 'none' .

csOrionSystemCLIRadiusAuthentication.name: csOrionSystemCLIRadiusAuthentication
csOrionSystemCLIRadiusAuthentication.description: NOTE: This object has been replaced by csOrionSystemLoginServer. When this object is set to radius, radius server will be used to authenticate a user logging into a CLI session. When this object is set to localDatabase, the password file resided locally will be used to authenticate the CLI user.

csOrionSystemBootTable.name: csOrionSystemBootTable
csOrionSystemBootTable.description: A list of Sources from which this Orion will boot.

csOrionSystemBootEntry.name: csOrionSystemBootEntry
csOrionSystemBootEntry.description: An entry containing Boot information applicable to this Orion System. Note, currently there is only one entry in this table. More entries may be added in future releases.

csOrionSystemBootIndex.name: csOrionSystemBootIndex
csOrionSystemBootIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each boot record.

csOrionSystemBootImageName1.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName1
csOrionSystemBootImageName1.description: The absolute path and file name for the boot image. If this string is prefaced with 'FLSH', tftp will be used to boot over the network. This applies to all 6 images.

csOrionSystemBootImageName2.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName2
csOrionSystemBootImageName2.description: The 2nd absolute path and file name for the boot image. This will be used only if the previous boot images fail.

csOrionSystemBootImageName3.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName3
csOrionSystemBootImageName3.description: The 3rd absolute path and file name for the boot image. This will be used only if the previous boot images fail.

csOrionSystemBootImageName4.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName4
csOrionSystemBootImageName4.description: The 4th absolute path and file name for the boot image. This will be used only if the previous boot images fail.

csOrionSystemBootImageName5.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName5
csOrionSystemBootImageName5.description: The 5th absolute path and file name for the boot image. This will be used only if the previous boot images fail.

csOrionSystemBootImageName6.name: csOrionSystemBootImageName6
csOrionSystemBootImageName6.description: The 6th absolute path and file name for the boot image. This will be used only if the previous boot images fail.

csOrionSystemBootPort.name: csOrionSystemBootPort
csOrionSystemBootPort.description: When booting over the network, the port used to load the image

csOrionSystemBootServerAddress.name: csOrionSystemBootServerAddress
csOrionSystemBootServerAddress.description: A boot server Ip Address. Note, this only applies if this entry specifies booting over the network.

csOrionSystemBootLocalIpAddr.name: csOrionSystemBootLocalIpAddr
csOrionSystemBootLocalIpAddr.description: When booting over the network using a boot protocol that does not supply a source IP address, This object specifies the local IP address to use when booting via the network.

csOrionSystemBootLocalIpMask.name: csOrionSystemBootLocalIpMask
csOrionSystemBootLocalIpMask.description: When booting over the network using a boot protocol that does not supply a source IP address, This object specifies the local IP address mask to use when booting via the network.

csOrionSystemBootDefGw.name: csOrionSystemBootDefGw
csOrionSystemBootDefGw.description: When booting over the network, this object is used to identify the gateway to use in communicating with the boot server.

csOrionSystemBootConfig.name: csOrionSystemBootConfig
csOrionSystemBootConfig.description: The absolute path and file name for the configuration file. Note, the configuration file must be on the local flash.

csOrionSystemBootSaveImage.name: csOrionSystemBootSaveImage
csOrionSystemBootSaveImage.description: This object specifies whether the IPSX system will save the boot image in local flash. Note this applies only if the csOrionSystemBootProtocol is tftp(2).

csOrionSystemBootUserName.name: csOrionSystemBootUserName
csOrionSystemBootUserName.description: User Name to use if the download is via FTP

csOrionSystemBootUserPassword.name: csOrionSystemBootUserPassword
csOrionSystemBootUserPassword.description: Password to use if the download is via FTP

csOrionSystemBootInternalNwAddr.name: csOrionSystemBootInternalNwAddr
csOrionSystemBootInternalNwAddr.description: All the blades in the system make a internal network. This attribute defines the network part (255.255.0.0) of this subnet. Default is 172.168.0.0

csOrionSystemBootConcurrentDownloads.name: csOrionSystemBootConcurrentDownloads
csOrionSystemBootConcurrentDownloads.description: Maximum number of downloads that can occur concurrently. if configured to 0, then there is no limit to number of simultaneous download sessions. This is useful if the TFTP/FTP server cannot handle a large number of TFTP/FTP sessions

csOrionSystemLoginUserTable.name: csOrionSystemLoginUserTable
csOrionSystemLoginUserTable.description: A login information for Orion, using console or telnet.

csOrionSystemLoginUserEntry.name: csOrionSystemLoginUserEntry
csOrionSystemLoginUserEntry.description: An entry contains information for one CLI login user.

csOrionSystemLoginUserPassword.name: csOrionSystemLoginUserPassword
csOrionSystemLoginUserPassword.description: A sequence of alphabetical and numerical characters, MUST not be less than 8 characters.

csOrionSystemLoginUserRowStatus.name: csOrionSystemLoginUserRowStatus
csOrionSystemLoginUserRowStatus.description: A row status type for the table entry.

csOrionSystemLoginUserOperStatus.name: csOrionSystemLoginUserOperStatus
csOrionSystemLoginUserOperStatus.description: A operational status for this table entry.

csOrionSystemLoginRoleTable.name: csOrionSystemLoginRoleTable
csOrionSystemLoginRoleTable.description: A role for a login user.

csOrionSystemLoginRoleEntry.name: csOrionSystemLoginRoleEntry
csOrionSystemLoginRoleEntry.description: An entry contains information for one role type. A role is a group of feature access permissions. Each login user is associated with a single role.

csOrionSystemLoginRoleAccessRights.name: csOrionSystemLoginRoleAccessRights
csOrionSystemLoginRoleAccessRights.description: Access rights of a role are a list of feature-wise permissions. The permissions of a feature are represented by a 4-byte tuple {rights (1-byte),featureid(3-bytes)}. The features in this list are in the ascending order of their feature-id. rights: Access rights are classified into the following categories (given below along with the mapping to unix-style read,write and execute permissions): 0 : none (rwx-style = ---) 1 : all (rwx-style = rwx) 2 : view (rwx-style = r--) 3 : config (rwx-style = rw-) 4 : monitor (rwx-style = r-x) Feature-id's: A feature is a set of commands which are grouped into a read, write or execute command-type. all (1), access (2), clear (3), device (4), dialup (5), diff_serve (6), event_log (7), field (8), firewall (9), froip (10), nat (11), routing (12), service_selection (13), show (14), tunnel (15), vpnvr (16)

csOrionSystemLoginRoleRowStatus.name: csOrionSystemLoginRoleRowStatus
csOrionSystemLoginRoleRowStatus.description: A row status type for the table entry.

csOrionSystemLoginDomainTable.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainTable
csOrionSystemLoginDomainTable.description: A domain for a login user.

csOrionSystemLoginDomainEntry.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainEntry
csOrionSystemLoginDomainEntry.description: An entry contains information for one domain. A domain is a group of object instances which defines the scope a role for for a user. Each login user is associated with a single domain.

csOrionSystemLoginDomainName.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainName
csOrionSystemLoginDomainName.description: The name of an access domain.

csOrionSystemLoginDomainVRList.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainVRList
csOrionSystemLoginDomainVRList.description: A list of VPN/VRs a user can access. A VPN/VR is represented as /. The VPN/VRs in the list are separated either by a space(s). The following are valid wildcards for a VR: /* : All VRs with the given VPN. */* : All VRs. If it used then it should be the only entry in the list.

csOrionSystemLoginDomainInterfaceList.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainInterfaceList
csOrionSystemLoginDomainInterfaceList.description: List of interfaces which an user can access. The interfaces in the list are separated either by space(s). Each interface is represented as follows: [/[:channel-range>[:]]] where each range above has the follog syntax: = { * | | - } If the optional elements (,,etc) are not specified they default to '*', which denotes all values. is always less than . If '*' or range is specified for an element then all following elements MUST be wildcard enrtries The chassis as an interface can also be included in the list and is represented by the key-word 'chassis' Valid interface examples: * - same as */*/*/* 5-6/* chassis 5/3-5/* 5/3/2-4 Invalid interface Eg: 5/*/3

csOrionSystemLoginDomainRowStatus.name: csOrionSystemLoginDomainRowStatus
csOrionSystemLoginDomainRowStatus.description: A row status type for the table entry.

csOrionSystemLoginPermTable.name: csOrionSystemLoginPermTable
csOrionSystemLoginPermTable.description: Access permissions for a login user. A permission id represented as a :. A user can have multiple permissions.

csOrionSystemLoginPermEntry.name: csOrionSystemLoginPermEntry
csOrionSystemLoginPermEntry.description: An entry contains information for one login user permission.

csOrionSystemLoginPermRowStatus.name: csOrionSystemLoginPermRowStatus
csOrionSystemLoginPermRowStatus.description: A row status type for the table entry.

csOrionSystemLoginServer.name: csOrionSystemLoginServer
csOrionSystemLoginServer.description: When this object is set to remote, a remote authentication server (csOrionSystemLoginServerListName) will be used to authenticate a user logging into a CLI session. When this object is set to localDatabase, the password file residing locally will be used to authenticate the CLI user.

csOrionSystemLoginServerListName.name: csOrionSystemLoginServerListName
csOrionSystemLoginServerListName.description: The name of the server list to use for remote authentication, if no list is specified then the server specified in the default server list is used. Cli authentication uses the server list and default servers configured on the system virtual router.

csOrionModemControl.name: csOrionModemControl
csOrionModemControl.description: This object controls access to this device via Dial In modem.

csOrionModemBaud.name: csOrionModemBaud
csOrionModemBaud.description: This object sets the target baud rate of the modem connection.

csOrionModemFlowCtl.name: csOrionModemFlowCtl
csOrionModemFlowCtl.description: This object specifies the type of flow control used by the modem.

csOrionModemConnectWait.name: csOrionModemConnectWait
csOrionModemConnectWait.description: This object sets the length of time, in seconds, the modem will wait for a connection.

csOrionConfigSaveFileName.name: csOrionConfigSaveFileName
csOrionConfigSaveFileName.description: This object is used when the save configuration is launched on an Orion box by setting the csOrionConfigSave object. The device handle the default value for this object. When this object is not set, the device look for the csOrionSystemBootConfig of the csOrionSystemBootTable. If that is not NULL, that name is used as the file name. Otherwise the default filename of config.dat is used.

csOrionConfigSaveStart.name: csOrionConfigSaveStart
csOrionConfigSaveStart.description: This object triggers the configuration saving on the divice. The result of this action is stored in csOrionConfigSaveStatus.

csOrionConfigSaveStatus.name: csOrionConfigSaveStatus
csOrionConfigSaveStatus.description: This object triggers the configuration saving on the divice. The result of this action is stored in csOrionConfigSaveStatus.

csOrionConfigLoadOutputEnable.name: csOrionConfigLoadOutputEnable
csOrionConfigLoadOutputEnable.description: This object controls whether output from loading configuration file should be printed out to the console. Loading configuration will be quicker if this object is disabled.

csOrionFileSysReqEntry.name: csOrionFileSysReqEntry
csOrionFileSysReqEntry.description: An entry of File System Request Table.

csOrionFileSysReqIndex.name: csOrionFileSysReqIndex
csOrionFileSysReqIndex.description: This object identifies a specific File System request entry. NMSs are expected to come up with a unique ID each request. This ID will also be used to index the File System result entry.

csOrionFileSysReqType.name: csOrionFileSysReqType
csOrionFileSysReqType.description: This object specifies the filesystem operation stated in the enumeration above. We will add entries as we support additional filesystem commands. Objects that hold the parameters must also be set for commands that requires some arguments.

csOrionFileSysReqSrcFile.name: csOrionFileSysReqSrcFile
csOrionFileSysReqSrcFile.description: This object is used to hold the source file for the file system operation. Must be set for 'delete', 'copy' and 'rename' requests. For 'load' request, the file to be loaded should be set using this object. If not set, the default file defined in csOrionSystemBootConfig will be loaded.

csOrionFileSysReqDestFile.name: csOrionFileSysReqDestFile
csOrionFileSysReqDestFile.description: This object is used to hold the source file for the file system operation. Must be set for copy and rename requests.

csOrionFileSysReqStatus.name: csOrionFileSysReqStatus
csOrionFileSysReqStatus.description: This object is used to store the status of the File System request. operation. For 'dir' operation, csOrionFileSysResultTable should only be evaluated after this object yields opSuccess(3).

csOrionFileSysReqRowStatus.name: csOrionFileSysReqRowStatus
csOrionFileSysReqRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add/delete rows from this table.

csOrionFileSysResultTable.name: csOrionFileSysResultTable
csOrionFileSysResultTable.description: File System Result Table. The object csOrionFileSysReqStatus should be evaluated before acquiring the results from this table.

csOrionFileSysResultEntry.name: csOrionFileSysResultEntry
csOrionFileSysResultEntry.description: An entry of File System Result Table. Each file returned from 'dir' request corresponds to an entry in csOrionFileSysResultEntry. Additional 'getnext' is expected to obtain the succeeding files. We will add objects in this table as we expose more file attributes.

csOrionFileSysResultIndex.name: csOrionFileSysResultIndex
csOrionFileSysResultIndex.description: This object identifies a specific File System result entry. This index corresponds to the ID provided by NMSs on File System request.

csOrionFileSysResultFilename.name: csOrionFileSysResultFilename
csOrionFileSysResultFilename.description: This object is used to hold the filename from the 'dir' request.

csOrionFileSysResultFilesize.name: csOrionFileSysResultFilesize
csOrionFileSysResultFilesize.description: This object is used to hold the filesize from the 'dir' request.

csOrionChassisMidplaneID.name: csOrionChassisMidplaneID
csOrionChassisMidplaneID.description: Midplane laser ID for this chassis.

csOrionChassisPacketRingStatus.name: csOrionChassisPacketRingStatus
csOrionChassisPacketRingStatus.description: Status of the packet ring. noProtection means protection ring is inactive. onProtection means protection ring is active.

csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimToProtEndpoi.name: csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimToProtEndpoint
csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimToProtEndpoi.description: Slot number of the primary to protection endpoint. If csOrionChassisPacketRingStatus is noProtection, this object will have a value of 0.

csOrionChassisPacketRingProtToPrimEndpoi.name: csOrionChassisPacketRingProtToPrimEndpoint
csOrionChassisPacketRingProtToPrimEndpoi.description: Slot number of the protection to primary endpoint. If csOrionChassisPacketRingStatus is noProtection, this object will have a value of 0.

csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimaryCRC.name: csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimaryCRC
csOrionChassisPacketRingPrimaryCRC.description: CRC count on the primary packet ring.

csOrionChassisPacketRingProtectionCRC.name: csOrionChassisPacketRingProtectionCRC
csOrionChassisPacketRingProtectionCRC.description: CRC count on the protection packet ring.

csEthEntry.name: csEthEntry
csEthEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Table.

csEthSlotIndex.name: csEthSlotIndex
csEthSlotIndex.description: This object identifies the slot in which the blade that supports this port is installed.

csEthModuleIndex.name: csEthModuleIndex
csEthModuleIndex.description: This object identifies a specific module on the blade installed in csEthSlotIndex.

csEthPortIndex.name: csEthPortIndex
csEthPortIndex.description: This object identifies a specific port on the module installed in csEthModuleIndex.

csEthEncapType.name: csEthEncapType
csEthEncapType.description: This object identifies the encapsulation method used on this Ethernet port.

csEthAutoneg.name: csEthAutoneg
csEthAutoneg.description: This object is used to enable or disable the autonegotiation feature of this Ethernet port. This feature is used to automatically negotiate the Speed and Duplex mode for 10/100 Mbps Ethernet ports.

csEthDuplex.name: csEthDuplex
csEthDuplex.description: This object is used to specify the Duplex mode of this Ethernet port. This is used only if csEthAutoneg is disabled. Note: The default value is removed because it is not fixed in the system after reboot when autonegotiation enabled. It is hardware configuration dependent.

csEthSpeed.name: csEthSpeed
csEthSpeed.description: This object is used to specify the speed of this Ethernet port. This is used only if csEthAutoneg is disabled. Note: The default value is removed because it is not fixed in the system after reboot when autonegotiation enabled. It is hardware configuration dependent.

csEthLinkTestInterval.name: csEthLinkTestInterval
csEthLinkTestInterval.description: This object is used to specify the interval, in seconds, between Link Test packet transmissions. If this object is set to 0, no Link Test packets are sent.

csEthAdminStatus.name: csEthAdminStatus
csEthAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable thie Ethernet port.

csEthOperStatus.name: csEthOperStatus
csEthOperStatus.description: This object indicates the current operational status of this Ethernet port.

csEthPppoeService.name: csEthPppoeService
csEthPppoeService.description: This object is used to enable or disable PPPoE service on Ethernet Ports.

csEthSubIfEntry.name: csEthSubIfEntry
csEthSubIfEntry.description: The Parameters for a VLAN Interface.

csEthSubIfChannelIndex.name: csEthSubIfChannelIndex
csEthSubIfChannelIndex.description: Channel ID of this VLAN connection. Currently, it will always be 0.

csEthSubIfIndex.name: csEthSubIfIndex
csEthSubIfIndex.description: The Sub Interface Id of the Logical Interface.

csEthSubIfVlanId.name: csEthSubIfVlanId
csEthSubIfVlanId.description: The unipue number between 0 and 4095 that identifies a particular VLAN. The range of VLAN IDs supported per port is from 2 to 4094. The null VLAN Id (0) indicates that the tag header contains only user priority information. The VLAN Id 1, 4095 is reserved for implementation use.

csEthSubIfUserPriority.name: csEthSubIfUserPriority
csEthSubIfUserPriority.description: The user priority for this VLAN

csEthSubIfAdmStatus.name: csEthSubIfAdmStatus
csEthSubIfAdmStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable this VLAN.

csEthSubIfOpStatus.name: csEthSubIfOpStatus
csEthSubIfOpStatus.description: The operational status for this VLAN.

csEthSubIfRowStatus.name: csEthSubIfRowStatus
csEthSubIfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention. Writable objects in the table may be written in any RowStatus state.

csEthSubifPppoeService.name: csEthSubifPppoeService
csEthSubifPppoeService.description: This object is used to enable or disable PPPoE service on VLAN.

csDs3ConfigEntry.name: csDs3ConfigEntry
csDs3ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 Configuration table.

csDs3ConfigSlotIndex.name: csDs3ConfigSlotIndex
csDs3ConfigSlotIndex.description: This object identifies the blade to which this Ds3 Port is attached. Together with csDs3ConfigModuleIndex, csDs3ConfigPortIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csDs3ConfigModuleIndex.name: csDs3ConfigModuleIndex
csDs3ConfigModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the type of of the Ds3 Module on the blade identified by csChDs3SlotIndex.

csDs3ConfigPortIndex.name: csDs3ConfigPortIndex
csDs3ConfigPortIndex.description: This object identifies the location of the Ds3 Port on the module identified by csChDs3ModuleIndex. Together with csDs3ConfigSlotIndex, csDs3ConfigModuleIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csDs3ConfigCableLength.name: csDs3ConfigCableLength
csDs3ConfigCableLength.description: The length of the DS3 cable. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigFraming.name: csDs3ConfigFraming
csDs3ConfigFraming.description: The framing format used on this Ds3 Interface. The default value is cbit if the interface is DS3. If the interface is E3, e3Framed will be used, and cannot be configured to any other types.

csDs3ConfigMdlPath.name: csDs3ConfigMdlPath
csDs3ConfigMdlPath.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Path message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig.name: csDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig
csDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Idle Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlTestSig.name: csDs3ConfigMdlTestSig
csDs3ConfigMdlTestSig.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Test Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlEic.name: csDs3ConfigMdlEic
csDs3ConfigMdlEic.description: This object specifies the Equipment Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlLic.name: csDs3ConfigMdlLic
csDs3ConfigMdlLic.description: This object specifies the Location Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlFic.name: csDs3ConfigMdlFic
csDs3ConfigMdlFic.description: This object specifies the Frame Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlUnit.name: csDs3ConfigMdlUnit
csDs3ConfigMdlUnit.description: This object specifies the Unit Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlPfi.name: csDs3ConfigMdlPfi
csDs3ConfigMdlPfi.description: This object specifies the Facility Identification Code sent in the MDL Path message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlPort.name: csDs3ConfigMdlPort
csDs3ConfigMdlPort.description: This object specifies the Port number string sent in the MDL Idle Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigMdlGenerator.name: csDs3ConfigMdlGenerator
csDs3ConfigMdlGenerator.description: This object specifies the Generator number string sent in the MDL Test Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigTestT1Id.name: csDs3ConfigTestT1Id
csDs3ConfigTestT1Id.description: This object identifies which of the 28 T1's within this DS3 are to be broken out into the Test T1 port. If none of the T1's are to be broken out, this object should be set to 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigAdminStatus.name: csDs3ConfigAdminStatus
csDs3ConfigAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable this Ds3 port.

csDs3ConfigOperStatus.name: csDs3ConfigOperStatus
csDs3ConfigOperStatus.description: This object indicates the current operational status of this Ds3 port.

csDs3ConfigClockSource.name: csDs3ConfigClockSource
csDs3ConfigClockSource.description: This object specifies the source of the Transmit Clock used on this (unchannelized) DS3. If this object is set to internal(1), a local clock source is used. If this object is set to line(2), the recovered received clock is used as the transmit clock. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigDeviceType.name: csDs3ConfigDeviceType
csDs3ConfigDeviceType.description: This object indicates whether the interface is DS3 or E3.

csDs3ConfigSendCode.name: csDs3ConfigSendCode
csDs3ConfigSendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS3 interface by the device. Setting this variable causes the interface to begin sending the code requested. The values mean: sendNoCode sending looped or normal data sendLineCode sending a request for a line loopback sendPayloadCode sending a request for a payload loopback (i.e., all DS1/E1s in a DS3/E3 frame) sendResetCode sending a loopback deactivation request NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3ConfigLoopbackType.name: csDs3ConfigLoopbackType
csDs3ConfigLoopbackType.description: This object represents the desired loopback configuration of the DS3 interface. The values mean: noLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as its value. It is the default value. payloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for retransmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. lineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out. otherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here. Currently not used in the IPSX system. inwardLoop The sent signal at this interface is looped back through the device. dualLoop Both lineLoop and inwardLoop will be active simultaneously.

csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus.name: csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus
csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus.description: This variable represents the current state of the loopback on the DS3 interface. It contains information about loopbacks established by a manager and remotely from the far end. The csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore is can represent multiple loopbacks simultaneously. The various bit positions are: 1 ds3NoLoopback 2 ds3NearEndPayloadLoopback 4 ds3NearEndLineLoopback 8 ds3NearEndOtherLoopback 16 ds3NearEndInwardLoopback 32 ds3FarEndPayloadLoopback 64 ds3FarEndLineLoopback

csDs3ConfigLineStatus.name: csDs3ConfigLineStatus
csDs3ConfigLineStatus.description: This variable indicates the Line Status of the interface. It contains loopback state information and failure state information. The csDs3ConfigLineStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple failures and a loopback (see csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus object for the type of loopback) simultaneously. The ds3NoAlarm must be set if and only if no other flag is set. If the ds3LoopbackState bit is set, the loopback in effect can be determined from the csDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus object. The various bit positions are: 0 ds3NoAlarm No alarm present 1 ds3RcvRAIFailure Receiving Yellow/Remote Alarm Indication 2 ds3XmitRAIAlarm Transmitting Yellow/Remote Alarm Indication 3 ds3RcvAIS Receiving AIS failure state 4 ds3XmitAIS Transmitting AIS 5 ds3LOF Receiving LOF failure state 6 ds3LOS Receiving LOS failure state 7 ds3LoopbackState Looping the received signal 8 ds3RcvTestCode Receiving a Test Pattern 9 ds3OtherFailure any line status not defined here 10 ds3UnavailSigState Near End in Unavailable Signal State 11 ds3NetEquipOOS Carrier Equipment Out of Service

csDs3ConfigTimeElapsed.name: csDs3ConfigTimeElapsed
csDs3ConfigTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds that have elapsed since the beginning of the near end current error-measurement period. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value.

csDs3ConfigValidInterval.name: csDs3ConfigValidInterval
csDs3ConfigValidInterval.description: The number of previous near end intervals for which data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought online within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute near end intervals since the interface has been online. In the case where the agent is a proxy, it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

csDs3ConfigInvalidInterval.name: csDs3ConfigInvalidInterval
csDs3ConfigInvalidInterval.description: The number of intervals in the range from 0 to csDs3ConfigValidInterval for which no data is available. This object will typically be zero except in cases where the data for some intervals are not available (e.g., in proxy situations).

csDs3ConfigLineCoding.name: csDs3ConfigLineCoding
csDs3ConfigLineCoding.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on this interface, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. ds3B3ZS and e3HDB3 refer to the use of specified patterns of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace sequences of zero bits of a specified length. NOTE: This is applicable only for E3 for now.

csDs3ConfigNationalBit.name: csDs3ConfigNationalBit
csDs3ConfigNationalBit.description: Bit 12 of the E3 G.751 frame. NOTE: This is applicable only for E3.

csDs3Ds1ConfigTable.name: csDs3Ds1ConfigTable
csDs3Ds1ConfigTable.description: The DS3 DS1 configuration table. This is used to configure each of the DS1 connections within a complete DS3.

csDs3Ds1ConfigEntry.name: csDs3Ds1ConfigEntry
csDs3Ds1ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS3 DS1 Configuration table.

csDs3Ds1Id.name: csDs3Ds1Id
csDs3Ds1Id.description: This identifies a single DS1 within a complete DS3.

csDs3Ds1Framing.name: csDs3Ds1Framing
csDs3Ds1Framing.description: This object specifies the framing used on the DS1 assigned to this channel.

csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmDetect.name: csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmDetect
csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmDetect.description: This object specifies whether Yellow Alarm detection is active on the DS1 assigned to this channel.

csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmGen.name: csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmGen
csDs3Ds1YellowAlarmGen.description: This object specifies whether Yellow Alarm generation is active on the DS1 assigned to this channel. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1.

csDs3Ds1LineCode.name: csDs3Ds1LineCode
csDs3Ds1LineCode.description: This object specifies the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the on the DS1 assigned to this channel. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1.

csDs3Ds1InvertData.name: csDs3Ds1InvertData
csDs3Ds1InvertData.description: This object specifies whether the 'invert data' feature is enabled on the DS1 assigned to this channel. This feature must be enabled if the Line Code parameter (csDs3Ds1LineCode) is set to ami. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1.

csDs3Ds1ClockSource.name: csDs3Ds1ClockSource
csDs3Ds1ClockSource.description: This object specifies the source of the Transmit Clock used on the DS1 assigned to this channel. If this object is set to internal(1), a local clock source is used. If this object is set to line(2), the recovered received clock is used as the transmit clock. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1.

csDs3Ds1Fdl.name: csDs3Ds1Fdl
csDs3Ds1Fdl.description: This is used to enable/disable 1 second transmission of performance reports via ANSI 403 FDL. If this is disabled, the AT&T 54016 version of FDL is used. Note, FDL is available only for ESF framing. And so it is only applicable for T1.

csDs3Ds1OperStatus.name: csDs3Ds1OperStatus
csDs3Ds1OperStatus.description: This object indicates the current operational status of this DS1.

csDs3Ds1SendCode.name: csDs3Ds1SendCode
csDs3Ds1SendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS1 interface by the device. Setting this variable causes the interface to send the code requested. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1.. The values mean: ds1SendNoCode sending looped or normal data ds1SendLineCode sending a request for a line loopback ds1SendPayloadCode sending a request for a payload loopback ds1SendResetCode sending a loopback termination request

csDs3Ds1LoopbackType.name: csDs3Ds1LoopbackType
csDs3Ds1LoopbackType.description: This object represents the desired loopback configuration of the DS1 interface. This variable will be interpreted only when csDs3Ds1LoopbackDestination is set to a valid value. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1. noLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as its value. payloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for retransmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. lineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out. otherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here. Currently not used in the IPSX system inwardLoop The transmitted signal at this interface is looped back and received by the same interface. What is transmitted onto the line is product dependent. Cannot be applied to far end. dualLoop Both dsx1LineLoop and dsx1InwardLoop will be active simultaneously. Cannot be applied to far end.

csDs3Ds1LoopbackStatus.name: csDs3Ds1LoopbackStatus
csDs3Ds1LoopbackStatus.description: This variable represents the current state of the loopback on the DS1 interface. It contains information about loopbacks established by a manager and remotely from the far end. NOTE: This is applicable only for T1. The csDs3Ds1LoopbackStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore is can represent multiple loopbacks simultaneously. The various bit positions are: 1 ds1NoLoopback 2 ds1NearEndPayloadLoopback 4 ds1NearEndLineLoopback 8 ds1NearEndOtherLoopback 16 ds1NearEndInwardLoopback 32 ds1FarEndPayloadLoopback 64 ds1FarEndLineLoopback

csDs3Ds1LineConfig.name: csDs3Ds1LineConfig
csDs3Ds1LineConfig.description: This variable represents DS1/E1 transmit line configuration. This is normally used for dignostic or service purpose, it is not supposed for user to configure. The various bit positions are: BIT(0) not used BIT(1) ds1NoAlarm BIT(2) ds1RcvFarEndLOF BIT(3) ds1XmtFarEndLOF BIT(4) ds1RcvAIS BIT(5) ds1XmtAIS BIT(6) ds1LossOfFrame BIT(7) ds1LossOfSignal BIT(8) ds1LoopbackState BIT(9) ds1T16AIS BIT(10) ds1RcvFarEndLOMF BIT(11) ds1XmtFarEndLOMF BIT(12) ds1RcvTestCode BIT(13) ds1OtherFailure BIT(14) ds1UnavailSigState BIT(15) ds1NetEquipOOS BIT(16) ds1RcvPayloadAIS BIT(17) ds1Ds2PerfThreshold BIT(18) ds1XmtTrnkCond

csDs3Ds1LineStatus.name: csDs3Ds1LineStatus
csDs3Ds1LineStatus.description: This variable represents DS1/E1 transmit and receive line status. The various bit positions are: BIT(0) not used BIT(1) ds1NoAlarm BIT(2) ds1RcvFarEndLOF BIT(3) ds1XmtFarEndLOF BIT(4) ds1RcvAIS BIT(5) ds1XmtAIS BIT(6) ds1LossOfFrame BIT(7) ds1LossOfSignal BIT(8) ds1LoopbackState BIT(9) ds1T16AIS BIT(10) ds1RcvFarEndLOMF BIT(11) ds1XmtFarEndLOMF BIT(12) ds1RcvTestCode BIT(13) ds1OtherFailure BIT(14) ds1UnavailSigState BIT(15) ds1NetEquipOOS BIT(16) ds1RcvPayloadAIS BIT(17) ds1Ds2PerfThreshold BIT(18) ds1XmtTrnkCond

csDs3E1IntBits.name: csDs3E1IntBits
csDs3E1IntBits.description: This variable is used to configure the 2-bits international bits for the E1 interface. NOTE: This is applicable only for E1.

csDs3E1NatBits.name: csDs3E1NatBits
csDs3E1NatBits.description: This 4-bit object is added for the E1 sub-multiframe aligned national bit codeword configuration. NOTE: This is applicable only for E1.

csChDs3Table.name: csChDs3Table
csChDs3Table.description: The Channelized DS3 Channel configuration table.

csChDs3Entry.name: csChDs3Entry
csChDs3Entry.description: An entry in the DS3 Fractional table.

csChDs3SlotIndex.name: csChDs3SlotIndex
csChDs3SlotIndex.description: This object identifies the blade to which this Ds3 Port is attached. Together with csChDs3ModuleIndex, csChDs3PortIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csChDs3ModuleIndex.name: csChDs3ModuleIndex
csChDs3ModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module of the Ds3 Blade

csChDs3PortIndex.name: csChDs3PortIndex
csChDs3PortIndex.description: This object identifies the location of the Ds3 Port on the blade identified by csChDs3SlotIndex. Together with csChDs3SlotIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csChDs3ChNumber.name: csChDs3ChNumber
csChDs3ChNumber.description: The channel number for this entry.

csChDs3T1Number.name: csChDs3T1Number
csChDs3T1Number.description: This object identifies the DS1 number that is assigned to this channel. This number for E1 is 1 to 16. NOTE: This object can only be set during row creation. Once the row is created, this object cannot be modified.

csChDs3TimeSlots.name: csChDs3TimeSlots
csChDs3TimeSlots.description: This object specifies the individual DS0 time slots within the DS1(T1 or E1, identified by csChDs3T1Number) that are assigned to this channel. The format can be a range of slots (1-8), a list of slots (1, 3, 7), or a mix of both. NOTE: This object can only be set during row creation. Once the row is created, this object cannot be modified.

csChDs3Speed.name: csChDs3Speed
csChDs3Speed.description: This object specifies the speed (and, hence the signaling mode) of the DS1 assigned to this channel.

csChDs3Encap.name: csChDs3Encap
csChDs3Encap.description: This object specifies the encapsulation used on this DS3 channel. If the encapsulation type is frameRelay(2), use the csFrameRelayTable to configure the Frame Relay specific parameters.

csChDs3RowStatus.name: csChDs3RowStatus
csChDs3RowStatus.description: A row status type for this Channel.

csChDs3OperStatus.name: csChDs3OperStatus
csChDs3OperStatus.description: A operational status for this Channel.

csEthStatsEntry.name: csEthStatsEntry
csEthStatsEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Statistic Table.

csEthStatsTxDeferPktsOk.name: csEthStatsTxDeferPktsOk
csEthStatsTxDeferPktsOk.description: The counter associated with the number of packets deferred upon the first transmit attempt due to a busy line .

csEthStatsTxColCounts.name: csEthStatsTxColCounts
csEthStatsTxColCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of Regular collisions during transmission.

csEthStatsTxScolPktsOk.name: csEthStatsTxScolPktsOk
csEthStatsTxScolPktsOk.description: The counter associated with the number of packets transmitted without any errors following a single collisions.

csEthStatsTxMulticCollisionPktsOK.name: csEthStatsTxMulticCollisionPktsOK
csEthStatsTxMulticCollisionPktsOK.description: The counter associated with the number of packets transmitted without any errors following multiple collisions.

csEthStatsTx16CollisionCounts.name: csEthStatsTx16CollisionCounts
csEthStatsTx16CollisionCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets that have experienced 16 consecutive collisions or more.

csEthStatsTxLateCollisionCounts.name: csEthStatsTxLateCollisionCounts
csEthStatsTxLateCollisionCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmission abortions due to a collision occurring after the transmission of packets that are 64 bytes in length.

csEthStatsTx64Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx64Pkts
csEthStatsTx64Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted packets 64 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx65To127Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx65To127Pkts
csEthStatsTx65To127Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 64 to 127 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx128To255Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx128To255Pkts
csEthStatsTx128To255Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 128 to 255 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx256To511Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx256To511Pkts
csEthStatsTx256To511Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 256 to 511 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx512To1023Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx512To1023Pkts
csEthStatsTx512To1023Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted packets 512 to 1023 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx1024To1518Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx1024To1518Pkts
csEthStatsTx1024To1518Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted packets 1024 to 1518 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTx1519Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx1519Pkts
csEthStatsTx1519Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted packets with length larger than 1518 bytes, including bad packets.

csEthStatsTxPausePktsOk.name: csEthStatsTxPausePktsOk
csEthStatsTxPausePktsOk.description: The counter associated with the number of correct transmitted flow-control packets.

csEthStatsTxErrCounts.name: csEthStatsTxErrCounts
csEthStatsTxErrCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets transmitted with an error due to transmit FIFO underflow or txerr signal assertion.

csEthStatsTxOctetsBad.name: csEthStatsTxOctetsBad
csEthStatsTxOctetsBad.description: The counter associated with the number of bytes transmitted in packets with errors.

csEthStatsRxRuntCounts.name: csEthStatsRxRuntCounts
csEthStatsRxRuntCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of frames received without SFD detection but with carrier assertion .

csEthStatsRxOvfCounts.name: csEthStatsRxOvfCounts
csEthStatsRxOvfCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of received packets not fully accepted due to receive FIFO overflow .

csEthStatsRxShortPktsOk.name: csEthStatsRxShortPktsOk
csEthStatsRxShortPktsOk.description: The counter associated with the number of received packets without error, less than 64 bytes length .

csEthStatsRxNormCrcCounts.name: csEthStatsRxNormCrcCounts
csEthStatsRxNormCrcCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets received with an integral number of bytes and a CRC error with lengths between 64 bytes and maximum packet size .

csEthStatsRxNormAliCounts.name: csEthStatsRxNormAliCounts
csEthStatsRxNormAliCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets received with an nonintegral number of bytes and a CRC error with lengths between 64 bytes and maximum packet size.

csEthStatsRxLongPktsCounts.name: csEthStatsRxLongPktsCounts
csEthStatsRxLongPktsCounts.description: The counter associated with the number ofpackets larger than maximum packet size received without any error .

csEthStatsRxLongCrcCounts.name: csEthStatsRxLongCrcCounts
csEthStatsRxLongCrcCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets larger than maximum packet size received with a CRC error

csEthStatsRx64Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx64Pkts
csEthStatsRx64Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of received packets 64 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsRx65To127Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx65To127Pkts
csEthStatsRx65To127Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of received packets 65 to 127 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsRx128To255Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx128To255Pkts
csEthStatsRx128To255Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 128 to 255 bytes in length, including bad packetsO.

csEthStatsRx256To511Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx256To511Pkts
csEthStatsRx256To511Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 256 to 511 bytes in length, including bad packets

csEthStatsRx512To1023Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx512To1023Pkts
csEthStatsRx512To1023Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 512 to 1023 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsRx1024To1518Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx1024To1518Pkts
csEthStatsRx1024To1518Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 1024 to 1518 bytes in length, including bad packets.

csEthStatsRx1519Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx1519Pkts
csEthStatsRx1519Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets with length larger than 1518 bytes and the maximum packet size, including bad packets.

csEthStatsRxPausePktsOk.name: csEthStatsRxPausePktsOk
csEthStatsRxPausePktsOk.description: The counter associated with the number of correct received flow-control packets.

csEthStatsRxFalsCrcCounts.name: csEthStatsRxFalsCrcCounts
csEthStatsRxFalsCrcCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of false carrier events detected

csEthStatsRxOctsBad.name: csEthStatsRxOctsBad
csEthStatsRxOctsBad.description: The counter associated with the number of bytes received in packets with errors.

csEthStatsRxSysErrCounts.name: csEthStatsRxSysErrCounts
csEthStatsRxSysErrCounts.description: The counter associated with the number of received packets during which PHY symbol errors were detected.

csEthStatsTx1024Pkts.name: csEthStatsTx1024Pkts
csEthStatsTx1024Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of transmitted packets 1024 bytes or more in length, including bad packets. It's only for Giga bit Ethernet card.

csEthStatsRx1024Pkts.name: csEthStatsRx1024Pkts
csEthStatsRx1024Pkts.description: The counter associated with the number of packets 1024 bytes or more in length, including bad packets. It's only for Giga bit Ethernet card.

csDs3StatCurrentTable.name: csDs3StatCurrentTable
csDs3StatCurrentTable.description: The DS3/E3 current table contains various statistics being collected for the current 15 minute interval.

csDs3StatCurrentEntry.name: csDs3StatCurrentEntry
csDs3StatCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the DS3/E3 Current table.

csDs3StatCurrentPESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentPESs
csDs3StatCurrentPESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentPSESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentPSESs
csDs3StatCurrentPSESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentSEFSs.name: csDs3StatCurrentSEFSs
csDs3StatCurrentSEFSs.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentUASs.name: csDs3StatCurrentUASs
csDs3StatCurrentUASs.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentLCVs.name: csDs3StatCurrentLCVs
csDs3StatCurrentLCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of Line Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentPCVs.name: csDs3StatCurrentPCVs
csDs3StatCurrentPCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentLESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentLESs
csDs3StatCurrentLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentCCVs.name: csDs3StatCurrentCCVs
csDs3StatCurrentCCVs.description: The number of C-bit Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentCESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentCESs
csDs3StatCurrentCESs.description: The number of C-bit Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentCSESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentCSESs
csDs3StatCurrentCSESs.description: The number of C-bit Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatCurrentLSESs.name: csDs3StatCurrentLSESs
csDs3StatCurrentLSESs.description: The number of Line Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalTable.name: csDs3StatIntervalTable
csDs3StatIntervalTable.description: The DS3/E3 Interval Table contains various statistics collected by each DS3/E3 Interface over the previous 24 hours of operation. The past 24 hours are broken into 96 completed 15 minute intervals. Each row in this table represents one such interval (identified by csDs3StatIntervalNumber) and for one specific DS3 port (identifed by csDs3ConfigPortIndex).

csDs3StatIntervalEntry.name: csDs3StatIntervalEntry
csDs3StatIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3/E3 Interval table.

csDs3StatIntervalNumber.name: csDs3StatIntervalNumber
csDs3StatIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the 15 minutes interval completed 23 hours and 45 minutes prior to interval 1.

csDs3StatIntervalPESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalPESs
csDs3StatIntervalPESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalPSESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalPSESs
csDs3StatIntervalPSESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalSEFSs.name: csDs3StatIntervalSEFSs
csDs3StatIntervalSEFSs.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable for both DS3 and E3.

csDs3StatIntervalUASs.name: csDs3StatIntervalUASs
csDs3StatIntervalUASs.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds. This object may decrease if the occurance of unavailable seconds occurs across an inteval boundary. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalLCVs.name: csDs3StatIntervalLCVs
csDs3StatIntervalLCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of Line Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalPCVs.name: csDs3StatIntervalPCVs
csDs3StatIntervalPCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalLESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalLESs
csDs3StatIntervalLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds (BPVs or illegal zero sequences). NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalCCVs.name: csDs3StatIntervalCCVs
csDs3StatIntervalCCVs.description: The number of C-bit Coding Violations. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalCESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalCESs
csDs3StatIntervalCESs.description: The number of C-bit Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalCSESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalCSESs
csDs3StatIntervalCSESs.description: The number of C-bit Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalLSESs.name: csDs3StatIntervalLSESs
csDs3StatIntervalLSESs.description: The number of Line Severely Errored Seconds. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatIntervalValidData.name: csDs3StatIntervalValidData
csDs3StatIntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

csDs3StatTotalTable.name: csDs3StatTotalTable
csDs3StatTotalTable.description: The DS3/E3 Total Table contains the cumulative sum of the various statistics for the 24 hour period preceding the current interval.

csDs3StatTotalEntry.name: csDs3StatTotalEntry
csDs3StatTotalEntry.description: An entry in the DS3/E3 Total table.

csDs3StatTotalPESs.name: csDs3StatTotalPESs
csDs3StatTotalPESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Errored Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalPSESs.name: csDs3StatTotalPSESs
csDs3StatTotalPSESs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Severely Errored Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalSEFSs.name: csDs3StatTotalSEFSs
csDs3StatTotalSEFSs.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds, encountered by a DS3/E3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalUASs.name: csDs3StatTotalUASs
csDs3StatTotalUASs.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds, encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalLCVs.name: csDs3StatTotalLCVs
csDs3StatTotalLCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of Line Coding Violations encountered by a DS3/E3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatTotalPCVs.name: csDs3StatTotalPCVs
csDs3StatTotalPCVs.description: The counter associated with the number of P-bit Coding Violations, encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalLESs.name: csDs3StatTotalLESs
csDs3StatTotalLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds (BPVs or illegal zero sequences) encountered by a DS3/E3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3StatTotalCCVs.name: csDs3StatTotalCCVs
csDs3StatTotalCCVs.description: The number of C-bit Coding Violations encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalCESs.name: csDs3StatTotalCESs
csDs3StatTotalCESs.description: The number of C-bit Errored Seconds encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalCSESs.name: csDs3StatTotalCSESs
csDs3StatTotalCSESs.description: The number of C-bit Severely Errored Seconds encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24-hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csDs3StatTotalLSESs.name: csDs3StatTotalLSESs
csDs3StatTotalLSESs.description: The number of Line Severely Errored Seconds encountered by a DS3 interface in the previous 24-hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0. NOTE: This is applicable for both E3 and DS3.

csDs3Ds1CurrentTable.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentTable
csDs3Ds1CurrentTable.description: The DS1 current table contains various statistics being collected for the current 15 minute interval.

csDs3Ds1CurrentEntry.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentEntry
csDs3Ds1CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Current table.

csDs3Ds1CurrentSESs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentSESs
csDs3Ds1CurrentSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1CurrentSEFSs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentSEFSs
csDs3Ds1CurrentSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds.

csDs3Ds1CurrentCSSs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentCSSs
csDs3Ds1CurrentCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds.

csDs3Ds1CurrentPCVs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentPCVs
csDs3Ds1CurrentPCVs.description: The number of Path Coding Violations.

csDs3Ds1CurrentLESs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentLESs
csDs3Ds1CurrentLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1CurrentBESs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentBESs
csDs3Ds1CurrentBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1CurrentLCVs.name: csDs3Ds1CurrentLCVs
csDs3Ds1CurrentLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs).

csDs3Ds1IntervalTable.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalTable
csDs3Ds1IntervalTable.description: The DS1 Interval Table contains various statistics collected by each DS1 Interface over the previous 24 hours of operation. The past 24 hours are broken into 96 completed 15 minute intervals. Each row in this table represents one such interval (identified by csDs3Ds1IntervalNumber) for one specific instance (identified by csDs3Ds1Id).

csDs3Ds1IntervalEntry.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalEntry
csDs3Ds1IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

csDs3Ds1IntervalNumber.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalNumber
csDs3Ds1IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the 15 minutes interval completed 23 hours and 45 minutes prior to interval 1.

csDs3Ds1IntervalSESs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalSESs
csDs3Ds1IntervalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1IntervalSEFSs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalSEFSs
csDs3Ds1IntervalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds.

csDs3Ds1IntervalUASs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalUASs
csDs3Ds1IntervalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds. This object may decrease if the occurance of unavailable seconds occurs across an inteval boundary.

csDs3Ds1IntervalCSSs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalCSSs
csDs3Ds1IntervalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds.

csDs3Ds1IntervalPCVs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalPCVs
csDs3Ds1IntervalPCVs.description: The number of Path Coding Violations.

csDs3Ds1IntervalLESs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalLESs
csDs3Ds1IntervalLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1IntervalBESs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalBESs
csDs3Ds1IntervalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds.

csDs3Ds1IntervalLCVs.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalLCVs
csDs3Ds1IntervalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations.

csDs3Ds1IntervalValidData.name: csDs3Ds1IntervalValidData
csDs3Ds1IntervalValidData.description: This variable indicates if the data for this interval is valid.

csDs3Ds1TotalTable.name: csDs3Ds1TotalTable
csDs3Ds1TotalTable.description: The DS1 Total Table contains the cumulative sum of the various statistics for the 24 hour period preceding the current interval.

csDs3Ds1TotalEntry.name: csDs3Ds1TotalEntry
csDs3Ds1TotalEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Total table.

csDs3Ds1TotalESs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalESs
csDs3Ds1TotalESs.description: The sum of Errored Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalSESs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalSESs
csDs3Ds1TotalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalSEFSs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalSEFSs
csDs3Ds1TotalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalUASs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalUASs
csDs3Ds1TotalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalCSSs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalCSSs
csDs3Ds1TotalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalPCVs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalPCVs
csDs3Ds1TotalPCVs.description: The number of Path Coding Violations encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalLESs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalLESs
csDs3Ds1TotalLESs.description: The number of Line Errored Seconds encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalBESs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalBESs
csDs3Ds1TotalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalDMs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalDMs
csDs3Ds1TotalDMs.description: The number of Degraded Minutes (DMs) encountered by a DS1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csDs3Ds1TotalLCVs.name: csDs3Ds1TotalLCVs
csDs3Ds1TotalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. Invalid 15 minute intervals count as 0.

csUnchanDs3ConfigEntry.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigEntry
csUnchanDs3ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Unchannelized DS3 Configuration table.

csUnchanDs3ConfigSlotIndex.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigSlotIndex
csUnchanDs3ConfigSlotIndex.description: This object identifies the blade to which this Unchannelized Ds3 Port is attached. Together with csUnchanDs3ConfigPortIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csUnchanDs3ConfigModuleIndex.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigModuleIndex
csUnchanDs3ConfigModuleIndex.description: This object identifies the module on the Unchannelized Ds3 Blade.

csUnchanDs3ConfigPortIndex.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigPortIndex
csUnchanDs3ConfigPortIndex.description: This object identifies the location of the Unchannelized Ds3 Port on the blade identified by csUnchanDs3SlotIndex. Together with csUnchanDs3ConfigSlotIndex, it uniquely identifies a physical port.

csUnchanDs3ConfigCableLength.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigCableLength
csUnchanDs3ConfigCableLength.description: The length of the DS3 cable.

csUnchanDs3ConfigFraming.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigFraming
csUnchanDs3ConfigFraming.description: The framing format used on this Ds3 Interface. The default value is cbit if the interface is DS3. If the interface is E3, e3Framed will be used, and cannot be configured to any other types.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPath.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPath
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPath.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Path message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlIdleSig.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Idle Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlTestSig.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlTestSig
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlTestSig.description: This object controls the transmission of the MDL Test Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlEic.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlEic
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlEic.description: This object specifies the Equipment Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlLic.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlLic
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlLic.description: This object specifies the Location Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlFic.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlFic
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlFic.description: This object specifies the Frame Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlUnit.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlUnit
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlUnit.description: This object specifies the Unit Identification Code. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPfi.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPfi
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPfi.description: This object specifies the Facility Identification Code sent in the MDL Path message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPort.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPort
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlPort.description: This object specifies the Port number string sent in the MDL Idle Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlGenerator.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlGenerator
csUnchanDs3ConfigMdlGenerator.description: This object specifies the Generator number string sent in the MDL Test Signal message. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigAdminStatus.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigAdminStatus
csUnchanDs3ConfigAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable this Ds3/E3 port.

csUnchanDs3ConfigOperStatus.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigOperStatus
csUnchanDs3ConfigOperStatus.description: This object indicates the current operational status of this Ds3/E3 port.

csUnchanDs3ConfigClockSource.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigClockSource
csUnchanDs3ConfigClockSource.description: This object specifies the source of the Transmit Clock used on this (unchannelized) DS3. If this object is set to internal(1), a local clock source is used. If this object is set to line(2), the recovered received clock is used as the transmit clock. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3.

csUnchanDs3ConfigEncap.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigEncap
csUnchanDs3ConfigEncap.description: This object specifies the encapsulation used on this DS3/E3 port. If the encapsulation type is frameRelay(2), use the csFrameRelayTable to configure the Frame Relay specific parameters.

csUnchanDs3ConfigSendCode.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigSendCode
csUnchanDs3ConfigSendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS3 interface by the device. Setting this variable causes the interface to begin sending the code requested. NOTE: This is applicable only for DS3. The values mean: sendNoCode sending looped or normal data sendLineCode sending a request for a line loopback sendResetCode sending a loopback deactivation request

csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackType.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackType
csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackType.description: This object represents the desired loopback configuration of the DS3 interface. The values mean: noLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as its value. lineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out. otherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here. Currently not used in the IPSX system. inwardLoop The sent signal at this interface is looped back through the device. dualLoop Both lineLoop and inwardLoop will be active simultaneously.

csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus
csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus.description: This variable represents the current state of the loopback on the DS3 interface. It contains information about loopbacks established by a manager and remotely from the far end. The csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore is can represent multiple loopbacks simultaneously. The various bit positions are: 1 ds3NoLoopback 2 ds3NearEndPayloadLoopback 4 ds3NearEndLineLoopback 8 ds3NearEndOtherLoopback 16 ds3NearEndInwardLoopback 32 ds3FarEndPayloadLoopback 64 ds3FarEndLineLoopback

csUnchanDs3ConfigLineStatus.name: csUnchanDs3ConfigLineStatus
csUnchanDs3ConfigLineStatus.description: This variable indicates the Line Status of the interface. It contains loopback state information and failure state information. The csUnchanDs3ConfigLineStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple failures and a loopback (see csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus object for the type of loopback) simultaneously. The ds3NoAlarm must be set if and only if no other flag is set. If the ds3LoopbackState bit is set, the loopback in effect can be determined from the csUnchanDs3ConfigLoopbackStatus object.
