csOspfIfMetricEntry.name: csOspfIfMetricEntry
csOspfIfMetricEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
csOspfIfMetricEntry.description: A particular TOS metric for a non-virtual in- terface identified by the interface index.

csOspfIfMetricIpAddress.name: csOspfIfMetricIpAddress
csOspfIfMetricIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface. On row creation, this can be derived from the in- stance.

csOspfIfMetricAddressLessIf.name: csOspfIfMetricAddressLessIf
csOspfIfMetricAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the value of ifIndex for in- terfaces having no IP Address. On row crea- tion, this can be derived from the instance.

csOspfIfMetricTOS.name: csOspfIfMetricTOS
csOspfIfMetricTOS.description: The type of service metric being referenced. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

csOspfIfMetricValue.name: csOspfIfMetricValue
csOspfIfMetricValue.description: The metric of using this type of service on this interface. The default value of the TOS 0 Metric is 10^8 / ifSpeed.

csOspfIfMetricStatus.name: csOspfIfMetricStatus
csOspfIfMetricStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

csOspfVirtIfTable.name: csOspfVirtIfTable
csOspfVirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
csOspfVirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual inter- faces.

csOspfVirtIfEntry.name: csOspfVirtIfEntry
csOspfVirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

csOspfVirtIfAreaId.name: csOspfVirtIfAreaId
csOspfVirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

csOspfVirtIfNeighbor.name: csOspfVirtIfNeighbor
csOspfVirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

csOspfVirtIfTransitDelay.name: csOspfVirtIfTransitDelay
csOspfVirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

csOspfVirtIfRetransInterval.name: csOspfVirtIfRetransInterval
csOspfVirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round- trip time.

csOspfVirtIfHelloInterval.name: csOspfVirtIfHelloInterval
csOspfVirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

csOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: csOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval
csOspfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neigh- bor.

csOspfVirtIfEvents.name: csOspfVirtIfEvents
csOspfVirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link

csOspfVirtIfAuthType.name: csOspfVirtIfAuthType
csOspfVirtIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for a virtu- al interface. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally.

csOspfVirtIfAuthKey.name: csOspfVirtIfAuthKey
csOspfVirtIfAuthKey.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure
csOspfVirtIfAuthKey.description: If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 oc- tets. Note that unauthenticated interfaces need no authentication key, and simple password authen- tication cannot use a key of more than 8 oc- tets. Larger keys are useful only with authen- tication mechanisms not specified in this docu- ment. When read, csOspfVifAuthKey always returns a string of length zero.

csOspfVirtIfStatus.name: csOspfVirtIfStatus
csOspfVirtIfStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

csOspfNbrTable.name: csOspfNbrTable
csOspfNbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
csOspfNbrTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information.

csOspfNbrEntry.name: csOspfNbrEntry
csOspfNbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure
csOspfNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

csOspfNbrIpAddr.name: csOspfNbrIpAddr
csOspfNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this neighbor is using in its IP Source Address. Note that, on addressless links, this will not be 0.0.0.0, but the ad- dress of another of the neighbor's interfaces.

csOspfNbrAddressLessIndex.name: csOspfNbrAddressLessIndex
csOspfNbrAddressLessIndex.description: On an interface having an IP Address, zero. On addressless interfaces, the corresponding value of ifIndex in the Internet Standard MIB. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

csOspfNbrRtrId.name: csOspfNbrRtrId
csOspfNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAd- dress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

csOspfNbrOptions.name: csOspfNbrOptions
csOspfNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's op- tions field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the associated area accepts and operates on external informa- tion; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 2, if set, indicates that the system is ca- pable of routing IP Multicast datagrams; i.e., that it implements the Multicast Extensions to OSPF. Bit 3, if set, indicates that the associated area is an NSSA. These areas are capable of carrying type 7 external advertisements, which are translated into type 5 external advertise- ments at NSSA borders.

csOspfNbrPriority.name: csOspfNbrPriority
csOspfNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designat- ed router election algorithm. The value 0 sig- nifies that the neighbor is not eligible to be- come the designated router on this particular network.

csOspfNbrState.name: csOspfNbrState
csOspfNbrState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neigh- bor.

csOspfNbrEvents.name: csOspfNbrEvents
csOspfNbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.

csOspfNbrLsRetransQLen.name: csOspfNbrLsRetransQLen
csOspfNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

csOspfNbmaNbrStatus.name: csOspfNbmaNbrStatus
csOspfNbmaNbrStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

csOspfNbmaNbrPermanence.name: csOspfNbmaNbrPermanence
csOspfNbmaNbrPermanence.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. 'dynamic' and 'permanent' refer to how the neighbor became known.

csOspfNbrHelloSuppressed.name: csOspfNbrHelloSuppressed
csOspfNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

csOspfVirtNbrTable.name: csOspfVirtNbrTable
csOspfVirtNbrTable.description: A table of virtual neighbor information.

csOspfVirtNbrRtrId.name: csOspfVirtNbrRtrId
csOspfVirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

csOspfVirtNbrIpAddr.name: csOspfVirtNbrIpAddr
csOspfVirtNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this Virtual Neighbor is us- ing.

csOspfVirtNbrOptions.name: csOspfVirtNbrOptions
csOspfVirtNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's op- tions field. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric. Bit 2, if set, indicates that the system is Network Multicast capable; ie, that it imple- ments OSPF Multicast Routing.

csOspfVirtNbrState.name: csOspfVirtNbrState
csOspfVirtNbrState.description: The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relation- ship.

csOspfVirtNbrEvents.name: csOspfVirtNbrEvents
csOspfVirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

csOspfVirtNbrLsRetransQLen.name: csOspfVirtNbrLsRetransQLen
csOspfVirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

csOspfVirtNbrHelloSuppressed.name: csOspfVirtNbrHelloSuppressed
csOspfVirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor

csOspfExtLsdbTable.name: csOspfExtLsdbTable
csOspfExtLsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
csOspfExtLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Links State Database.

csOspfExtLsdbType.name: csOspfExtLsdbType
csOspfExtLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
csOspfExtLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format.

csOspfExtLsdbLsid.name: csOspfExtLsdbLsid
csOspfExtLsdbLsid.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4 Link State ID
csOspfExtLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

csOspfExtLsdbRouterId.name: csOspfExtLsdbRouterId
csOspfExtLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters
csOspfExtLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

csOspfExtLsdbSequence.name: csOspfExtLsdbSequence
csOspfExtLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
csOspfExtLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

csOspfExtLsdbAge.name: csOspfExtLsdbAge
csOspfExtLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

csOspfExtLsdbChecksum.name: csOspfExtLsdbChecksum
csOspfExtLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

csOspfExtLsdbAdvertisement.name: csOspfExtLsdbAdvertisement
csOspfExtLsdbAdvertisement.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
csOspfExtLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

csOspfAreaAggregateTable.name: csOspfAreaAggregateTable
csOspfAreaAggregateTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
csOspfAreaAggregateTable.description: A range of IP addresses specified by an IP address/IP network mask pair. For example, class B address range of X.X.X.X with a network mask of 255.255.0.0 includes all IP addresses from X.X.0.0 to X.X.255.255. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range sub- sumes another range (e.g., 10.0.0.0 mask 255.0.0.0 and 10.1.0.0 mask 255.255.0.0), the most specific match is the preferred one.

csOspfAreaAggregateEntry.name: csOspfAreaAggregateEntry
csOspfAreaAggregateEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
csOspfAreaAggregateEntry.description: A range of IP addresses specified by an IP address/IP network mask pair. For example, class B address range of X.X.X.X with a network mask of 255.255.0.0 includes all IP addresses from X.X.0.0 to X.X.255.255. Note that if ranges are range configured such that one range subsumes another range (e.g., 10.0.0.0 mask 255.0.0.0 and 10.1.0.0 mask 255.255.0.0), the most specific match is the preferred one.

csOspfAreaAggregateAreaID.name: csOspfAreaAggregateAreaID
csOspfAreaAggregateAreaID.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
csOspfAreaAggregateAreaID.description: The Area the Address Aggregate is to be found within.

csOspfAreaAggregateLsdbType.name: csOspfAreaAggregateLsdbType
csOspfAreaAggregateLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header
csOspfAreaAggregateLsdbType.description: The type of the Address Aggregate. This field specifies the Lsdb type that this Address Ag- gregate applies to.

csOspfAreaAggregateNet.name: csOspfAreaAggregateNet
csOspfAreaAggregateNet.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
csOspfAreaAggregateNet.description: The IP Address of the Net or Subnet indicated by the range.

csOspfAreaAggregateMask.name: csOspfAreaAggregateMask
csOspfAreaAggregateMask.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
csOspfAreaAggregateMask.description: The Subnet Mask that pertains to the Net or Subnet.

csOspfAreaAggregateStatus.name: csOspfAreaAggregateStatus
csOspfAreaAggregateStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

csOspfAreaAggregateEffect.name: csOspfAreaAggregateEffect
csOspfAreaAggregateEffect.description: Subnets subsumed by ranges either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (ad- vertiseMatching), or result in the subnet's not being advertised at all outside the area.

csOspfImpPolTable.name: csOspfImpPolTable
csOspfImpPolTable.description: A set of Import Policies (see csImpPolTable) that are applied by ospf.

csOspfImpPolEntry.name: csOspfImpPolEntry
csOspfImpPolEntry.description: Each entry represents a single import policy applied by the ospf layer on a Virtual Router.

csOspfImpPolId.name: csOspfImpPolId
csOspfImpPolId.description: The Import Policy (see the corresponding entry in csImpPolTable) that is applied to this Virtual Router.

csOspfImpPolStatus.name: csOspfImpPolStatus
csOspfImpPolStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add and delete entries from this table.

csOspfExpPolTable.name: csOspfExpPolTable
csOspfExpPolTable.description: A set of Export Policies (see csExpPolTable) that are applied by ospf.

csOspfExpPolEntry.name: csOspfExpPolEntry
csOspfExpPolEntry.description: Each entry represents a single import policy applied by the ospf layer on a Virtual Router.

csOspfExpPolId.name: csOspfExpPolId
csOspfExpPolId.description: The Export Policy (see the corresponding entry in csExpPolTable) that is applied to this Virtual Router.

csOspfExpPolStatus.name: csOspfExpPolStatus
csOspfExpPolStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add and delete entries from this table.

csOspfSetTrap.name: csOspfSetTrap
csOspfSetTrap.description: A four-octet string serving as a bit map for the trap events defined by the OSPF traps. This object is used to enable and disable specific OSPF traps where a 1 in the bit field represents enabled. The right-most bit (least significant) represents trap 0.

csOspfConfigErrorType.name: csOspfConfigErrorType
csOspfConfigErrorType.description: Potential types of configuration conflicts. Used by the csOspfConfigError and csOspfConfigVir- tError traps.

csOspfPacketSrc.name: csOspfPacketSrc
csOspfPacketSrc.description: The IP address of an inbound packet that can- not be identified by a neighbor instance.

csOrionOspfEnd.name: csOrionOspfEnd
csOrionOspfEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csRipGlobalStatTable.name: csRipGlobalStatTable
csRipGlobalStatTable.description: This table contains per-VR level stats for RIP. These counters are intended to facilitate debugging quickly changing routes or failing neighbors.

csRipGlobalStatEntry.name: csRipGlobalStatEntry
csRipGlobalStatEntry.description: Each entry contains a set of statistics for a specific Virtual Router.

csRipGlobalRouteChanges.name: csRipGlobalRouteChanges
csRipGlobalRouteChanges.description: The number of route changes made to the IP Route Database by RIP. This does not include the refresh of a route's age.

csRipGlobalQueries.name: csRipGlobalQueries
csRipGlobalQueries.description: The number of responses sent to RIP queries from other systems.

csRipIfStatTable.name: csRipIfStatTable
csRipIfStatTable.description: A list of subnets which require separate status monitoring in RIP.

csRipIfStatEntry.name: csRipIfStatEntry
csRipIfStatEntry.description: A Single Routing Domain in a single Subnet.

csRipIfStatRcvBadPackets.name: csRipIfStatRcvBadPackets
csRipIfStatRcvBadPackets.description: The number of RIP response packets received by the RIP process which were subsequently discarded for any reason (e.g. a version 0 packet, or an unknown command type).

csRipIfStatRcvBadRoutes.name: csRipIfStatRcvBadRoutes
csRipIfStatRcvBadRoutes.description: The number of routes, in valid RIP packets, which were ignored for any reason (e.g. unknown address family, or invalid metric).

csRipIfStatSentUpdates.name: csRipIfStatSentUpdates
csRipIfStatSentUpdates.description: The number of triggered RIP updates actually sent on this interface. This explicitly does NOT include full updates sent containing new information.

csRipIfStatTableEnd.name: csRipIfStatTableEnd
csRipIfStatTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csRipGlobalConfTable.name: csRipGlobalConfTable
csRipGlobalConfTable.description: A table of virtual router-specific configuration parameters.

csRipGlobalConfEntry.name: csRipGlobalConfEntry
csRipGlobalConfEntry.description: Each entry contains a set of configuration specific to a single virtual router.

csRipGlobalConfStatus.name: csRipGlobalConfStatus
csRipGlobalConfStatus.description: Enable/Disable the use of RIP on this Virtual Router.

csRipGlobalConfJitterUpdateStatus.name: csRipGlobalConfJitterUpdateStatus
csRipGlobalConfJitterUpdateStatus.description: Enable/Disable the use of the Jitter Update feature

csRipGlobalConfRfc1058CalcStatus.name: csRipGlobalConfRfc1058CalcStatus
csRipGlobalConfRfc1058CalcStatus.description: Enable/Disable the use of the route metric calculation defined in rfc1058.

csRipGlobalConfReqOnStartup.name: csRipGlobalConfReqOnStartup
csRipGlobalConfReqOnStartup.description: Enable/Disable the use of the request on startup feature.

csRipGlobalConfRowStatus.name: csRipGlobalConfRowStatus
csRipGlobalConfRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this object. This is used to add/delete rows from this table. Setting it to create and go creates RIP on this Virtual Router. Setting it to destroy removes RIP from this Virtual Router.

csRipGlobalConfLogAreaFlag.name: csRipGlobalConfLogAreaFlag
csRipGlobalConfLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within RIP. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within RIP and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ packet 0 policy 1 end of description.

csRipGlobalConfLogLevelFlag.name: csRipGlobalConfLogLevelFlag
csRipGlobalConfLogLevelFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables logging at a specific level for RIP. Below is a list of the different log levels available and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ critical 0 error 1 warning 2 information 3 debug 4 end of description.

csRipIfConfTable.name: csRipIfConfTable
csRipIfConfTable.description: A list of virtual interfaces which require separate configuration in RIP.

csRipIfConfEntry.name: csRipIfConfEntry
csRipIfConfEntry.description: A Single Routing Domain in a single Subnet.

csRipIfConfStatus.name: csRipIfConfStatus
csRipIfConfStatus.description: Enable/Disable the use of RIP on this Virtual Interface.

csRipIfConfSend.name: csRipIfConfSend
csRipIfConfSend.description: Enable/Disable the sending of RIP advertisements on this Virtual Interface.

csRipIfConfReceiveV1.name: csRipIfConfReceiveV1
csRipIfConfReceiveV1.description: Enable/Disable the receiving of RIP V1 advertisements on this Virtual Interface.

csRipIfConfReceiveV2.name: csRipIfConfReceiveV2
csRipIfConfReceiveV2.description: Enable/Disable the receiving of RIP V2 advertisements on this Virtual Interface.

csRipIfConfSendDefRoute.name: csRipIfConfSendDefRoute
csRipIfConfSendDefRoute.description: Enable/Disable the advertisement of default routes.

csRipIfConfRcvDefRoute.name: csRipIfConfRcvDefRoute
csRipIfConfRcvDefRoute.description: Enable/Disable the acceptance of advertised default routes.

csRipIfConfAuthPassword.name: csRipIfConfAuthPassword
csRipIfConfAuthPassword.description: The password used in RIPv2 authentication. This object will return a zero length string in response to GET or GETNEXT requests.

csRipIfConfRowStatus.name: csRipIfConfRowStatus
csRipIfConfRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this object. This is used to add/delete rows from this table. Setting it to create and go creates RIP on this Virtual Interface. Setting it to destroy removes RIP from this Virtual Interface.

csRipImpPolTable.name: csRipImpPolTable
csRipImpPolTable.description: A set of Export Policies (see csExpPolTable) that are applied by rip.

csRipImpPolEntry.name: csRipImpPolEntry
csRipImpPolEntry.description: Each entry represents a single import policy applied by the rip layer on a Virtual Router.

csRipImpPolId.name: csRipImpPolId
csRipImpPolId.description: The Import Policy (see the corresponding entry in csImpPolTable) that is applied to this Virtual Router.

csRipImpPolStatus.name: csRipImpPolStatus
csRipImpPolStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add and delete entries from this table.

csRipExpPolTable.name: csRipExpPolTable
csRipExpPolTable.description: A set of Export Policies (see csExpPolTable) that are applied by rip.

csRipExpPolEntry.name: csRipExpPolEntry
csRipExpPolEntry.description: Each entry represents a single import policy applied by the rip layer on a Virtual Router.

csRipExpPolId.name: csRipExpPolId
csRipExpPolId.description: The Export Policy (see the corresponding entry in csExpPolTable) that is applied to this Virtual Router.

csRipExpPolStatus.name: csRipExpPolStatus
csRipExpPolStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add and delete entries from this table.

csOrionRipEnd.name: csOrionRipEnd
csOrionRipEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEntry.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEntry
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEntry.description: The entry of the table of TCP Parameters.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoAlgorithm.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoAlgorithm
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoAlgorithm.description: The algorithm used to determine the timeout value used for retransmitting unacknowledged octets.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMin.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMin
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMin.description: The minimum value permitted by a TCP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. In particular, when the timeout algorithm is rsre(3), an object of this type has the semantics of the LBOUND quantity described in RFC 793.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMax.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMax
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRtoMax.description: The maximum value permitted by a TCP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. In particular, when the timeout algorithm is rsre(3), an object of this type has the semantics of the UBOUND quantity described in RFC 793.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpMaxConn.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpMaxConn
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpMaxConn.description: The limit on the total number of TCP connections the entity can support. In entities where the maximum number of connections is dynamic, this object should contain the value -1.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpActiveOpens.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpActiveOpens
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpActiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-SENT state from the CLOSED state.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpPassiveOpens.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpPassiveOpens
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpPassiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-RCVD state from the LISTEN state.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpAttemptFails.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpAttemptFails
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpAttemptFails.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SYN-SENT state or the SYN-RCVD state, plus the number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the LISTEN state from the SYN-RCVD state.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEstabResets.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEstabResets
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpEstabResets.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the ESTABLISHED state or the CLOSE-WAIT state.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpCurrEstab.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpCurrEstab
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpCurrEstab.description: The number of TCP connections for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED or CLOSE- WAIT.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInSegs.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInSegs
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInSegs.description: The total number of segments received, including those received in error. This count includes segments received on currently established connections.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutSegs.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutSegs
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutSegs.description: The total number of segments sent, including those on current connections but excluding those containing only retransmitted octets.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRetransSegs.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRetransSegs
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpRetransSegs.description: The total number of segments retransmitted - that is, the number of TCP segments transmitted containing one or more previously transmitted octets.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInErrs.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInErrs
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpInErrs.description: The total number of segments received in error (e.g., bad TCP checksums).

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutRsts.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutRsts
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpOutRsts.description: The number of TCP segments sent containing the RST flag.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnTable.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnTable
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnEntry.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnEntry
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnState.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnState
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnState.description: The state of this TCP connection. The only value which may be set by a management station is deleteTCB(12). Accordingly, it is appropriate for an agent to return a `badValue' response if a management station attempts to set this object to any other value. If a management station sets this object to the value deleteTCB(12), then this has the effect of deleting the TCB (as defined in RFC 793) of the corresponding connection on the managed node, resulting in immediate termination of the connection. As an implementation-specific option, a RST segment may be sent from the managed node to the other TCP endpoint (note however that RST egments are not sent reliably).

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalAddress.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalAddress
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this TCP connection. In the case of a connection in the listen state which is willing to accept connections for any IP interface associated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalPort.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalPort
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnLocalPort.description: The local port number for this TCP connection.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemAddress.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemAddress
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemAddress.description: The remote IP address for this TCP connection.

csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemPort.name: csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemPort
csOrionVPNVRouterTcpConnRemPort.description: The remote port number for this TCP connection.

csOrionTcpEnd.name: csOrionTcpEnd
csOrionTcpEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpTable.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpTable
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpEntry.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpEntry
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInDatagrams.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInDatagrams
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams delivered to UDP users.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpNoPorts.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpNoPorts
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpNoPorts.description: The total number of received UDP datagrams for which there was no application at the destination port.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInErrors.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInErrors
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpInErrors.description: The number of received UDP datagrams that could not be delivered for reasons other than the lack of an application at the destination port.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpOutDatagrams.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpOutDatagrams
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpOutDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams sent from this entity.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerTable.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerTable
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerEntry.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerEntry
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this Orion's IP addresses.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalAddress.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalAddress
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this UDP listener. In the case of a UDP listener which is willing to accept datagrams for any IP interface associated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalPort.name: csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalPort
csOrionVPNVRouterUdpListenerLocalPort.description: The local port number for this UDP listener.

csOrionUdpEnd.name: csOrionUdpEnd
csOrionUdpEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csBgpGenTable.name: csBgpGenTable
csBgpGenTable.description: This table contains general, virtual router specific, BGP information.

csBgpGenEntry.name: csBgpGenEntry
csBgpGenEntry.description: Each entry contains general, virtual router specific BGP information for a single virtual router.

csBgpGenStatus.name: csBgpGenStatus
csBgpGenStatus.description: This object controls the operation of BGP as a whole on this virtual router.

csBgpGenLocalAS.name: csBgpGenLocalAS
csBgpGenLocalAS.description: The local autonomous system number of this virtual router. This object will have a value of 0 if bgp is disabled. If bgp is enabled, this object cannot be set to 0.

csBgpGenClearConn.name: csBgpGenClearConn
csBgpGenClearConn.description: This object is used to clear one of the existing BGP connections. To clear a single connection, enter the ip address of the remote end of the connection. When this object is read (get, getnext), the value 0.0.0.0 will be returned.

csBgpGenDefaultMetric.name: csBgpGenDefaultMetric
csBgpGenDefaultMetric.description: The default metric used by the system. default value is -1 which indicates that the metric is not configured

csBgpGenDefaultLocalPref.name: csBgpGenDefaultLocalPref
csBgpGenDefaultLocalPref.description: Default local preference of this BGP speaker default value is 100.

csBgpGenConfedId.name: csBgpGenConfedId
csBgpGenConfedId.description: The ConfedId of this system. -1 indicates no confedId has been configured.

csBgpGenDampEnable.name: csBgpGenDampEnable
csBgpGenDampEnable.description: This attribute is used to enable/disable route flap damping on this virtual router.

csBgpGenDampHalfLife.name: csBgpGenDampHalfLife
csBgpGenDampHalfLife.description: The time in seconds after which the penalty associated with a flapping route is reduced by one half. default value is 15 mintues.

csBgpGenDampReuse.name: csBgpGenDampReuse
csBgpGenDampReuse.description: If the penalty of a flapping route that has been suppressed falls below the value configured by this attribute, then the route is unsuppressed. Default is 2.

csBgpGenDampSuppress.name: csBgpGenDampSuppress
csBgpGenDampSuppress.description: If the penalty of a flapping route exceeds the value configured by this atttribute, the route is suppressed. Default is 3.

csBgpGenDampMaxSuppress.name: csBgpGenDampMaxSuppress
csBgpGenDampMaxSuppress.description: The maximum time that the route can be suppressed. Default is 16.

csBgpGenRowStatus.name: csBgpGenRowStatus
csBgpGenRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpGenLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpGenLogAreaFlag
csBgpGenLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within BGP. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within BGP and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ packet (all packets) 0 open (open packets) 1 update (update packets) 2 keepalive (keepalive packets) 3 notify (notify packets) 4 system (all system operations) 5 vpn-update (all vpn operations) 6 end of description.

csBgpGenLogLevelFlag.name: csBgpGenLogLevelFlag
csBgpGenLogLevelFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables logging at a specific level for BGP. Below is a list of the different log levels available and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ critical 0 error 1 warning 2 information 3 debug 4 end of description.

csBgpGenClearConnFlag.name: csBgpGenClearConnFlag
csBgpGenClearConnFlag.description: This object is used to indicate the set of BGP connections that need to be cleared. If set to 'nbr' the 'csBgpNbrClearConn' attribute must be set. If set to 'nbrGroup' the csBgpNbrClearNbrGroupName' must be set. When this object is read the value 'none' will be returned.

csBgpGenClearNbrGroupName.name: csBgpGenClearNbrGroupName
csBgpGenClearNbrGroupName.description: This object is used to clear all the BGP connections that belong to the specified peer group.

csBgpGenHoldTimeConfigured.name: csBgpGenHoldTimeConfigured
csBgpGenHoldTimeConfigured.description: The configured holdtime to use with all the Neighbors. default value of -1 indicates that this attribute has not been configured (default value used will be 180 seconds). The timers configured for a Nbr or NbrGroup overrides timers configured for all BGP neighbors using this attribute

csBgpGenKeepAliveConfigured.name: csBgpGenKeepAliveConfigured
csBgpGenKeepAliveConfigured.description: The configured Keepalive to use with all the Neighbors. default value of -1 indicates that this attribute has not been configured (default value used will be 60 seconds). The timers configured for a Nbr or NbrGroup overrides timers configured for all BGP neighbors using this attribute

csBgpGenVpnLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpGenVpnLogAreaFlag
csBgpGenVpnLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables logging for a specific area within BGP/VPN module. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ inbound-routes (updates recv) 0 outbound-routes (updates sent) 1 system (all system operations) 2 vrf (BGP to VRF interface) 3 bgp-peer (BGP/VPN peer mmgt) 4 tunnel (PE-PE tunnel mmgt) 5 end of description.

csBgpGenMaxPfx.name: csBgpGenMaxPfx
csBgpGenMaxPfx.description: This attribute limits the maximum number of BGP routes that can be learnt. Any additional routes learnt from BGP will be 1. discarded and a warning message is generated. or 2. accepted and a warning message is generated -1 indicates that no maximum threshold has been set

csBgpGenMaxPfxThreshold.name: csBgpGenMaxPfxThreshold
csBgpGenMaxPfxThreshold.description: If this attribute is configured, then when the number of routes learnt from all BGP peer reaches this threshold (percentage of csBgpMaxPfx) then a warning message is generated.

csBgpGenMaxPfxType.name: csBgpGenMaxPfxType
csBgpGenMaxPfxType.description: This attribute indicates the action that needs to be taken when the number of routes learnt from the bgp reaches the max prefix limit configured via 'csBgpGenMaxPfx' attribute. If this attribute is not set explicitly, and 'csBgpGenMaxPfx' attribute is set, this attribute defaults to warning-and-discard.

csBgpGenTableEnd.name: csBgpGenTableEnd
csBgpGenTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csBgpNbrTable.name: csBgpNbrTable
csBgpNbrTable.description: This table contains information about the BGP Neighbors on each virtual router.

csBgpNbrEntry.name: csBgpNbrEntry
csBgpNbrEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single neighbor on a single virtual router.

csBgpNbrAddr.name: csBgpNbrAddr
csBgpNbrAddr.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP neighbor.

csBgpNbrId.name: csBgpNbrId
csBgpNbrId.description: The BGP Identifier of this entry's BGP neighbor.

csBgpNbrAdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrAdminStatus
csBgpNbrAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the BGP connection. A transition from 'stop' to 'start' will cause the BGP Start Event to be generated. A transition from 'start' to 'stop' will cause the BGP Stop Event to be generated. This parameter can be used to restart BGP peer connections.

csBgpNbrMd5Password.name: csBgpNbrMd5Password
csBgpNbrMd5Password.description: The Md5 password used to authenticate messages exchanged with this neighbor. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not configured, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrRowStatus
csBgpNbrRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpNbrGroupNm.name: csBgpNbrGroupNm
csBgpNbrGroupNm.description: The Group to which the peer belongs. If the peer is not configured to any group an empty string is returned.

csBgpNbrHoldTimeConfigured.name: csBgpNbrHoldTimeConfigured
csBgpNbrHoldTimeConfigured.description: The configured holdtime to use with this Neighbor default value of -1 indicates that this attribute has not been configured (default value used will be 180 seconds). If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrLocalAddr.name: csBgpNbrLocalAddr
csBgpNbrLocalAddr.description: The IpAddress to be used at the local end of the connection with the bgp peer. If set to 0.0.0.0 it indicates that the LocalAddr is not configured. If the Nbr belongs to a NbrGroup, group level value of this attribute will override any value configured here.

csBgpNbrNextHopSelf.name: csBgpNbrNextHopSelf
csBgpNbrNextHopSelf.description: To enable/disable this system to be the next hopself for an ebgp session with this peer. default is -1 which indicates not configured. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrMhopGw.name: csBgpNbrMhopGw
csBgpNbrMhopGw.description: To specify the gateway address if this ebgp neighbor is not directly connected to this system. If the MhopGw is set to 0.0.0.0, it indicates that the MhopGw is not configured. If the Nbr belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrPassive.name: csBgpNbrPassive
csBgpNbrPassive.description: If this attribute is set to enable then this BGP speaker will not try to open a connection with the neighbor. Instead it will wait for the neighbor to initiate a connection.

csBgpNbrMhopTTL.name: csBgpNbrMhopTTL
csBgpNbrMhopTTL.description: To specify the maximum TTL value for the TTL in the IP Header for BGP packets. This attribute is applicable only for ebgp sessions. This attribute deprecates csBgpNbrMhopGw attribute. If this attribute is configured for a IBGP peer it has no effect. If the Nbr belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute

csBgpNbrIpv4AdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrIpv4AdminStatus
csBgpNbrIpv4AdminStatus.description: If this attribute is set to disable then this BGP speaker will not try to send/recieve routes for IPv4 address family. The BGP speaker will participate in IPv4 address family with its peer only if this attribute is set to enable.

csBgpNbrVpnIpv4AdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrVpnIpv4AdminStatus
csBgpNbrVpnIpv4AdminStatus.description: If this attribute is set to disable then this BGP speaker will not try to send/recieve routes for VPN IPv4 address family. The BGP speaker will participate in VPN IPv4 address family with its peer only if this attribute is set to enable.

csBgpNbrKeepAliveConfigured.name: csBgpNbrKeepAliveConfigured
csBgpNbrKeepAliveConfigured.description: The configured keepalive to use with this Neighbor default value of -1 indicates that this attribute has not been configured (default value used will be 60 seconds). KeepAlive timer is normally derived from the negotiated holdtime and is 1/3 the value of negotiated holdtime. However if keepalive is configured the minmum of this value and 1/3 the value of negotiated holdtime is used. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrRemovePrivateAs.name: csBgpNbrRemovePrivateAs
csBgpNbrRemovePrivateAs.description: This attribute is used to strip private as numbers from the aspath advertised to the neighbor. This attribute is used only with EBGP neighbors. Configuring this attribute to an IBGP peer has no effect. default is -1 which indicates not configured. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute.

csBgpNbrLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpNbrLogAreaFlag
csBgpNbrLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within BGP Neighbor. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within BGP and their corresponding bits identifier. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute. If the group level value is not set (or the neighbor does not belong to a NbrGroup) bgp global level value is inherited. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ packet (all packets) 0 open (open packets) 1 update (update packets) 2 keepalive (keepalive packets) 3 notify (notify packets) 4 system (all system operations) 5 end of description.

csBgpNbrMaxPfx.name: csBgpNbrMaxPfx
csBgpNbrMaxPfx.description: This attribute is used to set the maximum number of prefixes that can be learnt from this neighbor. If the neighbor advertises more than this number set in this attribute, the neighbor connection is closed and the state is set to Idle. Connection is not restored until user does a clearConnection. If this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute

csBgpNbrVpnLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpNbrVpnLogAreaFlag
csBgpNbrVpnLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within BGP Neighbor related VPN routing. If the neighbor belongs to a NbrGroup and this attribute is not set, the Nbr inherits the group level value of this attribute. If the group level value is not set (or the neighbor does not belong to a NbrGroup) bgp global level value is inherited. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ inbound-routes (updates recv) 0 outbound-routes (updates sent) 1 end of description.

csBgpNbrMaxPfxThreshold.name: csBgpNbrMaxPfxThreshold
csBgpNbrMaxPfxThreshold.description: If this attribute is configured, then when the number of routes learnt from this peer reaches this threshold (percentage of csBgpNbrMaxPfx) then a warning message is generated.

csBgpNbrMaxPfxType.name: csBgpNbrMaxPfxType
csBgpNbrMaxPfxType.description: This attribute indicates the action that needs to be taken when the number of routes learnt from the neighbor reaches the max prefix limit configured via 'csBgpNbrMaxPfx' attribute. If this attribute is not set explicitly, and 'csBgpNbrMaxPfx' attribute is set, this attribute defaults to shutdown.

csBgpNbrImpPolTable.name: csBgpNbrImpPolTable
csBgpNbrImpPolTable.description: This table is used to configure the import policies applied to each BGP neighbor on each virtual router.

csBgpNbrImpPolEntry.name: csBgpNbrImpPolEntry
csBgpNbrImpPolEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single policy applied to a single virtual router's BGP neighbor.

csBgpNbrImpPolId.name: csBgpNbrImpPolId
csBgpNbrImpPolId.description: The identifier of the policy to apply to this neighbor. This identifies an entry in either the csBgpImpImpPolTable or the csBgpExpImpPolTable. If the Nbr belongs to a Group any import policies defined at the neighbor level overrides group level import policies. If no import policies are defined at the neighbor level group level policies are inherited.

csBgpNbrImpPolRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrImpPolRowStatus
csBgpNbrImpPolRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpNbrExpPolTable.name: csBgpNbrExpPolTable
csBgpNbrExpPolTable.description: This table is used to configure the import policies applied to each BGP neighbor on each virtual router.

csBgpNbrExpPolEntry.name: csBgpNbrExpPolEntry
csBgpNbrExpPolEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single policy applied to a single virtual router's BGP neighbor.

csBgpNbrExpPolId.name: csBgpNbrExpPolId
csBgpNbrExpPolId.description: The identifier of the policy to apply to this neighbor. This identifies an entry in either the csBgpExpExpPolTable or the csBgpExpExpPolTable. If the Nbr belongs to a NbrGroup then any Export policies configured to this Nbr are ignored.i.e. Export policies defined at the group level takes precedence

csBgpNbrExpPolRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrExpPolRowStatus
csBgpNbrExpPolRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpConfedASTable.name: csBgpConfedASTable
csBgpConfedASTable.description: This table maintains a list of AS's which belong to the same confederation as this virtual router.

csBgpConfedASEntry.name: csBgpConfedASEntry
csBgpConfedASEntry.description: Each entry contains as AS number which belongs to the same confederation as this virtual router.

csBgpConfedAS.name: csBgpConfedAS
csBgpConfedAS.description: This attribute identifies the AS which belongs to the same confederation as this virtual router.

csBgpConfedASRowStatus.name: csBgpConfedASRowStatus
csBgpConfedASRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpConfedASTableEnd.name: csBgpConfedASTableEnd
csBgpConfedASTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csBgpNetworkTable.name: csBgpNetworkTable
csBgpNetworkTable.description: This table maintains a list of IP Address/Mask which can be distributed from IGP into BGP.

csBgpNetworkEntry.name: csBgpNetworkEntry
csBgpNetworkEntry.description: Each entry contains an IP Address/Mask that need to be sent via BGP.

csBgpNetworkAddr.name: csBgpNetworkAddr
csBgpNetworkAddr.description: The IP Address that needs to be redistrubted to BGP.

csBgpNetworkMask.name: csBgpNetworkMask
csBgpNetworkMask.description: The IP Mask of the csBgpNetworkAddr that needs to be redistrubted to BGP.

csBgpNetworkRowStatus.name: csBgpNetworkRowStatus
csBgpNetworkRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpNetworkTableEnd.name: csBgpNetworkTableEnd
csBgpNetworkTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csBgpNbrGroupTable.name: csBgpNbrGroupTable
csBgpNbrGroupTable.description: This table contains information about the BGP Group's on a single virtual router.

csBgpNbrGroupEntry.name: csBgpNbrGroupEntry
csBgpNbrGroupEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single group on a single virtual router.

csBgpNbrGroupName.name: csBgpNbrGroupName
csBgpNbrGroupName.description: The Name of the BGP Group

csBgpNbrGroupAdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupAdminStatus
csBgpNbrGroupAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the BGP connection. A transition from 'stop' to 'start' will cause the BGP Start Event to be generated. A transition from 'start' to 'stop' will cause the BGP Stop Event to be generated. This parameter can be used to restart BGP peer connections in the bgp group.

csBgpNbrGroupRemoteAS.name: csBgpNbrGroupRemoteAS
csBgpNbrGroupRemoteAS.description: The remote autonomous system number of the group.

csBgpNbrGroupMd5Password.name: csBgpNbrGroupMd5Password
csBgpNbrGroupMd5Password.description: The Md5 password used to authenticate messages exchanged with the neighbors defined in the group. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrMd5Password Attribute

csBgpNbrGroupRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupRowStatus
csBgpNbrGroupRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpNbrGroupHoldTimeConfigured.name: csBgpNbrGroupHoldTimeConfigured
csBgpNbrGroupHoldTimeConfigured.description: The configured holdtime to be used by the neighbors in this group. default value is -1 which indicates this is not configured and the neighbors in the group will be use a value of 180 seconds. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrHoldTimeConfigured attribute.

csBgpNbrGroupLocalAddr.name: csBgpNbrGroupLocalAddr
csBgpNbrGroupLocalAddr.description: The IpAddress to be used at the local end of the connection with the bgp peers in this group. If the LocalAddr is set to 0.0.0.0, it indicates that the LocalAddr is not configured.

csBgpNbrGroupNextHopSelf.name: csBgpNbrGroupNextHopSelf
csBgpNbrGroupNextHopSelf.description: To enable/disable this system to be the next hopself for an ebgp session with the bgp peers in this group. default is -1 which indicates not configured and disabled. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrNextHopSelf attribute.

csBgpNbrGroupMhopGw.name: csBgpNbrGroupMhopGw
csBgpNbrGroupMhopGw.description: To specify the gateway address if the ebgp neighbors belonging to this group are not directly connected to this system. If the MhopGw is set to 0.0.0.0, it indicates that the MhopGw is not configured. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrMhopGw attribute.

csBgpNbrGroupMhopTTL.name: csBgpNbrGroupMhopTTL
csBgpNbrGroupMhopTTL.description: To specify the maximum TTL value for the TTL in the IP Header for BGP packets. This attribute is applicable only for ebgp sessions. This attribute deprecates csBgpNbrGroupMhopGw attribute. If this attribute is configured to an IBGP peer it has not effect. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrMhopTTL attribute

csBgpNbrGroupIpv4AdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupIpv4AdminStatus
csBgpNbrGroupIpv4AdminStatus.description: If this attribute is set to disable then this BGP speaker will not try to send/recieve routes for IPv4 address family. The BGP speaker will participate in IPv4 address family with its peer only if this attribute is set to enable.

csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AdminStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AdminStatus
csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AdminStatus.description: If this attribute is set to disable then this BGP speaker will not try to send/recieve routes for VPN IPv4 address family. The BGP speaker will participate in VPN IPv4 address family with its peer only if this attribute is set to enable.

csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowRfc2547Customer.name: csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowRfc2547Customers
csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowRfc2547Customer.description: This attribute specifies the scope of RFC2547bis customers provisioned by this BGP speaker. none : no rfc2547 customers all : all VRs which are requesting to participate other: access controlled by specifying explicit list of customers by name or group-names in csBgpVpnv4AccessMapTable.

csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowVrmodelCustomer.name: csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowVrmodelCustomers
csBgpNbrGroupVpnIpv4AllowVrmodelCustomer.description: This attribute specifies the scope of VR-model customers provisioned by this BGP speaker. none : no VR-model customers all : all VRs which are requesting to participate other: access controlled by specifying explicit list of customers by name or group-names in csBgpVpnv4AccessMapTable.

csBgpNbrGroupKeepAliveConfigured.name: csBgpNbrGroupKeepAliveConfigured
csBgpNbrGroupKeepAliveConfigured.description: The configured keepalive to be used by the neighbors in this group. default value is -1 which indicates this is not configured and the neighbors in the group will be use a value of 60 seconds. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrKeepAliveConfigured attribute. be 180 seconds). KeepAlive timer is normally derived from the negotiated holdtime and is 1/3 the value of negotiated holdtime. However if keepalive is configured the minmum of this value and 1/3 the value of negotiated holdtime is used.

csBgpNbrGroupRemovePrivateAs.name: csBgpNbrGroupRemovePrivateAs
csBgpNbrGroupRemovePrivateAs.description: This attribute is used to strip private as numbers from the aspath advertised to the neighbor. This attribute is used only with EBGP neighbors. Configuring this attribute to an IBGP peer has no effect. default is -1 which indicates not configured and disabled. This attribute can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by setting the csBgpNbrNextHopSelf attribute.

csBgpNbrGroupLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpNbrGroupLogAreaFlag
csBgpNbrGroupLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within BGP Neighbor. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within BGP and their corresponding bits identifier. If the group level value is not set bgp global level value is inherited. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ packet (all packets) 0 open (open packets) 1 update (update packets) 2 keepalive (keepalive packets) 3 notify (notify packets) 4 system (all system operations) 5 end of description.

csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx.name: csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx
csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx.description: This attribute is used to set the maximum number of prefixes that can be learnt from each neighbor in this group. If a neighbor advertises more than this number set in this attribute, then that neighbor connection is closed and the state is set to Idle. Connection is not restored until user does a clearConnection. The group level value can be over-ridden for each nbr by setting the csBgpNbrMaxPfx attribute

csBgpNbrGroupVpnLogAreaFlag.name: csBgpNbrGroupVpnLogAreaFlag
csBgpNbrGroupVpnLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within BGP Neighbor related to VPN routing. If the group level value is not set bgp global level value is inherited. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ inbound-routes (updates recv) 0 outbound-routes (updates sent) 1 end of description.

csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxThreshold.name: csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxThreshold
csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxThreshold.description: If this attribute is configured, then when the number of routes learnt from the peers in this group reaches this threshold (percentage of csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx) then a warning message is generated.

csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxType.name: csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxType
csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfxType.description: This attribute indicates the action that needs to be taken when the number of routes learnt from the peers in this group reaches the max prefix limit configured via 'csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx' attribute. If this attribute is not set explicitly, and 'csBgpNbrGroupMaxPfx' attribute is set, this attribute defaults to shutdown.

csBgpNbrGroupImpPolTable.name: csBgpNbrGroupImpPolTable
csBgpNbrGroupImpPolTable.description: This table is used to configure the import policies applied to each BGP Group on each virtual router.

csBgpNbrGroupImpPolEntry.name: csBgpNbrGroupImpPolEntry
csBgpNbrGroupImpPolEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single policy applied to a single virtual router's BGP Group.

csBgpNbrGroupImpPolId.name: csBgpNbrGroupImpPolId
csBgpNbrGroupImpPolId.description: The identifier of the policy to apply to this group. This identifies an entry in either the csBgpImpImpPolTable or the csBgpExpImpPolTable. The import polices defined at the group level can be over-ridden for each Nbr in the group by accessing the csBgpNbrImpPolTable.

csBgpNbrGroupImpPolRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupImpPolRowStatus
csBgpNbrGroupImpPolRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csBgpNbrGroupExpPolTable.name: csBgpNbrGroupExpPolTable
csBgpNbrGroupExpPolTable.description: This table is used to configure the export policies applied to each BGP Group on each virtual router.

csBgpNbrGroupExpPolEntry.name: csBgpNbrGroupExpPolEntry
csBgpNbrGroupExpPolEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single policy applied to a single virtual router's BGP Group.

csBgpNbrGroupExpPolId.name: csBgpNbrGroupExpPolId
csBgpNbrGroupExpPolId.description: The identifier of the policy to apply to this group. This identifies an entry in either the csBgpExpExpPolTable or the csBgpExpExpPolTable. If the export policies are defined at the group level, all the neighbors in the group will inherit these export policies, even if export policies are defined at the Nbr level.

csBgpNbrGroupExpPolRowStatus.name: csBgpNbrGroupExpPolRowStatus
csBgpNbrGroupExpPolRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add & remove rows from this table.

csOrionBgpEnd.name: csOrionBgpEnd
csOrionBgpEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

OSINSAddress.name: OSINSAddress
OSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g. NSAP, Network Entity Title

SNPAAddress.name: SNPAAddress
SNPAAddress.description: A MAC Address or DTE Address or other SNPA Address.

NSAPPrefix.name: NSAPPrefix
NSAPPrefix.description: NSAP Prefix. The first octet of the string is used to encode as an unsigned integer the length in bits of the subsequent prefix. This length must be a multiple of 4 bits and may range from 0..160. The second and subsequent octets are used to hold the prefix value. If the last 4 bits of the last octet are not part of the prefix then their value is undefined.

SNPAPrefix.name: SNPAPrefix
SNPAPrefix.description: SNPA Prefix. The first octet of the string is used to encode as an unsigned integer the length in bits of the subsequent prefix. The second and subsequent octets are used to hold the prefix value. Bits in the last octet which are not part of the prefix have undefined value.

LSPBuffSize.name: LSPBuffSize
LSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub range for LSP size.

SupportedProtocol.name: SupportedProtocol
SupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated ISIS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

DefaultMetric.name: DefaultMetric
DefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop.

OtherMetric.name: OtherMetric
OtherMetric.description: Integer sub-range for metrics other than the default metric for single hop.

csIsisSysTable.name: csIsisSysTable
csIsisSysTable.description: The set of instances of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

csIsisSysEntry.name: csIsisSysEntry
csIsisSysEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a single instance of the protocol existing on the system.

csIsisSysInstance.name: csIsisSysInstance
csIsisSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisSysVersion.name: csIsisSysVersion
csIsisSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this instance conforms. This value must be set by the implementation when the row is valid.

csIsisSysType.name: csIsisSysType
csIsisSysType.description: The type of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisSysID.name: csIsisSysID
csIsisSysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the instance's area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles valid for this instance. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may assign values and not permit write MAX-ACCESS, others may require the value to be set manually.

csIsisSysMaxPathSplits.name: csIsisSysMaxPathSplits
csIsisSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: csIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt
csIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.This value should be always lesser than csIsisSysMaxLSPLifetime and greater than csIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt

csIsisSysMaxLSPLifetime.name: csIsisSysMaxLSPLifetime
csIsisSysMaxLSPLifetime.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, after which LSPs shall be aged out by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour. This value should always be greater than csIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt

csIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.name: csIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize
csIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 1 LSPs and SNPs originated by this instance. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.name: csIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses
csIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.description: The maximum number of area addresses to be permitted for the area in which this instance exists. Note that all Intermediate Systems in the same area must have the same value configured for this attribute if correct operation is to be assumed. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.name: csIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt
csIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L1 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.name: csIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt
csIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L2 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisSysPollESHelloRate.name: csIsisSysPollESHelloRate
csIsisSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

csIsisSysWaitTime.name: csIsisSysWaitTime
csIsisSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in waiting state before entering on state. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisSysOperState.name: csIsisSysOperState
csIsisSysOperState.description: The operational state of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. Setting this object to the value on when its current value is off enables operation of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

csIsisSysL1State.name: csIsisSysL1State
csIsisSysL1State.description: The state of the Level 1 database.

csIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.name: csIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads
csIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP L1 database has become overloaded.

csIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.name: csIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas
csIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

csIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: csIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
csIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

csIsisSysSeqNumSkips.name: csIsisSysSeqNumSkips
csIsisSysSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

csIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.name: csIsisSysOwnLSPPurges
csIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

csIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.name: csIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches
csIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

csIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: csIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches
csIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for MaximumAreaAddresses from that of the receiving system.

csIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.name: csIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize
csIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 2 LSPs and SNPs originated by this system. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisSysL2State.name: csIsisSysL2State
csIsisSysL2State.description: The state of the Level 2 database.

csIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.name: csIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads
csIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the Level 2 LSP database has become overloaded.

csIsisSysAuthAreaType.name: csIsisSysAuthAreaType
csIsisSysAuthAreaType.description: What authentication scheme, if any, is used to protect Level 1 Link State packets?

csIsisSysAuthAreaTransPwd.name: csIsisSysAuthAreaTransPwd
csIsisSysAuthAreaTransPwd.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key in Level 1 Link State Packets whenever the value of csIsisSysAuthAreaType has a value of plaintext. A modification of csIsisSysAuthAreaType does not modify the csIsisSysAuthAreaTransPwd value. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

csIsisSysAuthDomainType.name: csIsisSysAuthDomainType
csIsisSysAuthDomainType.description: What authentication scheme, if any, is used to protect Level 2 Link State packets?

csIsisSysAuthDomainTransPwd.name: csIsisSysAuthDomainTransPwd
csIsisSysAuthDomainTransPwd.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key in Level 2 Link State Packets whenever the value of csIsisSysAuthDomainType has a value of plaintext. A modification of csIsisSysAuthDomainType does not modify the csIsisSysAuthDomainTransPwd value. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

csIsisSysAuthFails.name: csIsisSysAuthFails
csIsisSysAuthFails.description: The number of authentication failures recognized by this instance of the protocol.

csIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.name: csIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors
csIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.description: If true, allow the router to ignore IS-IS link state packets (LSPs) that are received with internal checksum errors rather than purging the LSPs.

csIsisSysLogAdjacencyChanges.name: csIsisSysLogAdjacencyChanges
csIsisSysLogAdjacencyChanges.description: If true, causes IS-IS to generate a log message when an IS-IS adjacency changes state (up or down).

csIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.name: csIsisSysMaxAreaCheck
csIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.description: When on, enables checking of maximum area addresses per IS version of ISO10589.

csIsisSysNextCircIndex.name: csIsisSysNextCircIndex
csIsisSysNextCircIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to csIsisCircIndex as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads this object, and then writes the value back in a SET that creates a new instance of csIsisCircEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the ob- ject is incremented, and the new instance is created according to the manager's directions.

csIsisSysExistState.name: csIsisSysExistState
csIsisSysExistState.description: The state of the ISIS router. Turning this off forces the router to forget all current state

csIsisSysAdminStatus.name: csIsisSysAdminStatus
csIsisSysAdminStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable IS-IS routing on this Virtual Router.

csIsisSysSPFL1Int.name: csIsisSysSPFL1Int
csIsisSysSPFL1Int.description: This object is used for SPF Level 1 Interval, it is in seconds.

csIsisSysSPFL2Int.name: csIsisSysSPFL2Int
csIsisSysSPFL2Int.description: This object is used for SPF Level 2 Interval, it is in seconds.

csIsisSysSPFStartInt.name: csIsisSysSPFStartInt
csIsisSysSPFStartInt.description: The number in seconds system will wait to start SPF Interval calculation.

csIsisSysDefInfoOrig.name: csIsisSysDefInfoOrig
csIsisSysDefInfoOrig.description: When on, distributes the default route into the IS-IS routing domain.

csIsisSysL2TO1Leak.name: csIsisSysL2TO1Leak
csIsisSysL2TO1Leak.description: When on, enables Level-2 to Level-1 route leaking.

csIsisSysLogAreaFlag.name: csIsisSysLogAreaFlag
csIsisSysLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within ISIS. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within BGP and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ system 0 adj 1 lsp 2 snp 3 spf 4 packet recv 5 packet send 6 end of description.

csIsisSysLogLevelFlag.name: csIsisSysLogLevelFlag
csIsisSysLogLevelFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables logging at a specific level for ISIS. Below is a list of the different log levels available and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ------------------------------------------------------ critical 0 error 1 warning 2 information 3 detail 4 debug 5 end of description.

csIsisManAreaAddrTable.name: csIsisManAreaAddrTable
csIsisManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

csIsisManAreaAddrEntry.name: csIsisManAreaAddrEntry
csIsisManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system

csIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.name: csIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance
csIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisManAreaAddr.name: csIsisManAreaAddr
csIsisManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behaviour. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an Octet string is part of the OID.

csIsisManAreaAddrExistState.name: csIsisManAreaAddrExistState
csIsisManAreaAddrExistState.description: The state of the csIsisManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the Row Status behaviour. If an attempt is made to set this object to the value off when the corresponding csIsisManAreaAddrEntry is the only valid entry for this instance and when the corresponding ISIS instance has csIsisSysOperState set to On then the attempt is rejected.

csIsisAreaAddrTable.name: csIsisAreaAddrTable
csIsisAreaAddrTable.description: The union of the sets of area addresses reported in all Level 1 LSPs received by this instance of the protocol.

csIsisAreaAddrEntry.name: csIsisAreaAddrEntry
csIsisAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the protocol.

csIsisAreaAddrSysInstance.name: csIsisAreaAddrSysInstance
csIsisAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

csIsisAreaAddr.name: csIsisAreaAddr
csIsisAreaAddr.description: An area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the protocol.

csIsisSysProtSuppTable.name: csIsisSysProtSuppTable
csIsisSysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

csIsisSysProtSuppEntry.name: csIsisSysProtSuppEntry
csIsisSysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

csIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.name: csIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance
csIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.name: csIsisSysProtSuppProtocol
csIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisSysProtSuppExistState.name: csIsisSysProtSuppExistState
csIsisSysProtSuppExistState.description: The state of the csIsisSysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behavior.

csIsisL2SummAddrTable.name: csIsisL2SummAddrTable
csIsisL2SummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming the contents of Level 2 LSPs originated by this level 2 Intermediate System.

csIsisL2SummAddrEntry.name: csIsisL2SummAddrEntry
csIsisL2SummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address.

csIsisL2SummAddrSysInstance.name: csIsisL2SummAddrSysInstance
csIsisL2SummAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviours.

csIsisL2SummAddress.name: csIsisL2SummAddress
csIsisL2SummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisL2SummAddrMask.name: csIsisL2SummAddrMask
csIsisL2SummAddrMask.description: The mask value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisL2SummAddrExistState.name: csIsisL2SummAddrExistState
csIsisL2SummAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the row status behaviour.

csIsisL2SummAddrOperState.name: csIsisL2SummAddrOperState
csIsisL2SummAddrOperState.description: The operational state of this entry. This object follows the operationalState behaviour. When the operational state changes if this would cause the contents of Level 2 LSPs originated by the system to change then those new LSPs must be generated and sent as soon as is permitted by the ISIS protocol.

csIsisL2SummAddrDefaultMetric.name: csIsisL2SummAddrDefaultMetric
csIsisL2SummAddrDefaultMetric.description: The default metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system.

csIsisL2SummAddrDelayMetric.name: csIsisL2SummAddrDelayMetric
csIsisL2SummAddrDelayMetric.description: The delay metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisL2SummAddrExpenseMetric.name: csIsisL2SummAddrExpenseMetric
csIsisL2SummAddrExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisL2SummAddrErrorMetric.name: csIsisL2SummAddrErrorMetric
csIsisL2SummAddrErrorMetric.description: The error metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisExpPolTable.name: csIsisExpPolTable
csIsisExpPolTable.description: A set of Export Policies (see csExpPolTable) that are applied by ISIS.

csIsisExpPolEntry.name: csIsisExpPolEntry
csIsisExpPolEntry.description: Each entry represents a single export policy applied by the ISIS layer on a Virtual Router.

csIsisExpPolId.name: csIsisExpPolId
csIsisExpPolId.description: The Export Policy (see the corresponding entry in csExpPolTable) that is applied to this Virtual Router.

csIsisExpPolStatus.name: csIsisExpPolStatus
csIsisExpPolStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add and delete entries from this table.

csIsisExpPolTableEnd.name: csIsisExpPolTableEnd
csIsisExpPolTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csIsisCircTable.name: csIsisCircTable
csIsisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

csIsisCircEntry.name: csIsisCircEntry
csIsisCircEntry.description: An csIsisCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

csIsisCircSysInstance.name: csIsisCircSysInstance
csIsisCircSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

csIsisCircIndex.name: csIsisCircIndex
csIsisCircIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the instance of the protocol. This object follows the index behaviour. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

csIsisCircIfIndex.name: csIsisCircIfIndex
csIsisCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds. This object cannot be modified after creation

csIsisCircIfSubIndex.name: csIsisCircIfSubIndex
csIsisCircIfSubIndex.description: A specifier for the part of the interface ifIndex to which this circuit corresponds, such as a DLCI or VPI/VCI. This object cannot be modified after creation

csIsisCircLocalID.name: csIsisCircLocalID
csIsisCircLocalID.description: An identification that can be used in protocol packets to identify a circuit. Implementations may devise ways to assure that this value is suitable for the circuit it is used on. LAN packets only have space for 8 bits. Values of csIsisCircLocalID do not need to be unique. They are only required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

csIsisCircOperState.name: csIsisCircOperState
csIsisCircOperState.description: The operational state of the circuit. This object follows the operationalState behaviour.

csIsisCircExistState.name: csIsisCircExistState
csIsisCircExistState.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the Row Status behaviour.

csIsisCircType.name: csIsisCircType
csIsisCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of csIsisCircIfIndex.

csIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.name: csIsisCircL1DefaultMetric
csIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic.
