csIsisCircL1DelayMetric.name: csIsisCircL1DelayMetric
csIsisCircL1DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.name: csIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric
csIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.name: csIsisCircL1ErrorMetric
csIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircExtDomain.name: csIsisCircExtDomain
csIsisCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain ISIS PDUs on this circuit.

csIsisCircAdjChanges.name: csIsisCircAdjChanges
csIsisCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

csIsisCircInitFails.name: csIsisCircInitFails
csIsisCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed.

csIsisCircRejAdjs.name: csIsisCircRejAdjs
csIsisCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

csIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.name: csIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs
csIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs sent on this circuit.

csIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.name: csIsisCircInCtrlPDUs
csIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs received on this circuit.

csIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: csIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches
csIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

csIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.name: csIsisCircL2DefaultMetric
csIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic.

csIsisCircL2DelayMetric.name: csIsisCircL2DelayMetric
csIsisCircL2DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.name: csIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric
csIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.name: csIsisCircL2ErrorMetric
csIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

csIsisCircManL2Only.name: csIsisCircManL2Only
csIsisCircManL2Only.description: When true, indicates that this circuit is to be used only for level 2. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisCircL1ISPriority.name: csIsisCircL1ISPriority
csIsisCircL1ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Level 1 Deignated Intermediate System on a broadcast circuit.

csIsisCircL1CircID.name: csIsisCircL1CircID
csIsisCircL1CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of the value (because it is not participating in the Level 1 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

csIsisCircL1DesIS.name: csIsisCircL1DesIS
csIsisCircL1DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

csIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.name: csIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges
csIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

csIsisCircL2ISPriority.name: csIsisCircL2ISPriority
csIsisCircL2ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN level 2 Designated Intermediate System.

csIsisCircL2CircID.name: csIsisCircL2CircID
csIsisCircL2CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of this value (because it is not participating in the Level 2 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

csIsisCircL2DesIS.name: csIsisCircL2DesIS
csIsisCircL2DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

csIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.name: csIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges
csIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

csIsisCircMCAddr.name: csIsisCircMCAddr
csIsisCircMCAddr.description: Specifies which type of multicast address will be used for sending HELLO PDUs on this circuit.

csIsisCircPtToPtCircID.name: csIsisCircPtToPtCircID
csIsisCircPtToPtCircID.description: The ID of the circuit allocated during initialization. If no value has been negotiated (either because the adjacency is to an End System, or because initialization has not yet successfully completed), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

csIsisCircL1HelloTimer.name: csIsisCircL1HelloTimer
csIsisCircL1HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in milliseconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. It is also used as the period between Hellos on point to point circuits. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircL2HelloTimer.name: csIsisCircL2HelloTimer
csIsisCircL2HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in milliseconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.name: csIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier
csIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

csIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.name: csIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier
csIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

csIsisCircDRL1HelloTimer.name: csIsisCircDRL1HelloTimer
csIsisCircDRL1HelloTimer.description: Period, in milliseconds, between Level 1 PDUs on multiaccess networks when this IS is the Designated Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircDRL2HelloTimer.name: csIsisCircDRL2HelloTimer
csIsisCircDRL2HelloTimer.description: Period, in milliseconds, between Level 2 PDUs on multiaccess networks when this IS is the Designated Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircMinBroadLSPTransInt.name: csIsisCircMinBroadLSPTransInt
csIsisCircMinBroadLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in milliseconds, between transmission of LSPs on a broadcast circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour. This timer shall be capable of a resolution not coarser than 10 milliseconds.

csIsisCircL1MinLSPTransInt.name: csIsisCircL1MinLSPTransInt
csIsisCircL1MinLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an Level 1 LSP. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircL2MinLSPTransInt.name: csIsisCircL2MinLSPTransInt
csIsisCircL2MinLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an Level 2 LSP. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.name: csIsisCircL1CSNPInterval
csIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 1 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router.

csIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.name: csIsisCircL2CSNPInterval
csIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 2 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router.

csIsisCircL1PartSNPInterval.name: csIsisCircL1PartSNPInterval
csIsisCircL1PartSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval between sending Level 1 Partial Sequence Number PDUs. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircL2PartSNPInterval.name: csIsisCircL2PartSNPInterval
csIsisCircL2PartSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval between sending Level 2 Partial Sequence Number PDUs. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

csIsisCircLSPThrottle.name: csIsisCircLSPThrottle
csIsisCircLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between transmissions of LSPs on a point to point interface.

csIsisCircPassiveCircuit.name: csIsisCircPassiveCircuit
csIsisCircPassiveCircuit.description: Should we include this interface in LSPs, even if it is not running the ISIS Protocol?

csIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.name: csIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled
csIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

csIsisCircMeshGroup.name: csIsisCircMeshGroup
csIsisCircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If csIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled is false, this value is ignored.

csIsisCircL1AuthType.name: csIsisCircL1AuthType
csIsisCircL1AuthType.description: What authentication scheme, if any, is used to protect Level 1 and Point-to-Point hello packets?

csIsisCircL1Password.name: csIsisCircL1Password
csIsisCircL1Password.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key in Level 1 and Point-to-Point hello packets whenever the corresponding instance of csIsisCircL1AuthType has a value of plaintext. A modification of the corresponding instance of csIsisCircL1AuthType does not modify the csIsisCircL1Password value. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

csIsisCircL2AuthType.name: csIsisCircL2AuthType
csIsisCircL2AuthType.description: What authentication scheme, if any, is used to protect Level 2 hello packets?

csIsisCircL2Password.name: csIsisCircL2Password
csIsisCircL2Password.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key in Level 1 Hello packets whenever the corresponding instance of csIsisCircL1AuthType has a value of plaintext. A modification of the corresponding instance of csIsisCircL1AuthType does not modify the csIsisCircL1Password value. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

csIsisCircSmallHellos.name: csIsisCircSmallHellos
csIsisCircSmallHellos.description: Can we send unpadded hellos on LAN circuits? Off means LAN Hellos must be padded.

csIsisManAdjNeighNSAP.name: csIsisManAdjNeighNSAP
csIsisManAdjNeighNSAP.description: The address of the neighbour if this is a manual adjacency. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisManAdjNeighSNPA.name: csIsisManAdjNeighSNPA
csIsisManAdjNeighSNPA.description: The SNPA of the neighbour if this is a manual adjacency. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

csIsisCircIPEncaps.name: csIsisCircIPEncaps
csIsisCircIPEncaps.description: Should we encapsulate IS-IS in IP packets?

csIsisCircUpTime.name: csIsisCircUpTime
csIsisCircUpTime.description: The amount of time in seconds since this circuit entered state 'up'. Note: This can be implemented as start time less the current time.

csIsisCircIpAddress.name: csIsisCircIpAddress
csIsisCircIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the VI that IS-IS is enabled on.

csIsisCircLevel.name: csIsisCircLevel
csIsisCircLevel.description: This is the IS-IS circuit level. Level-1 only => isisCircLevel = 1, Level-2 only => isisCircLevel = 2, Level-1 or 2 => isisCircLevel = 3.

csIsisCircTableEnd.name: csIsisCircTableEnd
csIsisCircTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csIsisISAdjTable.name: csIsisISAdjTable
csIsisISAdjTable.description: The table of adjacencies to Intermediate Systems.

csIsisISAdjEntry.name: csIsisISAdjEntry
csIsisISAdjEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one adjacency to an Intermediate System on this system.

csIsisISAdjSysInstance.name: csIsisISAdjSysInstance
csIsisISAdjSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

csIsisISAdjCircIndex.name: csIsisISAdjCircIndex
csIsisISAdjCircIndex.description: The Circuit Index of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency.

csIsisISAdjIndex.name: csIsisISAdjIndex
csIsisISAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is assigned by the system when the adjacency is created automatically.

csIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: csIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress
csIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system.

csIsisISAdjNeighSysType.name: csIsisISAdjNeighSysType
csIsisISAdjNeighSysType.description: The type of the neighboring system.

csIsisISAdjNeighSysID.name: csIsisISAdjNeighSysID
csIsisISAdjNeighSysID.description: The system ID and circuit ID of the neighboring Intermediate System set from the source ID field of the neighbor's IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjUsage.name: csIsisISAdjUsage
csIsisISAdjUsage.description: An adjacency of type level1 is used for level 1 traffic only. An adjacency of type level2 is used for level 2 traffic only. An adjacency of type level1and2 is used for both level 1 and level 2 traffic. There may be two adjacencies (of types level1 and level2) between the same pair of Intermediate Systems.

csIsisISAdjHoldTimer.name: csIsisISAdjHoldTimer
csIsisISAdjHoldTimer.description: The holding time for this adjacency updated from received IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjNeighPriority.name: csIsisISAdjNeighPriority
csIsisISAdjNeighPriority.description: Priority of the neighboring Intermediate System for becoming the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System if the value of csIsisISAdjNeighSysType is L1IntermediateSystem or LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System if the value of csIsisISAdjNeighSysType is L2IntermediateSystem.

csIsisISAdjUpTime.name: csIsisISAdjUpTime
csIsisISAdjUpTime.description: The amount of time in seconds since this adjacency entered state 'up'. Note: This can be implemented as start time less the current time.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable
csIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of Area Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry
csIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one Area Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance
csIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex
csIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this Area Address entry corresponds.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex
csIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex.description: The identifier of the IS adjacency to which this entry belongs.

csIsisISAdjAreaAddress.name: csIsisISAdjAreaAddress
csIsisISAdjAreaAddress.description: One Area Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

csIsisISAdjIPAddrTable.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddrTable
csIsisISAdjIPAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of IP Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry
csIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance
csIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

csIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex
csIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this IP Address entry corresponds.

csIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex
csIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex.description: The identifier of the IS adjacency to which this entry belongs.

csIsisISAdjIPAddress.name: csIsisISAdjIPAddress
csIsisISAdjIPAddress.description: One IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppTable.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppTable
csIsisISAdjProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the set of protocols supported by neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry
csIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by a neighboring Intermediate System as reported in its IIH PDUs.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance
csIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex
csIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this supported protocol entry corresponds.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex
csIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex.description: The identifier the IS adjacency to which this entry corresponds.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol
csIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

csIsisISAdjProtSuppTableEnd.name: csIsisISAdjProtSuppTableEnd
csIsisISAdjProtSuppTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csIsisIPRATable.name: csIsisIPRATable
csIsisIPRATable.description: The table of IP Reachable Addresses to networks, subnetworks or hosts either manually configured or learned from another protocol.

csIsisIPRAEntry.name: csIsisIPRAEntry
csIsisIPRAEntry.description: Each entry defines an IP Reachable Address to a network, subnetwork or host.

csIsisIPRASysInstance.name: csIsisIPRASysInstance
csIsisIPRASysInstance.description: The identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

csIsisIPRACircIndex.name: csIsisIPRACircIndex
csIsisIPRACircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit over which this IP destination is reachable. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

csIsisIPRAIndex.name: csIsisIPRAIndex
csIsisIPRAIndex.description: The identifier for this csIsisIPRAEntry. This value must be unique amongst all IP Reachable Addresses on the same parent Circuit. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

csIsisIPRAType.name: csIsisIPRAType
csIsisIPRAType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol.

csIsisIPRADest.name: csIsisIPRADest
csIsisIPRADest.description: The destination of this IP Reachable Address. This is either a network address, subnetwork address or host address. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAMask.name: csIsisIPRAMask
csIsisIPRAMask.description: The network mask for the IP Address in the csIsisIPRADest object. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAExistState.name: csIsisIPRAExistState
csIsisIPRAExistState.description: The state of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ExistenceState and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

csIsisIPRAOperState.name: csIsisIPRAOperState
csIsisIPRAOperState.description: The operational state of the IP Reachable Address. This object follows the operationalState and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

csIsisIPRADefMetric.name: csIsisIPRADefMetric
csIsisIPRADefMetric.description: The default metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRADelMetric.name: csIsisIPRADelMetric
csIsisIPRADelMetric.description: The delay metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. The value zero is reserved to mean the metric is not supported. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAExpMetric.name: csIsisIPRAExpMetric
csIsisIPRAExpMetric.description: The expense metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. The value zero is reserved to mean the metric is not supported. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAErrMetric.name: csIsisIPRAErrMetric
csIsisIPRAErrMetric.description: The error metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. The value zero is reserved to mean the metric is not supported. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRADefMetricType.name: csIsisIPRADefMetricType
csIsisIPRADefMetricType.description: Indicates whether the default metric is internal or external. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRADelMetricType.name: csIsisIPRADelMetricType
csIsisIPRADelMetricType.description: Indicates whether the delay metric is internal or external. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAExpMetricType.name: csIsisIPRAExpMetricType
csIsisIPRAExpMetricType.description: Indicates whether the expense metric is internal or external. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRAErrMetricType.name: csIsisIPRAErrMetricType
csIsisIPRAErrMetricType.description: Indicates whether the error metric is internal or external. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csIsisIPRASNPAAddress.name: csIsisIPRASNPAAddress
csIsisIPRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

csOrionIsisEnd.name: csOrionIsisEnd
csOrionIsisEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csRsvpSessionTable.name: csRsvpSessionTable
csRsvpSessionTable.description: This table has one row for each session being managed by LSR. It provides the statistics pertaining to the session.

csRsvpSessionEntry.name: csRsvpSessionEntry
csRsvpSessionEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by LSR for every established session. This entry is indexed by Session destination IP address Tunnel Identifier and Extended Tunnel Identifier.

csRsvpSessionTunnelEndpoint.name: csRsvpSessionTunnelEndpoint
csRsvpSessionTunnelEndpoint.description: One of the indices for the row of the table. Specifies the IP address (IPv4 only supported) of the destination of the Session.

csRsvpSessionTunnelID.name: csRsvpSessionTunnelID
csRsvpSessionTunnelID.description: One of the indices for the row of the table. Specifies the Tunnel identifier of the Session.

csRsvpSessionExtendedTunnelID.name: csRsvpSessionExtendedTunnelID
csRsvpSessionExtendedTunnelID.description: One of the indices for the row of the table. Specifies the Extended Tunnel identifier of the Session.

csRsvpSessionUpPsbs.name: csRsvpSessionUpPsbs
csRsvpSessionUpPsbs.description: This object specifies the number of upside senders (Up PSBs) for this session known to this processor of this LSR.

csRsvpSessionDownPsbs.name: csRsvpSessionDownPsbs
csRsvpSessionDownPsbs.description: This object specifies the number of downside senders (Down PSBs) for this session known to this processor of this LSR.

csRsvpSessionUpRsbs.name: csRsvpSessionUpRsbs
csRsvpSessionUpRsbs.description: This object specifies the number of upside receivers (Up RSBs) for this session known to this processor of this LSR.

csRsvpSessionDownRsbs.name: csRsvpSessionDownRsbs
csRsvpSessionDownRsbs.description: This object specifies the number of downside receivers (Down RSBs) for this session known to this processor of this LSR.

csRsvpIfTable.name: csRsvpIfTable
csRsvpIfTable.description: This table has one row each for every interface of this LSR running TE-RSVP. Corresponding row in csRsvpNbrTable must be configured before a row in this table can be activated.

csRsvpIfEntry.name: csRsvpIfEntry
csRsvpIfEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every interface running TE-RSVP.

csRsvpIfUdpNbrs.name: csRsvpIfUdpNbrs
csRsvpIfUdpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP UDP Encapsulation.

csRsvpIfIpNbrs.name: csRsvpIfIpNbrs
csRsvpIfIpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP IP Encapsulation.

csRsvpIfNbrs.name: csRsvpIfNbrs
csRsvpIfNbrs.description: The number of neighbors currently perceived; this will exceed rsvpIfIpNbrs + rsvpIfUdpNbrs by the number of neighbors using both encapsulations.

csRsvpIfEnabled.name: csRsvpIfEnabled
csRsvpIfEnabled.description: If TRUE, RSVP is enabled on this Interface. If FALSE, RSVP is not enabled on this interface.

csRsvpIfUdpRequired.name: csRsvpIfUdpRequired
csRsvpIfUdpRequired.description: If TRUE, manual configuration forces the use of UDP encapsulation on the interface. If FALSE, UDP encapsulation is only used if rsvpIfUdpNbrs is not zero.

csRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.name: csRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple
csRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'Kb', Which is the minimum number of refresh intervals that blockade state will last once entered.

csRsvpIfRefreshMultiple.name: csRsvpIfRefreshMultiple
csRsvpIfRefreshMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'K', which is the number of refresh intervals which must elapse (minimum) before a PATH or RESV message which is not being refreshed will be aged out.

csRsvpIfTTL.name: csRsvpIfTTL
csRsvpIfTTL.description: The value of SEND_TTL used on this interface for messages this node originates. If set to zero, the node determines the TTL via other means.

csRsvpIfRefreshInterval.name: csRsvpIfRefreshInterval
csRsvpIfRefreshInterval.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface.

csRsvpIfRouteDelay.name: csRsvpIfRouteDelay
csRsvpIfRouteDelay.description: The approximate period from the time a route is changed to the time a resulting message appears on the interface.

csRsvpIfStatus.name: csRsvpIfStatus
csRsvpIfStatus.description: 'active' on interfaces that are configured for RSVP. Corresponding row in csRsvpNbrTable must be configured and activated before the row in this table can be activated.

csRsvpIfPktsIn.name: csRsvpIfPktsIn
csRsvpIfPktsIn.description: Number of RSVP Packets received in this interface.

csRsvpIfPathIn.name: csRsvpIfPathIn
csRsvpIfPathIn.description: Number of PATH messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfResvIn.name: csRsvpIfResvIn
csRsvpIfResvIn.description: Number of RESV messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfPathTearIn.name: csRsvpIfPathTearIn
csRsvpIfPathTearIn.description: Number of Path Tear messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfPathErrIn.name: csRsvpIfPathErrIn
csRsvpIfPathErrIn.description: Number of Path Error messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfResvTearIn.name: csRsvpIfResvTearIn
csRsvpIfResvTearIn.description: Number of Resv Tear messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfResvErrIn.name: csRsvpIfResvErrIn
csRsvpIfResvErrIn.description: Number of RESV Error messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfResvConfIn.name: csRsvpIfResvConfIn
csRsvpIfResvConfIn.description: Number of RESV COnfirmation messages received on this interface.

csRsvpIfPathOut.name: csRsvpIfPathOut
csRsvpIfPathOut.description: Number of Path messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfResvOut.name: csRsvpIfResvOut
csRsvpIfResvOut.description: Number of Resv messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfPathTearOut.name: csRsvpIfPathTearOut
csRsvpIfPathTearOut.description: Number of Path Tear messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfPathErrOut.name: csRsvpIfPathErrOut
csRsvpIfPathErrOut.description: Number of Path Error messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfResvTearOut.name: csRsvpIfResvTearOut
csRsvpIfResvTearOut.description: Number of Resv Tear messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfResvErrOut.name: csRsvpIfResvErrOut
csRsvpIfResvErrOut.description: Number of Resv Error messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfResvConfOut.name: csRsvpIfResvConfOut
csRsvpIfResvConfOut.description: Number of Resv Confirm messages sent out over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadPathIn.name: csRsvpIfBadPathIn
csRsvpIfBadPathIn.description: Number of bad Path messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadResvIn.name: csRsvpIfBadResvIn
csRsvpIfBadResvIn.description: Number of bad Resv messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadPathTearIn.name: csRsvpIfBadPathTearIn
csRsvpIfBadPathTearIn.description: Number of bad Path Tear messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadPathErrIn.name: csRsvpIfBadPathErrIn
csRsvpIfBadPathErrIn.description: Number of bad Path Error messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadResvTearIn.name: csRsvpIfBadResvTearIn
csRsvpIfBadResvTearIn.description: Number of bad Resv Tear messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadResvErrIn.name: csRsvpIfBadResvErrIn
csRsvpIfBadResvErrIn.description: Number of bad Resv Error messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadResvConfIn.name: csRsvpIfBadResvConfIn
csRsvpIfBadResvConfIn.description: Number of bad Resv Confirm messages received over this interface.

csRsvpIfBadOtherIn.name: csRsvpIfBadOtherIn
csRsvpIfBadOtherIn.description: Number of messages received over this interface which were not valid RSVP messages.

csRsvpIfUpPsbsCreated.name: csRsvpIfUpPsbsCreated
csRsvpIfUpPsbsCreated.description: Number of Upside PSBs created so far on this interface.

csRsvpIfDownPsbsCreated.name: csRsvpIfDownPsbsCreated
csRsvpIfDownPsbsCreated.description: Number of Downside PSBs created so far on this interface.

csRsvpIfUpRsbsCreated.name: csRsvpIfUpRsbsCreated
csRsvpIfUpRsbsCreated.description: Number of Upside RSBs created so far on this interface.

csRsvpIfDownRsbsCreated.name: csRsvpIfDownRsbsCreated
csRsvpIfDownRsbsCreated.description: Number of Downside RSBs created so far on this interface.

csRsvpIfIngressLspsCreated.name: csRsvpIfIngressLspsCreated
csRsvpIfIngressLspsCreated.description: Number of LSPs created on this node which were originated from this interface of this node.

csRsvpIfEgressLspsCreated.name: csRsvpIfEgressLspsCreated
csRsvpIfEgressLspsCreated.description: Number of LSPs created on this node which were terminated on this interface of this node.

csRsvpIfIpAddress.name: csRsvpIfIpAddress
csRsvpIfIpAddress.description: The IP Address of this RSVP interface.

csRsvpIfRRCapable.name: csRsvpIfRRCapable
csRsvpIfRRCapable.description: Indicates the administrator's intent to switch on/off RSVP aggregation on the interface. Aggregation includes RSVP Refresh Reduction related messages.

csRsvpIfAckDesired.name: csRsvpIfAckDesired
csRsvpIfAckDesired.description: Indicates the administrator's intent as to whether acknowledgement is desired for the aggregation messages on this interface. If the administrator switches this variable on, then RSVP aggregation (csRsvpIfRRCapable) is switched ON automatically.

csRsvpIfHelloInterval.name: csRsvpIfHelloInterval
csRsvpIfHelloInterval.description: Configures the interval in seconds between Rsvp Hello messages exchanged between neighbors, on this interface.

csRsvpVrConfTable.name: csRsvpVrConfTable
csRsvpVrConfTable.description: This table is used to provide RSVP related functionality at the router level

csRsvpVrConfEntry.name: csRsvpVrConfEntry
csRsvpVrConfEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VR ID

csRsvpVrAdminStatus.name: csRsvpVrAdminStatus
csRsvpVrAdminStatus.description: Indicates the administrator's intent as to whether RSVP should be enabled or disabled on this router.

csRsvpVrEventLogLevel.name: csRsvpVrEventLogLevel
csRsvpVrEventLogLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of details for event logs for RSVP

csRsvpVrEventLogArea.name: csRsvpVrEventLogArea
csRsvpVrEventLogArea.description: This object is used to set the area of event logs for RSVP

csRsvpVrConfRowStatus.name: csRsvpVrConfRowStatus
csRsvpVrConfRowStatus.description: A row status type for the Rsvp Table

csRsvpVrConfTableEnd.name: csRsvpVrConfTableEnd
csRsvpVrConfTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csRsvpIfQueueTable.name: csRsvpIfQueueTable
csRsvpIfQueueTable.description: This table is used to allocate MPLS bandwidth for different hardware queues on a physical VI.

csRsvpIfQueueEntry.name: csRsvpIfQueueEntry
csRsvpIfQueueEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for every hardware queue on a physical VI to reserve bandwidth for MPLS.

csRsvpIfQueueID.name: csRsvpIfQueueID
csRsvpIfQueueID.description: The possible queue on a physical VI

csRsvpIfQueueBandwidth.name: csRsvpIfQueueBandwidth
csRsvpIfQueueBandwidth.description: The maximum reservable bandwidth for MPLS.

csRsvpIfQueueRowStatus.name: csRsvpIfQueueRowStatus
csRsvpIfQueueRowStatus.description: A row status type for this table

csRsvpIfQueueTableEnd.name: csRsvpIfQueueTableEnd
csRsvpIfQueueTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csMplsLspTable.name: csMplsLspTable
csMplsLspTable.description: List of Configured Label Switched Paths.

csMplsLspEntry.name: csMplsLspEntry
csMplsLspEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular Label Switched Path.

csMplsLspID.name: csMplsLspID
csMplsLspID.description: This object identifies a Label Switched Path.

csMplsLspName.name: csMplsLspName
csMplsLspName.description: Name of the Label Switched Path.

csMplsLspState.name: csMplsLspState
csMplsLspState.description: The operational state of the LSP.

csMplsLspOctets.name: csMplsLspOctets
csMplsLspOctets.description: The number of octets that have been forwarded over current LSP active path. The number reported is not realtime, may subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by mpls statistics gathering interval, which by default is once every 5 minutes. If mpls statistics gathering is not enabled, this number will not increment.

csMplsLspPackets.name: csMplsLspPackets
csMplsLspPackets.description: The number of packets that have been forwarded over current LSP active path. The number reported is not realtime, may subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by mpls statistics gathering interval, which by default is once every 5 minutes. If mpls statistics gathering is not enabled, this number will not increment.

csMplsLspAge.name: csMplsLspAge
csMplsLspAge.description: The age (i.e., time from creation till now) of this LSP in 10-millisecond periods.

csMplsLspTimeUp.name: csMplsLspTimeUp
csMplsLspTimeUp.description: The total time in 10-millisecond units that this LSP has been operational. For example, the percentage up time can be determined by computing (mplsLspTimeUp/mplsLspAge * 100 %).

csMplsLspPrimaryTimeUp.name: csMplsLspPrimaryTimeUp
csMplsLspPrimaryTimeUp.description: The total time in 10-millisecond units that this LSP's primary path has been operational. For example, the percentage contribution of the primary path to the operational time is given by (mplsLspPrimaryTimeUp/mplsLspTimeUp * 100) %.

csMplsLspTransitions.name: csMplsLspTransitions
csMplsLspTransitions.description: The number of state transitions (up -> down and down -> up) this LSP has undergone.

csMplsLspLastTransition.name: csMplsLspLastTransition
csMplsLspLastTransition.description: The time in 10-millisecond units since the last transition occurred on this LSP.

csMplsLspPathChanges.name: csMplsLspPathChanges
csMplsLspPathChanges.description: The number of path changes this LSP has had. For every path change (path down, path up, path change), a corresponding syslog/trap (if enabled) is generated for it.

csMplsLspLastPathChange.name: csMplsLspLastPathChange
csMplsLspLastPathChange.description: The time in 10-millisecond units since the last change occurred on this LSP.

csMplsLspConfiguredPaths.name: csMplsLspConfiguredPaths
csMplsLspConfiguredPaths.description: The number of paths configured for this LSP.

csMplsLspStandbyPaths.name: csMplsLspStandbyPaths
csMplsLspStandbyPaths.description: The number of standby paths configured for this LSP.

csMplsLspOperationalPaths.name: csMplsLspOperationalPaths
csMplsLspOperationalPaths.description: The number of operational paths for this LSP. This includes the path currently active, as well as operational standby paths.

csMplsLspFrom.name: csMplsLspFrom
csMplsLspFrom.description: Source IP address of this LSP.

csMplsLspTo.name: csMplsLspTo
csMplsLspTo.description: Destination IP address of this LSP.

csMplsPathName.name: csMplsPathName
csMplsPathName.description: The name of the active path for this LSP, if any. If there is none, the name should be empty.

csMplsPathType.name: csMplsPathType
csMplsPathType.description: The type of path that is active, i.e., a primary path, a standby path, or a generic secondary path. This field is meaningless if csMplsPathName or csMplsPathIdentifier is not supplied

csMplsPathBandwidth.name: csMplsPathBandwidth
csMplsPathBandwidth.description: The configured bandwidth for this LSP, in units of thousands of bits per second (Kbps).

csMplsPathCOS.name: csMplsPathCOS
csMplsPathCOS.description: The configured Class Of Service on this path. If the value is between 0 and 7 inclusive, this value will be inserted in the 3 bit COS field in the label. If the value is 255, the value in the COS field of the label will depend on other factors. This field is meaningless if csMplsPathName or csMplsPathIdentifier is not supplied

csMplsPathInclude.name: csMplsPathInclude
csMplsPathInclude.description: This is a configured set of colors (administrative groups) specified as a bit vector (i.e., bit n is 1 if color n is in the set, where n = 0 is the LSB). For each link that this path goes through, the link MUST have colors associated with it, and the intersection of the link's colors and the 'include' set MUST be non-null. This field is meaningless if csMplsPathName or csMplsPathIdentifier is not supplied

csMplsPathExclude.name: csMplsPathExclude
csMplsPathExclude.description: This is a configured set of colors (administrative groups) specified as a bit vector (i.e., bit n is 1 if color n is in the set, where n = 0 is the LSB). For each link that this path goes through, the link MUST have colors associated with it, and the intersection of the link's colors and the 'exclude' set MUST be null.This field is meaningless if csMplsPathName or csMplsPathIdentifier is not supplied

csMplsPathSetupPriority.name: csMplsPathSetupPriority
csMplsPathSetupPriority.description: The setup priority configured for this path.

csMplsPathHoldPriority.name: csMplsPathHoldPriority
csMplsPathHoldPriority.description: The hold priority configured for this path.

csMplsPathRecordRoute.name: csMplsPathRecordRoute
csMplsPathRecordRoute.description: This is used to set record route

csMplsPathDynamic.name: csMplsPathDynamic
csMplsPathDynamic.description: This is used to configure a dynamic path

csMplsPathBgpAutoRouteAnnounce.name: csMplsPathBgpAutoRouteAnnounce
csMplsPathBgpAutoRouteAnnounce.description: Used to specify that the IGP should use the tunnel (if the tunnel is up) in its enhanced shortest path first (SPF) calculation.

csMplsPathMetricMode.name: csMplsPathMetricMode
csMplsPathMetricMode.description: Used to specify the MPLS traffic engineering tunnel metric type that the IGP enhanced SPF calculation uses. MetricMode can be absolute or relative

csMplsPathMetricValue.name: csMplsPathMetricValue
csMplsPathMetricValue.description: Absolute metric mode the user can enter a positive value and for relative metric mode the user can enter a positive negative or zero value

csMplsPathAffinity.name: csMplsPathAffinity
csMplsPathAffinity.description: Used to configure an affinity for an MPLS traffic engineering tunnel

csMplsPathAffinityMask.name: csMplsPathAffinityMask
csMplsPathAffinityMask.description: Used to configure affinity mask value for an MPLS traffic engineering tunnel

csMplsLspPreference.name: csMplsLspPreference
csMplsLspPreference.description: Used to set the Lsp Preference Value

csMplsLspRowStatus.name: csMplsLspRowStatus
csMplsLspRowStatus.description: A row status type for the Lsp Table

csMplsPathIsisAutoRouteAnnounce.name: csMplsPathIsisAutoRouteAnnounce
csMplsPathIsisAutoRouteAnnounce.description: Used to specify that the IGP should use the tunnel (if the tunnel is up) in its enhanced shortest path first (SPF) calculation.Used by Isis.

csMplsPathOspfAutoRouteAnnounce.name: csMplsPathOspfAutoRouteAnnounce
csMplsPathOspfAutoRouteAnnounce.description: Used to specify that the IGP should use the tunnel (if the tunnel is up) in its enhanced shortest path first (SPF) calculation. Used by Ospf.

csMplsVrPathRecordRoute.name: csMplsVrPathRecordRoute
csMplsVrPathRecordRoute.description: This entry records the path recorded by Rsvp for the tunnel. This field is a displayable string in the format of XXX.XXX.XXX.XXX repeated for each explicit address.

csMplsLspOperationStatus.name: csMplsLspOperationStatus
csMplsLspOperationStatus.description: This object contains the operational status for the LSP

csMplsPathExpValue.name: csMplsPathExpValue
csMplsPathExpValue.description: Exp Value to use for this path

csMplsPathHotStandby.name: csMplsPathHotStandby
csMplsPathHotStandby.description: Mark this path as Hot Standby

csMplsPathVpnAutoRouteAnnounce.name: csMplsPathVpnAutoRouteAnnounce
csMplsPathVpnAutoRouteAnnounce.description: Used to specify that the IGP should use the tunnel (if the tunnel is up) in its enhanced shortest path first (SPF) calculation

csMplsPathPwe3AutoRouteAnnounce.name: csMplsPathPwe3AutoRouteAnnounce
csMplsPathPwe3AutoRouteAnnounce.description: Used to specify that the IGP should use the tunnel (if the tunnel is up) in its enhanced shortest path first (SPF) calculation

csMplsInterfaceConfTable.name: csMplsInterfaceConfTable
csMplsInterfaceConfTable.description: This table has one entry for every interface running Mpls

csMplsInterfaceConfEntry.name: csMplsInterfaceConfEntry
csMplsInterfaceConfEntry.description: An entry in this table is created for interface specific Label space configuration information.

csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels.name: csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels
csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels.description: If TRUE indicates that this interface is configured to use interface specific label space. If FALSE then this interface is configured to use Platform specific label space.

csMplsInterfaceLabelRange.name: csMplsInterfaceLabelRange
csMplsInterfaceLabelRange.description: This object specifies the type of Labels that are being use for interface specific label space configuration information. Value of this object is significant only if csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is set to TRUE. (If csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is FALSE then this interface is configured to use Platform specific label space.)

csMplsInterfaceLabelMinIn.name: csMplsInterfaceLabelMinIn
csMplsInterfaceLabelMinIn.description: This object specifies the lower limit of the label range to be used in incoming packets over this interface. This object specifies configuration information for interface specific label space and is significant only if value of csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is set to TRUE.

csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxIn.name: csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxIn
csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxIn.description: This object specifies the upper limit of the label range to be used in incoming packets over this interface. This object specifies configuration information for interface specific label space and is significant only if value of csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is set to TRUE.

csMplsInterfaceLabelMinOut.name: csMplsInterfaceLabelMinOut
csMplsInterfaceLabelMinOut.description: This object specifies the lower limit of the label range to be used in outgoing packets over this interface. This object specifies configuration information for interface specific label space and is significant only if value of csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is set to TRUE.

csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxOut.name: csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxOut
csMplsInterfaceLabelMaxOut.description: This object specifies the upper limit of the label range to be used in outgoing packets over this interface. This object specifies configuration information for interface specific label space and is significant only if value of csMplsInterfaceUseInterfaceLabels is set to TRUE.

csMplsInterfaceAdminStatus.name: csMplsInterfaceAdminStatus
csMplsInterfaceAdminStatus.description: Indicates the administrator's intent as to whether MPLS should be enabled or disabled on this interface.

csMplsInterfaceOperStatus.name: csMplsInterfaceOperStatus
csMplsInterfaceOperStatus.description: This object specifies the operational state of MPLS on this interface.

csMplsInterfaceAdminWeight.name: csMplsInterfaceAdminWeight
csMplsInterfaceAdminWeight.description: Used to override the Interior Gateway Protocol (IGP) administrative weight (cost) of the link

csMplsInterfaceAttribFlags.name: csMplsInterfaceAttribFlags
csMplsInterfaceAttribFlags.description: Used to set the user-specified attribute flags for the interface

csMplsInterfaceRowStatus.name: csMplsInterfaceRowStatus
csMplsInterfaceRowStatus.description: A row status type for the MplsInterface table

csMplsVrConfTable.name: csMplsVrConfTable
csMplsVrConfTable.description: This table is used to Configure Mpls on a Virtual Router.

csMplsVrConfEntry.name: csMplsVrConfEntry
csMplsVrConfEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VR ID

csMplsVrAdminStatus.name: csMplsVrAdminStatus
csMplsVrAdminStatus.description: Indicates the administrator's intent as to whether MPLS should be enabled or disabled on this router.

csMplsVrEventLogLevel.name: csMplsVrEventLogLevel
csMplsVrEventLogLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of details for event logs for MPLS

csMplsVrEventLogArea.name: csMplsVrEventLogArea
csMplsVrEventLogArea.description: This object is used to set the area of event logs for MPLS

csMplsVrConfOpCode.name: csMplsVrConfOpCode
csMplsVrConfOpCode.description: Used for Mpls Trace Commands only

csMplsVrConfRowStatus.name: csMplsVrConfRowStatus
csMplsVrConfRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour

csMplsExtensionsTable.name: csMplsExtensionsTable
csMplsExtensionsTable.description: This table is used to support Mpls Extensions

csMplsExtensionsEntry.name: csMplsExtensionsEntry
csMplsExtensionsEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VrID

csMplsMetricStyle.name: csMplsMetricStyle
csMplsMetricStyle.description: This entry is used to define the metric-style. wide => csMplsMetricStyle = 1, narrow => csMplsMetricStyle = 2, transition => csMplsMetricStyle = 3

csMplsExtensionsRowStatus.name: csMplsExtensionsRowStatus
csMplsExtensionsRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour.

csMplsOspfOpaqueAdminStatus.name: csMplsOspfOpaqueAdminStatus
csMplsOspfOpaqueAdminStatus.description: This entry is used to indicate if Ospf Opaque is enabled or disabled on a router.

csMplsVrPathConfTable.name: csMplsVrPathConfTable
csMplsVrPathConfTable.description: This table is used to configure Explicitly Routed Path

csMplsVrPathConfEntry.name: csMplsVrPathConfEntry
csMplsVrPathConfEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VR ID

csMplsVrPathExplicitRoute.name: csMplsVrPathExplicitRoute
csMplsVrPathExplicitRoute.description: The explicit route used to set up this LSP. This may either be the route configured by the user, or a route automatically computed to satisfy constraints set by the user. This field is a displayable string in the format of XXX.XXX.XXX.XXX S/L repeated for each explicit address. The S/L character stands for Strict/Loose route. This field is meaningless if csMplsVrPathIdentifier or csMplsVrPathName is not supplied

csMplsVrPathConfRowStatus.name: csMplsVrPathConfRowStatus
csMplsVrPathConfRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour

csMplsIsisExtensionsTable.name: csMplsIsisExtensionsTable
csMplsIsisExtensionsTable.description: This table is used to support ISIS extensions to MPLS

csMplsIsisExtensionsEntry.name: csMplsIsisExtensionsEntry
csMplsIsisExtensionsEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VrID

csMplsTrafficEnggLevel.name: csMplsTrafficEnggLevel
csMplsTrafficEnggLevel.description: This entry is used to define the level on which MPLS traffic-eng will be used. Level-1 only => csMplsExtLevel = 1, Level-2 only => csMplsExtLevel = 2

csMplsTrafficEnggAdminStatus.name: csMplsTrafficEnggAdminStatus
csMplsTrafficEnggAdminStatus.description: This entry is used to indicate if mpls traffic-eng is enabled or disabled on a level. This entry is used in conjunction with csMplsTrafficEnggLevel.

csMplsIsisExtensionsRowStatus.name: csMplsIsisExtensionsRowStatus
csMplsIsisExtensionsRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour.

csMplsOspfExtensionsTable.name: csMplsOspfExtensionsTable
csMplsOspfExtensionsTable.description: This table is used to support Ospf Extensions for Mpls

csMplsOspfExtensionsEntry.name: csMplsOspfExtensionsEntry
csMplsOspfExtensionsEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VrID

csMplsOspfAreaId.name: csMplsOspfAreaId
csMplsOspfAreaId.description: A router running MPLS is configured to flood traffic-engineering for OSPF area csMplsOspfAreaId

csMplsOspfAreaAdminStatus.name: csMplsOspfAreaAdminStatus
csMplsOspfAreaAdminStatus.description: This entry is used to indicate if mpls is enabled or disabled on area. This entry is used in conjunction with csMplsOspfAreaId.

csMplsOspfExtensionsRowStatus.name: csMplsOspfExtensionsRowStatus
csMplsOspfExtensionsRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour.

csMplsOspfExtensionsTableEnd.name: csMplsOspfExtensionsTableEnd
csMplsOspfExtensionsTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csLdpVrConfTable.name: csLdpVrConfTable
csLdpVrConfTable.description: This table is used to provide LDP related functionality at the router level

csLdpVrConfEntry.name: csLdpVrConfEntry
csLdpVrConfEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VR ID

csLdpVrConfRowStatus.name: csLdpVrConfRowStatus
csLdpVrConfRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour

csLdpVrAdminStatus.name: csLdpVrAdminStatus
csLdpVrAdminStatus.description: Indicates the administrator's intent as to whether LDP should be enabled or disabled on this router.

csLdpVrEventLogLevel.name: csLdpVrEventLogLevel
csLdpVrEventLogLevel.description: This specifies the level of detail for the event log.

csLdpVrEventLogArea.name: csLdpVrEventLogArea
csLdpVrEventLogArea.description: Each bit within this object enables loggin for a specific area within LDP. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within LDP and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ----------------------------------------------------- all 1 adjacency 2 packet-receive 3 packet-send 4 session 5 packet-verbose 6 lsp 7 end of description.

csLdpVrEventLogAreaMask.name: csLdpVrEventLogAreaMask
csLdpVrEventLogAreaMask.description: csLdpVrEventLogAreaMask is used to indicate which area bit is being set to on/off. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging within LDP and their corresponding bits identifiers. area bit ----------------------------------------------------- all 1 adjacency 2 packet-receive 3 packet-send 4 session 5 packet-verbose 6 lsp 7 end of description.

csLdpVrRoutePreference.name: csLdpVrRoutePreference
csLdpVrRoutePreference.description: Route preference Value for LDP routes

csLdpVrAutorouteAnnounce.name: csLdpVrAutorouteAnnounce
csLdpVrAutorouteAnnounce.description: Indicates the administrator's intent to let BGP use LDP LSP's present in MPLS RIB for the bgp-next-hop resolution

csLdpVrVpnAutorouteAnnounce.name: csLdpVrVpnAutorouteAnnounce
csLdpVrVpnAutorouteAnnounce.description: Indicates the administrator's intent to let Vpn use LDP LSP's present in MPLS RIB for the vpn-next-hop resolution

csLdpVrPwe3AutorouteAnnounce.name: csLdpVrPwe3AutorouteAnnounce
csLdpVrPwe3AutorouteAnnounce.description: Indicates the administrator's intent to let PWE3 use LDP LSP's present in MPLS RIB for the next-hop resolution

csLdpVrAcceptTargetedHellos.name: csLdpVrAcceptTargetedHellos
csLdpVrAcceptTargetedHellos.description: Indicates the targeted hellos are accepeted or rejected

csLdpVrConfTableEnd.name: csLdpVrConfTableEnd
csLdpVrConfTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csLdpEntityTable.name: csLdpEntityTable
csLdpEntityTable.description: This table contains information about the MPLS Label Distribution Protocol Entities which exist on this Label Switch Router (LSR).

csLdpEntityEntry.name: csLdpEntityEntry
csLdpEntityEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an LDP entity. An entry can be created by a network administrator or by an SNMP agent as instructed by LDP.

csLdpEntityIndex.name: csLdpEntityIndex
csLdpEntityIndex.description: This index is used as a secondary index to uniquely identify this row. Before creating a row in this table, the 'csLdpEntityIndexNext' object should be retrieved. That value should be used for the value of this index when creating a row in this table. (NOTE: if a value of zero (0) is retrieved, that indicates that no rows can be created in this table at this time. A secondary index (this object) is needed by some but not all, LDP implementations. For example in an LDP implementation which uses PPP, this index may be needed.

csLdpEntityRowStatus.name: csLdpEntityRowStatus
csLdpEntityRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention. Once the 'csLdpEntityAdminStatus' object has the value of 'up' and this object has the value of 'active' then the Entity will atttempt to contact an LDP Peer. If the value of this object is changed to 'notInService', then the Entity looses contact with the LDP Peer and all information related to that Peer must be removed from the MIB. This has the same effect as changing 'csLdpEntityAdminStatus' from 'enable' to 'disable'. When this object is set to 'active' and the value of the 'csLdpEntityAdminStatus' is 'enable' then this Entity will attempt to contact the Peer and establish new sessions.

csLdpEntityAdminStatus.name: csLdpEntityAdminStatus
csLdpEntityAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of this LDP Entity. If this object is changed from 'enable' to 'disable' and this entity has already attempted to establish contact with a Peer (which implies that the 'csLdpEntityRowStatus' object has been set to 'active'), then all contact with that Peer is lost and all information from that Peer needs to be removed from the MIB. At this point the user is able to change values which are related to this entity. When the admin status is set back to 'up', then this Entity will attempt to establish new sessions with the Peer.

csLdpEntityHelloTimer.name: csLdpEntityHelloTimer
csLdpEntityHelloTimer.description: Configures the interval in seconds between LDP hello's on this interface.

csLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer.name: csLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer
csLdpEntityHelloHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed Hello hold timer for this LDP Entity. A value of 0 means use the default, which is 15 seconds for Link Hellos and 45 seconds for Targeted Hellos. A value of 65535 means infinite.

csLdpEntityKeepAliveTimer.name: csLdpEntityKeepAliveTimer
csLdpEntityKeepAliveTimer.description: Configures the interval in seconds between keepalive messages on this interface.

csLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer.name: csLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer
csLdpEntityKeepAliveHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed keep alive hold timer for this LDP Entity.

csLdpEntityTransportAddr.name: csLdpEntityTransportAddr
csLdpEntityTransportAddr.description: This is used to store transport ip address for LDP Entity

csLdpTargetTable.name: csLdpTargetTable
csLdpTargetTable.description: This table contains information about the MPLS Label Distribution Protocol Targeted Sessions which exist on this Label Switch Router (LSR).

csLdpTargetEntry.name: csLdpTargetEntry
csLdpTargetEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an LDP Targeted Session. An entry can be created by a network administrator or by an SNMP agent as instructed by LDP.

csLdpTargetPeerIpAddr.name: csLdpTargetPeerIpAddr
csLdpTargetPeerIpAddr.description: This index is used as a secondary index to uniquely identify this row. Before creating a row in this table, the 'csLdpTargetIndexNext' object should be retrieved. That value should be used for the value of this index when creating a row in this table. (NOTE: if a value of zero (0) is retrieved, that indicates that no rows can be created in this table at this time. A secondary index (this object) is needed by some but not all, LDP implementations. For example in an LDP implementation which uses PPP, this index may be needed.

csLdpTargetRowStatus.name: csLdpTargetRowStatus
csLdpTargetRowStatus.description: An object that allows entries in this table to be created and deleted using the RowStatus convention. Once the 'csLdpTargetAdminStatus' object has the value of 'up' and this object has the value of 'active' then the Session will atttempt to contact an LDP Peer. If the value of this object is changed to 'notInService', then the Session looses contact with the LDP Peer and all information related to that Peer must be removed from the MIB. This has the same effect as changing 'csLdpTargetAdminStatus' from 'enable' to 'disable'. When this object is set to 'active' and the value of the 'csLdpTargetAdminStatus' is 'enable' then this Session will attempt to contact the Peer and establish new sessions.

csLdpTargetAdminStatus.name: csLdpTargetAdminStatus
csLdpTargetAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of this LDP Targeted Session. If this object is changed from 'enable' to 'disable' and this Session has already attempted to establish contact with a Peer (which implies that the 'csLdpTargetRowStatus' object has been set to 'active'), then all contact with that Peer is lost and all information from that Peer needs to be removed from the MIB. At this point the user is able to change values which are related to this entity. When the admin status is set back to 'up', then this Session will attempt to establish new sessions with the Peer.

csLdpTargetHelloTimer.name: csLdpTargetHelloTimer
csLdpTargetHelloTimer.description: Configures the interval in seconds between LDP Targeted hello's on VR

csLdpTargetHelloHoldTimer.name: csLdpTargetHelloHoldTimer
csLdpTargetHelloHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed Hello hold timer for this LDP Targeted Session. A value of 0 means use the default, which is 15 seconds for Link Hellos and 45 seconds for Targeted Hellos. A value of 65535 means infinite.

csLdpTargetKeepAliveTimer.name: csLdpTargetKeepAliveTimer
csLdpTargetKeepAliveTimer.description: Configures the interval in seconds between keepalive messages

csLdpTargetKeepAliveHoldTimer.name: csLdpTargetKeepAliveHoldTimer
csLdpTargetKeepAliveHoldTimer.description: The two octet value which is the proposed keep alive hold timer for this LDP Targeted Session.

csLdpTargetActive.name: csLdpTargetActive
csLdpTargetActive.description: If TRUE indicates that this is an active targeted entity i.e a targeted neighbor is explictly configured through CLI. The value set to true while creating an targeted entity

csOrionMplsEnd.name: csOrionMplsEnd
csOrionMplsEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csVpnVrfTable.name: csVpnVrfTable
csVpnVrfTable.description: This table is used to configure RFC2547 VPN routing instances. Each instance represent the partication of this router as a VRF in an BGP/MPLS VPN provider edge (PE). A router can suppport multiple VPN routing instances to allow peering with with multiple VPN providers.

csVpnVrfEntry.name: csVpnVrfEntry
csVpnVrfEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single RFC2547 BGP/MPLS VPN routing instance.

csVpnVrfName.name: csVpnVrfName
csVpnVrfName.description: The name for this VPN instance. It can contain alphanumic characters and hiphens (-).

csVpnVrfProviderName.name: csVpnVrfProviderName
csVpnVrfProviderName.description: The name of the VPN Service Provider VR for this instance. Multiple Service Provider names can be specified by separating them using spaces. The VRF instance will select to use one of these providers. If the selected provider connectivity not active then the VRF instance will select another provider from its list. A VRF peers with only one provider at any time.

csVpnVrfRouteDistinguisher.name: csVpnVrfRouteDistinguisher
csVpnVrfRouteDistinguisher.description: The route distinguisher for this VPN customer instance.

csVpnVrfAdminStatus.name: csVpnVrfAdminStatus
csVpnVrfAdminStatus.description: The enable/disable status of this VPN customer instance.

csVpnVrfLogAreaFlag.name: csVpnVrfLogAreaFlag
csVpnVrfLogAreaFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables logging for a specific area within the VPN routing instance. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging: area bit ------------------------------------------------------ system 0 routes-receive 1 routes-send 2 vpn-sp (control interface to VPN-SP) 3 end of description.

csVpnVrfLogLevelFlag.name: csVpnVrfLogLevelFlag
csVpnVrfLogLevelFlag.description: This object enables logging at a specific level.

csVpnVrfPreference.name: csVpnVrfPreference
csVpnVrfPreference.description: This default preference value for routes added by the instance to the RIB. A value of -1 indicates that this attribute is not configured.

csVpnVrfRowStatus.name: csVpnVrfRowStatus
csVpnVrfRowStatus.description: The variable is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

csVpnVrfSiteOfOrigin.name: csVpnVrfSiteOfOrigin
csVpnVrfSiteOfOrigin.description: The site-f-origin extended community attribute for this VPN customer instance.

csVpnVrfAllowASIn.name: csVpnVrfAllowASIn
csVpnVrfAllowASIn.description: To allow duplicate AS numbers for the BGP VPN routes received by this VRF. This attribute specifies the number of duplicates which are permitted. By default duplocate ASNs are not permitted. This attribute is used only if the VR is configured with an ASN, i.e., BGP is enabled.

csVpnVrfASOverride.name: csVpnVrfASOverride
csVpnVrfASOverride.description: To allow the VPN service provider VR to override a VRF's ASN with the provders ASN. This option is normally used along with the site-of-origin option.

csVpnVrfMaxRoutes.name: csVpnVrfMaxRoutes
csVpnVrfMaxRoutes.description: The maximum number of routes the VRF instance is allowed to add to the RIB. A value of -1 indicates that this attribute is not set, i.e., no maximum is configured.

csVpnVrfMaxRoutesExceedAction.name: csVpnVrfMaxRoutesExceedAction
csVpnVrfMaxRoutesExceedAction.description: The action to take if the number of routes exceed the csVpnVrfMaxRoutes configured for this VRF. discard: Routes are rejected with an error mesaage warning-message: Routes are accepted but a warning message is displayed.

csVpnVrfRouteTargetTable.name: csVpnVrfRouteTargetTable
csVpnVrfRouteTargetTable.description: This table is used to configure import/export route targets for RFC2547 VPN routing instances (VRFs).

csVpnVrfRouteTargetEntry.name: csVpnVrfRouteTargetEntry
csVpnVrfRouteTargetEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single route target. It is an 8-byte value. Also, each entry indicates if it is an import or export route target

csVpnVrfRouteTargetType.name: csVpnVrfRouteTargetType
csVpnVrfRouteTargetType.description: The type of Route Target entry.

csVpnVrfRouteTargetValue.name: csVpnVrfRouteTargetValue
csVpnVrfRouteTargetValue.description: The route target value. It is an extended community encoded as an 8-byte value. An extended community is specified either as <4-byte-ip-address>:<2-byte num> or as <2-byte AS-num>:<4-byte-num>.

csVpnVrfRouteTargetRowStatus.name: csVpnVrfRouteTargetRowStatus
csVpnVrfRouteTargetRowStatus.description: The variable is used to create, modify or delete a row in this table.

csOrionViPbfFilterTable.name: csOrionViPbfFilterTable
csOrionViPbfFilterTable.description: This table specifies a set of acl's to be applied to packets received over an interface. The first entry whose ACL matches a packet causes the packet to be forwarded over the specified next-hop.

csOrionViPbfFilterEntry.name: csOrionViPbfFilterEntry
csOrionViPbfFilterEntry.description: Each filter specifies whether packets matching a specific access list entry are forwarded to the specified next hop.

csOrionViPbfFilterIndex.name: csOrionViPbfFilterIndex
csOrionViPbfFilterIndex.description: The Index of this particular PBF Filter.

csOrionViPbfFilterAclId.name: csOrionViPbfFilterAclId
csOrionViPbfFilterAclId.description: The Id of an access list entry (from csOrionGenAclTable).

csOrionViPbfFilterEgressViId.name: csOrionViPbfFilterEgressViId
csOrionViPbfFilterEgressViId.description: The index value to uniquely identify the local interface through which the next hop for matching flows should be reached. This field is valid for VIs connected to point-point links only. A value of 0 (zero) indicates the next-hop-vi is not specified.

csOrionViPbfFilterNextHopIpAddr.name: csOrionViPbfFilterNextHopIpAddr
csOrionViPbfFilterNextHopIpAddr.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. A value of 0 (zero) indicates the next-hop-addr is not specified.

csOrionViPbfFilterAction.name: csOrionViPbfFilterAction
csOrionViPbfFilterAction.description: The action performed by this filter.

csOrionViPbfFilterRowStatus.name: csOrionViPbfFilterRowStatus
csOrionViPbfFilterRowStatus.description: A row status type for this Table entry.

csOrionViPbfFilterCounter.name: csOrionViPbfFilterCounter
csOrionViPbfFilterCounter.description: Enable or disable counter on this filter.

csIgmpInterfaceTable.name: csIgmpInterfaceTable
csIgmpInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the interfaces on which IGMP is enabled.

csIgmpInterfaceEntry.name: csIgmpInterfaceEntry
csIgmpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an interface on which IGMP is enabled.

csIgmpInterfaceIfIndex.name: csIgmpInterfaceIfIndex
csIgmpInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which IGMP is enabled.

csIgmpInterfaceQueryInterval.name: csIgmpInterfaceQueryInterval
csIgmpInterfaceQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this interface.

csIgmpInterfaceStatus.name: csIgmpInterfaceStatus
csIgmpInterfaceStatus.description: The activation of a row enables IGMP on the interface. The destruction of a row disables IGMP on the interface.

csIgmpInterfaceVersion.name: csIgmpInterfaceVersion
csIgmpInterfaceVersion.description: The version of IGMP which is running on this interface. This object can be used to configure a router capable of running either value. For IGMP to function correctly, all routers on a LAN must be configured to run the same version of IGMP on that LAN.

csIgmpInterfaceQuerier.name: csIgmpInterfaceQuerier
csIgmpInterfaceQuerier.description: The address of the IGMP Querier on the IP subnet to which this interface is attached.

csIgmpInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTime.name: csIgmpInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTime
csIgmpInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time advertised in IGMPv2 queries on this interface.

csIgmpInterfaceQuerierUpTime.name: csIgmpInterfaceQuerierUpTime
csIgmpInterfaceQuerierUpTime.description: The time since csIgmpInterfaceQuerier was last changed.

csIgmpInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime.name: csIgmpInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime
csIgmpInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime.description: The amount of time remaining before the Other Querier Present Timer expires. If the local system is the querier, the value of this object is zero.

csIgmpInterfaceVersion1QuerierTimer.name: csIgmpInterfaceVersion1QuerierTimer
csIgmpInterfaceVersion1QuerierTimer.description: The time remaining until the host assumes that there are no IGMPv1 routers present on the interface. While this is non- zero, the host will reply to all queries with version 1 membership reports.

csIgmpInterfaceWrongVersionQueries.name: csIgmpInterfaceWrongVersionQueries
csIgmpInterfaceWrongVersionQueries.description: The number of queries received whose IGMP version does not match csIgmpInterfaceVersion, over the lifetime of the row entry. IGMP requires that all routers on a LAN be configured to run the same version of IGMP. Thus, if any queries are received with the wrong version, this indicates a configuration error.

csIgmpInterfaceJoins.name: csIgmpInterfaceJoins
csIgmpInterfaceJoins.description: The number of times a group membership has been added on this interface; that is, the number of times an entry for this interface has been added to the Cache Table. This object gives an indication of the amount of IGMP activity over the lifetime of the row entry.

csIgmpInterfaceProxyIfIndex.name: csIgmpInterfaceProxyIfIndex
csIgmpInterfaceProxyIfIndex.description: Some devices implement a form of IGMP proxying whereby memberships learned on the interface represented by this row, cause IGMP Host Membership Reports to be sent on the interface whose ifIndex value is given by this object. Such a device would implement the csIgmpV2RouterMIBGroup only on its router interfaces (those interfaces with non-zero csIgmpInterfaceProxyIfIndex). Typically, the value of this object is 0, indicating that no proxying is being done.

csIgmpInterfaceGroups.name: csIgmpInterfaceGroups
csIgmpInterfaceGroups.description: The current number of entries for this interface in the Cache Table.

csIgmpInterfaceRobustness.name: csIgmpInterfaceRobustness
csIgmpInterfaceRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

csIgmpInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl.name: csIgmpInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl
csIgmpInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group. The value of this object is irrelevant if csIgmpInterfaceVersion is 1.

csIgmpInterfaceMulticastTTLThreshold.name: csIgmpInterfaceMulticastTTLThreshold
csIgmpInterfaceMulticastTTLThreshold.description: The Multicast TTL threshold value to be used by IGMP forwarding. This value is used to contol multicast packets from going beyone a certain number of routers.

csIgmpInterfaceAdminStatus.name: csIgmpInterfaceAdminStatus
csIgmpInterfaceAdminStatus.description: This attribute controls the enable/disable settings of an IGMP or IGMP Proxy interface. If this attribute is set to disable, the interface configuration will be saved.

csIgmpCacheTable.name: csIgmpCacheTable
csIgmpCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface.

csIgmpCacheEntry.name: csIgmpCacheEntry
csIgmpCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the csIgmpCacheTable.

csIgmpCacheAddress.name: csIgmpCacheAddress
csIgmpCacheAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

csIgmpCacheIfIndex.name: csIgmpCacheIfIndex
csIgmpCacheIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

csIgmpCacheSelf.name: csIgmpCacheSelf
csIgmpCacheSelf.description: An indication of whether the local system is a member of this group address on this interface.

csIgmpCacheLastReporter.name: csIgmpCacheLastReporter
csIgmpCacheLastReporter.description: The IP address of the source of the last membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this interface. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0.0.0.0.

csIgmpCacheUpTime.name: csIgmpCacheUpTime
csIgmpCacheUpTime.description: The time elapsed since this entry was created.

csIgmpCacheExpiryTime.name: csIgmpCacheExpiryTime
csIgmpCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. A value of 0 indicates that the entry is only present because csIgmpCacheSelf is true and that if the router left the group, this entry would be aged out immediately. Note that some implementations may process membership reports from the local system in the same way as reports from other hosts, so a value of 0 is not required.

csIgmpCacheVersion1HostTimer.name: csIgmpCacheVersion1HostTimer
csIgmpCacheVersion1HostTimer.description: The time remaining until the local router will assume that there are no longer any IGMP version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface. Upon hearing any IGMPv1 Membership Report, this value is reset to the group membership timer. While this time remaining is non-zero, the local router ignores any IGMPv2 Leave messages for this group that it receives on this interface.

csIgmpStaticGroupTable.name: csIgmpStaticGroupTable
csIgmpStaticGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast static groups to which traffic needs to be sent to even if IGMP is not enabled on the respective interface.

csIgmpStaticGroupEntry.name: csIgmpStaticGroupEntry
csIgmpStaticGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the csIgmpStaticGroupTable.

csIgmpStaticGroupIfIndex.name: csIgmpStaticGroupIfIndex
csIgmpStaticGroupIfIndex.description: The interface for which the static group has been configured.

csIgmpStaticGroupAddress.name: csIgmpStaticGroupAddress
csIgmpStaticGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which corresponds to the configured static group.

csIgmpStaticGroupStatus.name: csIgmpStaticGroupStatus
csIgmpStaticGroupStatus.description: The activation of a row enables a static group configuration on the interface. The destruction of a row disables the static group configuration on the interface.

csIgmpAccessGroupTable.name: csIgmpAccessGroupTable
csIgmpAccessGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast access groups to which traffic needs to be sent to or rejected from. This table will usually be used to reject traffic to a particular set of multicast groups

csIgmpAccessGroupEntry.name: csIgmpAccessGroupEntry
csIgmpAccessGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the csIgmpAccessGroupTable.

csIgmpAccessGroupIfIndex.name: csIgmpAccessGroupIfIndex
csIgmpAccessGroupIfIndex.description: The interface for which the access group has been configured.

csIgmpAccessGroupAddress.name: csIgmpAccessGroupAddress
csIgmpAccessGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which corresponds to the configured access group.

csIgmpAccessGroupStatus.name: csIgmpAccessGroupStatus
csIgmpAccessGroupStatus.description: The activation of a row enables a access group configuration on the interface. The destruction of a row disables the access group configuration on the interface.

csIgmpGeneralTable.name: csIgmpGeneralTable
csIgmpGeneralTable.description: MIB object to control router level attributes of IGMP.

csIgmpGeneralEntry.name: csIgmpGeneralEntry
csIgmpGeneralEntry.description: Information regarding the router level attributes of IGMP.

csIgmpGeneralEntryRowStatus.name: csIgmpGeneralEntryRowStatus
csIgmpGeneralEntryRowStatus.description: The activation of a row enables an IGMP object for the router. The destruction of a row destroys the IGMP object for this router.

csPwVcTable.name: csPwVcTable
csPwVcTable.description: This table specifies information for connecting various emulated services to various tunnel type.

csPwVcEntry.name: csPwVcEntry
csPwVcEntry.description: A row in this table represents an emulated virtual connection (VC) across a packet network. It is indexed by: - The csPwVcIndex. Uniquely identifying a singular connection (or set of connections). If a set, individual VCs are identified by the Instance.

csPwVcIndex.name: csPwVcIndex
csPwVcIndex.description: Primary index for the conceptual row identifying a VC (or set of VCs) within this PW Emulation VC table.

csPwVcID.name: csPwVcID
csPwVcID.reference: Martini, et al, . Note: as specified in l2circuit-trans: It is REQUIRED to assign the same VC ID, and VC type for a given circuit in both directions.
csPwVcID.description: Used in the outgoing VC ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' when LDP signaling is used.

csPwVcOutboundGroupID.name: csPwVcOutboundGroupID
csPwVcOutboundGroupID.description: Used in the outbound Group ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' when some control methods (for example LDP) is used for VC setup, zero if not used.

csPwVcInboundGroupID.name: csPwVcInboundGroupID
csPwVcInboundGroupID.description: Obtained from the inbound Group ID field in the remote 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' as received by control methods are used for VC setup, zero if not used or not known yet.

csPwVcInboundMTU.name: csPwVcInboundMTU
csPwVcInboundMTU.description: MTU of the interface at the remote PE. 0 means assume same as outbound MTU

csPwVcPeerAddrType.name: csPwVcPeerAddrType
csPwVcPeerAddrType.description: Denotes the address type of the peer node signaling address if PW signaling is used for the VC creation. It should be set to 'notApplicable' if PE/PW signaling is not used, i.e. csPwVcOwner is set to 'manual'.

csPwVcPeerIpv4Addr.name: csPwVcPeerIpv4Addr
csPwVcPeerIpv4Addr.description: If csPwVcPeerAddrType is set to ipV4(1), then this value will contain the IPv4 address of the peer node PW/PE signaling entity. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

csPwVcPeerIpv6Addr.name: csPwVcPeerIpv6Addr
