csPwVcPeerIpv6Addr.description: If csPwVcPeerAddrType is set to ipV6(2), then this value will contain the Ipv6 address of the peer node PW/PE signaling entity. This object is otherwise insignificant and should contain a value of 0.

csPwVcOutboundVcLabel.name: csPwVcOutboundVcLabel
csPwVcOutboundVcLabel.description: The VC label used in the outbound direction. It may be set up manually if owner is 'manual' or automatically otherwise. Examples: For MPLS PSN, it represents the 20 bits of VC tag, for L2TP it represent the 16 bits Session ID.

csPwVcInboundVcLabel.name: csPwVcInboundVcLabel
csPwVcInboundVcLabel.description: The VC label used in the inbound direction. It may be set up manually if owner is 'manual' or automatically otherwise. Examples: For MPLS PSN, it represents the 20 bits of VC tag, for L2TP it represent the 16 bits Session ID.

csPwVcInboundMode.name: csPwVcInboundMode
csPwVcInboundMode.description: This object is used to enable greater security for implementation that use global VC label space. In conservative mode, inbound packets with a VC label are accepted only from tunnels that are associated to the same VC via the inbound tunnel table. The entries in the inbound tunnel table are either explicitly configured or implicitly known by the control protocol used for VC set-up. If such association is not known, not configured or not desired, liberal mode should be configured, and the node should accept the packet based on the VC label only regardless of the outer tunnel used to carry the VC.

csPwVcName.name: csPwVcName
csPwVcName.description: The canonical name assigned to the VC. This name can be used to refer to the VC on the node console port.

csPwVcDescr.name: csPwVcDescr
csPwVcDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the VC. If there is no description this object contains a zero length string.

csPwVcCreateTime.name: csPwVcCreateTime
csPwVcCreateTime.description: System time when this VC was created.

csPwVcUpTime.name: csPwVcUpTime
csPwVcUpTime.description: Number of consecutive ticks this VC has been 'up' in both directions together (i.e. 'up' is observed in csPwVcOperStatus.)

csPwVcType.name: csPwVcType
csPwVcType.reference: Martini, et al, . Note: as specified in l2circuit-trans: It is REQUIRED to assign the same VC ID, and VC type for a given circuit in both directions.
csPwVcType.description: This value dictates what service-specific tables are indexed by csPwVcIndex and csPwVcInstance. For example, if set for 'cem' csPwVcIndex indexes the csPwVcCemTable in [CEMMIB]. Note: CEM will also have the MSBit set in the VC type (0x8008). This is the 'Control Word' bit used within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' when LDP signaling is used

csPwVcOwner.name: csPwVcOwner
csPwVcOwner.description: Set by the operator to indicate the protocol responsible for establishing this VC. Value 'manual' is used in all cases where no signaling is used to set-up the VC, i.e. require configuration of all entries in the VC tables including VC labels, etc. The value 'signaling' is used in case of standard signaling of the VC for the specific PSN, for example LDP for MPLS PSN as specified in . Value 'other' is used for other types of signaling.

csPwVcPsnType.name: csPwVcPsnType
csPwVcPsnType.description: Set by the operator to indicate the PSN type on which this VC will be carried. Based on this object, the relevant PSN table entries are created in the in the PSN specific MIB modules. For example, if mpls(1) is defined, the agent create an entry in csPwVcMplsTable, which further define the MPLS PSN configuration.

csPwVcPriority.name: csPwVcPriority
csPwVcPriority.description: This object define the relative priority of the VC instance in a lowest-to-highest fashion. VC instances with the same priority are treated with equal priority (i.e. are signaled in parallel). VC instances dropped will be set 'dormant' (as indicated in csPwVcOperStatus).

csPwVcAdminStatus.name: csPwVcAdminStatus
csPwVcAdminStatus.description: The desired operational status of this VC. It is set by the operator if csPwVcIsIf is set to false. Otherwise, it reflects the ifIndex AdminStatus.

csPwVcOperStatus.name: csPwVcOperStatus
csPwVcOperStatus.description: Indicates the actual combined operational status of this VC. It is 'up' if both csPwVcInboundOperStatus and csPwVcOutboundOperStatus are in 'up' state. For all other values, if the VCs in both directions are of the same value it reflects that value, otherwise it is set to 'unknown', and the operator may consult the per direction OperStatus for fault isolation.

csPwVcInboundOperStatus.name: csPwVcInboundOperStatus
csPwVcInboundOperStatus.description: Indicates the actual operational status of this VC in the inbound direction. - down: if PW signaling has not yet finished, or indications available at the service level indicate that the VC is not passing packets. - testing: if AdminStatus at the VC level is set to test. - dormant: The VC is not available because of the required resources are occupied VC with higher priority VCs . - notPresent: Some component is missing to accomplish the set up of the VC. - lowerLayerDown: The underlying PSN is not in OperStatus 'up'.

csPwVcOutboundOperStatus.name: csPwVcOutboundOperStatus
csPwVcOutboundOperStatus.description: Indicates the actual operational status of this VC in the outbound direction - down: if PW signaling has not yet finished, or indications available at the service level indicate that the VC is not passing packets. - testing: if AdminStatus at the VC level is set to test. - dormant: The VC is not available because of the required resources are occupied VC with higher priority VCs . - notPresent: Some component is missing to accomplish the set up of the VC. - lowerLayerDown: The underlying PSN is not in OperStatus 'up'.

csPwVcRowStatus.name: csPwVcRowStatus
csPwVcRowStatus.description: For creating, modifying, and deleting this row.

csPwVcStorageType.name: csPwVcStorageType
csPwVcStorageType.description: This variable indicates the storage type for this object.

csPwVcCeIntf.name: csPwVcCeIntf
csPwVcCeIntf.description: This object is used to identify the CE interface. This format allows for many formats. We only support LI for now. The format used for this ascii-string valued object is as follows: 'B|L VPNID|SlotID/VRID|PortID/VIID|LLID:BIID' Where 'B' indicates the other end is a Bridge Interface. 'L' indicates this connection maps to a Logical Link. 'VPNID' is a Virtual Private Network ID. 'SlotID' identifies a specific slot on the Orion Box. 'VRID' is a Virtual Router ID for the VPN specified by VPNID. 'PortID' identifies a specific Port on the blade installed in the previously identified slot. 'VIID' is a Virtual Interface on the VR identified by VRID. 'LLID' is a Logical Link ID on PortID. BIID is the bridge interface ID. For example, if this connection maps to a bridge interface. (BI 3 on VI number 1 on VR 1.2.3.4 on VPN 4), this object might be set to this value: 'B 4/1.2.3.4/1:3' If this connection maps to subinterface 20 on Logical Link 100 on Port 2 of Slot 2, this object might be set to this value: 'L 2/2:100:10' If this Virtual Interface has not been mapped, this object will have the value 'DISCONNECTED'.

csPwVcForwardSlot.name: csPwVcForwardSlot
csPwVcForwardSlot.description: Slot number of the data forwarding processor engine. 0 means not set.

csPwVcForwardPE.name: csPwVcForwardPE
csPwVcForwardPE.description: Processor engine number of the data forwarding processor engine. 0 means not set.

csPwVcCtrlWord.name: csPwVcCtrlWord
csPwVcCtrlWord.description: Include and except control word in the data packets.

csPwVcSeqNumber.name: csPwVcSeqNumber
csPwVcSeqNumber.description: Include and check the sequence numbers.

csPwVcTestResult.name: csPwVcTestResult
csPwVcTestResult.description: The result of the previous testing request.

csPwVcVlanId.name: csPwVcVlanId
csPwVcVlanId.description: The result of the previous testing request. Note: A valid VLAN ID should be provided if Connected to a BI.

csPwe3ConfTable.name: csPwe3ConfTable
csPwe3ConfTable.description: This table is used to Configure Mpls on a Virtual Router.

csPwe3ConfEntry.name: csPwe3ConfEntry
csPwe3ConfEntry.description: This entry is indexed by the VPN and VR ID

csPwe3EventLogLevel.name: csPwe3EventLogLevel
csPwe3EventLogLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of details for event logs for L2oL3

csPwe3EventLogArea.name: csPwe3EventLogArea
csPwe3EventLogArea.description: Each bit within this object enables logging for a specific area within the Pwe3 instance. Below is a list of the different areas available for logging: area bit ------------------------------------------------------ events 0 forwarding 1 end of description.

csPwe3ConfRowStatus.name: csPwe3ConfRowStatus
csPwe3ConfRowStatus.description: The existence state of this table. This object follows the Row Status behaviour

csOrionChangeTableOID.name: csOrionChangeTableOID
csOrionChangeTableOID.description: Object identifier of the Table, which was changed.

csOrionChangeSource.name: csOrionChangeSource
csOrionChangeSource.description: The source of the configuration change (illegal).

csOrionChangeSourceUserName.name: csOrionChangeSourceUserName
csOrionChangeSourceUserName.description: A textual string containing information about the user name of the source configuration change.

csOrionLogLinkSlotIndex.name: csOrionLogLinkSlotIndex
csOrionLogLinkSlotIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the slot index of the Logical Link.

csOrionLogLinkPortIndex.name: csOrionLogLinkPortIndex
csOrionLogLinkPortIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the port index (relative to the slot index) of the Logical Link.

csOrionLogLinkChannelIndex.name: csOrionLogLinkChannelIndex
csOrionLogLinkChannelIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the channel index (relative to the slot/port index) of the Logical Link. If there is no channel, this object has the value -1.

csOrionLogLinkSubIfIndex.name: csOrionLogLinkSubIfIndex
csOrionLogLinkSubIfIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the sub interface index (relative to the slot/port[:chan] index) of the Logical Link. If there is no sub interface, this object has the value -1.

csOrionNumConfigChanges.name: csOrionNumConfigChanges
csOrionNumConfigChanges.description: Number of changed objects for which the csOrionConfigChange Trap PDU generated. This identifies the number of VarBinds follows this object in the csOrionConfigChange Trap PDU.

csOrionConfigChangeType.name: csOrionConfigChangeType
csOrionConfigChangeType.description: For ConfigChange Traps, this identifies the type of change that was made on a table. For scalar objects, this always has the value 1.

csOrionPortIndex.name: csOrionPortIndex
csOrionPortIndex.description: For port level alarms related traps, this identifies the port index (relative to the slot index) of the alarm origination.

csOrionRestoreBladeStatus.name: csOrionRestoreBladeStatus
csOrionRestoreBladeStatus.description: Blade Restoration status. Fail if blade is not restored successfully. Success if blade restoration is successfull. Cold-start if blade reboots. Note that cold-start will not have restored data presented in the trap packet

csOrionRestoreSlotIndex.name: csOrionRestoreSlotIndex
csOrionRestoreSlotIndex.description: Slot number of the affected blade.

csOrionRestoreNumVRs.name: csOrionRestoreNumVRs
csOrionRestoreNumVRs.description: Number of VRs affected by this blade restoration trap. This corresponds the number of VPN/VRs that follows.

csOrionAlarmType.name: csOrionAlarmType
csOrionAlarmType.description: For port level alarms related DS3 traps, this identifies the alarm which is cleared now.

csOrionOc3AlarmType.name: csOrionOc3AlarmType
csOrionOc3AlarmType.description: For port level alarms related OC3 traps, this identifies the type of alarm being sent out.

csOrionAlarmAffectType.name: csOrionAlarmAffectType
csOrionAlarmAffectType.description: Indicates that it is a not service affecting alarm or a service affecting alarm.

csOrionAlarmSeverityType.name: csOrionAlarmSeverityType
csOrionAlarmSeverityType.description: Indicates the severity of this alarm.

csOrionLogLinkModuleIndex.name: csOrionLogLinkModuleIndex
csOrionLogLinkModuleIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the module index (relative to the slot index) of the Logical Link.

csOrionModuleIndex.name: csOrionModuleIndex
csOrionModuleIndex.description: For Logical Link up/down traps, this identifies the module index (relative to the slot index) of the Logical Link.

csOrionBladeTable.name: csOrionBladeTable
csOrionBladeTable.description: A list of Blades which belongs to Orion box.

csOrionBladeEntry.name: csOrionBladeEntry
csOrionBladeEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular Blade.

csOrionBladeSlotLocation.name: csOrionBladeSlotLocation
csOrionBladeSlotLocation.description: Slot Location of the Blade in the Orion box.

csOrionBladeDescr.name: csOrionBladeDescr
csOrionBladeDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the blade. This string should include the name of the manufacturer and the product name.

csOrionBladeType.name: csOrionBladeType
csOrionBladeType.description: The type of blade inserted in this slot.

csOrionBladeState.name: csOrionBladeState
csOrionBladeState.description: The current state of this blade.

csOrionBladeEnginesNumb.name: csOrionBladeEnginesNumb
csOrionBladeEnginesNumb.description: The number of engines on the blade. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladePortNumb.name: csOrionBladePortNumb
csOrionBladePortNumb.description: The number of ports on this blade (note, process blades have no ports).

csOrionBladeSerialNumb.name: csOrionBladeSerialNumb
csOrionBladeSerialNumb.description: The serial number of the blade. This is a series of alphanumeric characters which uniquely identifies this blade. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladeHwVer.name: csOrionBladeHwVer
csOrionBladeHwVer.description: A textual string containing information about the hardware revision version. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladeSwVer.name: csOrionBladeSwVer
csOrionBladeSwVer.description: A textual string containing information about the software revision version. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladeReset.name: csOrionBladeReset
csOrionBladeReset.description: The software reset for this blade. It is an action object such that when set to 'reset' will reset this blade. Setting it to 'none' has no effect, and when it is retrieved the value will always be 'none'.

csOrionBladeConfigAttributes.name: csOrionBladeConfigAttributes
csOrionBladeConfigAttributes.description: Contains the configured or static parameters of this blade. Each parameter is represented by a type-lenth-value data structure. A single TLV may contain individual TLVs. The types IDs currently supported are : 1 - Description (string) [sample only] more parameters will be added. NOTE: This object is deprecated and is replaced by individual objects starting from csOrionBladeModelNumb.

csOrionBladeOperAttributes.name: csOrionBladeOperAttributes
csOrionBladeOperAttributes.description: Contains the operational or dynamic parameters of this blade. Each parameter is represented by a type-lenth-value data structure. A single TLV may contain individual TLVs. The types IDs currently supported are : 1 - Description (string) [sample only] more parameters will be added. NOTE: This object is deprecated and is replaced by individual objects starting from csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor1.

csOrionBladeModelNumb.name: csOrionBladeModelNumb
csOrionBladeModelNumb.description: A textual string containing information about the model number of the blade.

csOrionBladeCLEICode.name: csOrionBladeCLEICode
csOrionBladeCLEICode.description: A textual string containing information about the CLEI of the blade.

csOrionBladeFPGAVersion.name: csOrionBladeFPGAVersion
csOrionBladeFPGAVersion.description: A textual string containing information about the FPGA version of the blade.

csOrionBladePort1MacAddr.name: csOrionBladePort1MacAddr
csOrionBladePort1MacAddr.description: MAC Address of ethernet port 1 on the blade. Applies only to control or ethernet blade.

csOrionBladePort2MacAddr.name: csOrionBladePort2MacAddr
csOrionBladePort2MacAddr.description: MAC Address of ethernet port 2 on the blade. Applies only to control or ethernet blade.

csOrionBladePort3MacAddr.name: csOrionBladePort3MacAddr
csOrionBladePort3MacAddr.description: MAC Address of ethernet port 3 on the blade. Applies only to control or ethernet blade.

csOrionBladePort4MacAddr.name: csOrionBladePort4MacAddr
csOrionBladePort4MacAddr.description: MAC Address of ethernet port 4 on the blade. Applies only to control or ethernet blade.

csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderProduct.name: csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderProduct
csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderProduct.description: A textual string containing information about the IPSX loader.

csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderVersion.name: csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderVersion
csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderVersion.description: A textual string containing information about the version of the loader NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderDate.name: csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderDate
csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the loader. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderTime.name: csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderTime
csOrionBladeIPSXLoaderTime.description: A textual string containing information about the time of the loader.

csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor1.name: csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor1
csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor1.description: A textual string containing information about the temperature of sensor 1.

csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor2.name: csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor2
csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor2.description: A textual string containing information about the temperature of sensor 2.

csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor3.name: csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor3
csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor3.description: A textual string containing information about the temperature of sensor 3.

csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor4.name: csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor4
csOrionBladeTemperatureSensor4.description: A textual string containing information about the temperature of sensor 4.

csOrionBladeShutdown.name: csOrionBladeShutdown
csOrionBladeShutdown.description: The software shutdown for this blade. It is an action object such that when set to 'shutdown' will stop the file-system on this blade. Setting it to 'none' has no effect, and when it is retrieved the value will always be 'none'.

csOrionBladeNumSharcCrypto.name: csOrionBladeNumSharcCrypto
csOrionBladeNumSharcCrypto.description: Number of crypto modules present on the sharc blade

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId1.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId1
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId1.description: Blade port in which the first crypto is present (Note, -1 indicates that there are no crypto modules in the blade)

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId2.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId2
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoModuleId2.description: Blade port in which the first crypto is present (Note, -1 indicates that there are one or less crypto modules in the blade)

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType1.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType1
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType1.description: Type of the first sharc crypto module present

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType2.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType2
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoType2.description: Type of the second sharc crypto module present

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial1.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial1
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial1.description: The serial number of the first sharc crypto module - series of alphanumeric characters which uniquely identifies the crypto module on this blade.

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial2.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial2
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoSerial2.description: The serial number of the second sharc crypto module - series of alphanumeric characters which uniquely identifies the crypto module on this blade.

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly1.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly1
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly1.description: The assembly number of the first sharc crypto module

csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly2.name: csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly2
csOrionBladeSharcCryptoAssembly2.description: The assembly number of the second sharc crypto module

csOrionEngineTable.name: csOrionEngineTable
csOrionEngineTable.description: A list of Process Engines such as CPU, Search Engine and Encryption Engine which exist in the Orion box. This table is used as csOrionModuleTable. Engine becomes a special type of Module. Module can also be a network interface. To keep the minimum change in 3.0 for the addition of module and maintain the compatibility between 3.0 and 3.1, the name of csOrionEngineTable is still used in 3.0. After 3.1, this table will be rename as csOrionModuleTable.

csOrionEngineEntry.name: csOrionEngineEntry
csOrionEngineEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular process engine.

csOrionEngineIndex.name: csOrionEngineIndex
csOrionEngineIndex.description: A unique value for each engine.

csOrionEngineMemorySize.name: csOrionEngineMemorySize
csOrionEngineMemorySize.description: The size of the memory for the specified Engine, in bytes. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionEngineMemoryUtil.name: csOrionEngineMemoryUtil
csOrionEngineMemoryUtil.description: The current percentage utilization of the memory for the specified Engine.

csOrionEngineType.name: csOrionEngineType
csOrionEngineType.description: A type of the process engine.

csOrionEngineDescr.name: csOrionEngineDescr
csOrionEngineDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the process engine manufacturer and the product name. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionEngineUtilization.name: csOrionEngineUtilization
csOrionEngineUtilization.description: A % utilization for the specified Engine.

csOrionEngineTemperature.name: csOrionEngineTemperature
csOrionEngineTemperature.description: A temperature (in Fahrenheit or Celsius near the specified Engine. NOTE: This object is not used.

csOrionEngineState.name: csOrionEngineState
csOrionEngineState.description: The current state of this engine.

csOrionEngineConfigAttributes.name: csOrionEngineConfigAttributes
csOrionEngineConfigAttributes.description: Contains the configured or static parameters of this engine. Each parameter is represented by a type-lenth-value data structure. A single TLV may contain individual TLVs. The types IDs currently supported are : 1 - Description (string) [sample only] more parameters will be added. NOTE: This object is deprecated and is replaced by individual objects starting from csOrionEngineLoaderProduct.

csOrionEngineOperAttributes.name: csOrionEngineOperAttributes
csOrionEngineOperAttributes.description: Contains the operational or dynamic parameters of this engine. Each parameter is represented by a type-lenth-value data structure. A single TLV may contain individual TLVs. The types IDs currently supported are : 1 - Description (string) [sample only] more parameters will be added. NOTE: This object is deprecated and is replaced by individual objects starting from csOrionEngineMemoryAllocs.

csOrionEngineLoaderProduct.name: csOrionEngineLoaderProduct
csOrionEngineLoaderProduct.description: A textual string containing information about the engine loader.

csOrionEngineLoaderVersion.name: csOrionEngineLoaderVersion
csOrionEngineLoaderVersion.description: A textual string containing information about the version of the loader.

csOrionEngineLoaderDate.name: csOrionEngineLoaderDate
csOrionEngineLoaderDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the loader.

csOrionEngineLoaderTime.name: csOrionEngineLoaderTime
csOrionEngineLoaderTime.description: A textual string containing information about the time of the loader.

csOrionEngineApplicationProduct.name: csOrionEngineApplicationProduct
csOrionEngineApplicationProduct.description: A textual string containing information about the application.

csOrionEngineApplicationVersion.name: csOrionEngineApplicationVersion
csOrionEngineApplicationVersion.description: A textual string containing information about the version of the application.

csOrionEngineApplicationDate.name: csOrionEngineApplicationDate
csOrionEngineApplicationDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the application.

csOrionEngineApplicationTime.name: csOrionEngineApplicationTime
csOrionEngineApplicationTime.description: A textual string containing information about the time of the application.

csOrionEngineSerialNumb.name: csOrionEngineSerialNumb
csOrionEngineSerialNumb.description: The serial number of the engine. This is a series of alphanumeric characters which uniquely identifies the engine on this blade.

csOrionEngineAssemblyNumb.name: csOrionEngineAssemblyNumb
csOrionEngineAssemblyNumb.description: The assembly number of the engine.

csOrionEngineCpuType.name: csOrionEngineCpuType
csOrionEngineCpuType.description: The type of cpu for the engine.

csOrionEngineCpuVersion.name: csOrionEngineCpuVersion
csOrionEngineCpuVersion.description: The CPU version of the engine.

csOrionEngineDataCacheSize.name: csOrionEngineDataCacheSize
csOrionEngineDataCacheSize.description: Data cache size of the engine.

csOrionEngineInstructionCacheSize.name: csOrionEngineInstructionCacheSize
csOrionEngineInstructionCacheSize.description: Instruction cache size of the engine.

csOrionEngineSecondaryCacheSize.name: csOrionEngineSecondaryCacheSize
csOrionEngineSecondaryCacheSize.description: Secondary cache size of the engine.

csOrionEngineLevel3CacheSize.name: csOrionEngineLevel3CacheSize
csOrionEngineLevel3CacheSize.description: Level 3 cache size of the engine.

csOrionEngineMemoryAllocFailures.name: csOrionEngineMemoryAllocFailures
csOrionEngineMemoryAllocFailures.description: Memory allocation failures for the engine.

csOrionEngineMemoryBadFrees.name: csOrionEngineMemoryBadFrees
csOrionEngineMemoryBadFrees.description: Memory free failures for the engine.

csOrionEngineLargestFreeMemory.name: csOrionEngineLargestFreeMemory
csOrionEngineLargestFreeMemory.description: Size of the largest free memory block for the engine.

csOrionEngineFreeMemoryMedium.name: csOrionEngineFreeMemoryMedium
csOrionEngineFreeMemoryMedium.description: Free memory, in 100 KByte unit, averaged over the last 30 seconds.

csOrionEngineFreeMemoryLong.name: csOrionEngineFreeMemoryLong
csOrionEngineFreeMemoryLong.description: Free memory, in 100 KByte unit, averaged over the last 10 minutes.

csOrionEngineUtilizationMedium.name: csOrionEngineUtilizationMedium
csOrionEngineUtilizationMedium.description: CPU utilization averaged over the last 30 seconds.

csOrionEngineUtilizationLong.name: csOrionEngineUtilizationLong
csOrionEngineUtilizationLong.description: CPU utilization averaged over the last 10 minutes.

csOrionEngineForwardingMode.name: csOrionEngineForwardingMode
csOrionEngineForwardingMode.description: Packet Forarding Mode for the Engine,HW Prefix,HW Flow,SW Passthrough

csOrionEngineOsVersion.name: csOrionEngineOsVersion
csOrionEngineOsVersion.description: The OS version of the engine/module.

csOrionQueueGroupTable.name: csOrionQueueGroupTable
csOrionQueueGroupTable.description: A list of group of queues found in every blade

csOrionQueueGroupEntry.name: csOrionQueueGroupEntry
csOrionQueueGroupEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular group of queue.

csOrionQueueGroupType.name: csOrionQueueGroupType
csOrionQueueGroupType.description: Indicates the type of queue group. 'systemQueue' is a group of queue used by the system as it sends out packets to the backplane. 'portQueue' is used by the the interface ports.

csOrionQueueGroupId.name: csOrionQueueGroupId
csOrionQueueGroupId.description: A unique id for each group of Queues. Currently (March 2001, for Release 3.0), there is only one group of queues to be shared by all ports/interfaces. And also one group of queues used to send out packets to the packet-ring. A future hardware version could come up with one group of queues per port, or multiple system queues. Our MIB model is ready for that.

csOrionQueueGroupPriorityIndex.name: csOrionQueueGroupPriorityIndex
csOrionQueueGroupPriorityIndex.description: A unique id for each group of priority of Queues. Currently (July 2001, for Release 3.0), there is only four priority groups. Priority Group 1, 2 and 3 have 100% and priority group 4 a group of 5 queues.

csOrionQueueGroupSubGroupAllocation.name: csOrionQueueGroupSubGroupAllocation
csOrionQueueGroupSubGroupAllocation.description: An action object used to set the weigth of all queues that belong to the same group priority. It starts with octet 1 for the first queue and octet n-1 for the last queue. Each value will be propagated to the parameter csOrionQueueWeight of a specific csOrionQueueEntry. That should be used for reading. Currently(rel.3.0), a single priority group can have only a maximum of 5 queues. And, sum of percentage of all the Queues must not exceed 100%

csOrionQueueGroupOperStatus.name: csOrionQueueGroupOperStatus
csOrionQueueGroupOperStatus.description: Indicates operational status of this queue group.

csOrionQueueGroupTableEnd.name: csOrionQueueGroupTableEnd
csOrionQueueGroupTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionQueueTable.name: csOrionQueueTable
csOrionQueueTable.description: A list of individual queues in every csOrionGroupQueueTable

csOrionQueueEntry.name: csOrionQueueEntry
csOrionQueueEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular queue.

csOrionQueueId.name: csOrionQueueId
csOrionQueueId.description: A unique id for each queue. Currently(rel.3.0), there are only 8 queues in every group.

csOrionQueueClassOfService.name: csOrionQueueClassOfService
csOrionQueueClassOfService.description: Identifies a class of service this queue is handling.

csOrionQueueWeight.name: csOrionQueueWeight
csOrionQueueWeight.description: Weight setting of this queue for scheduling expressed in percent. This can be modified along with other queues on the same priority group through the object csOrionQueueGroupPriorityAllocation.

csOrionQueueMinThresholdForRed.name: csOrionQueueMinThresholdForRed
csOrionQueueMinThresholdForRed.description: Min threshold to start discarding the red packet. Represented as the percentage of the queue size, 256KB.

csOrionQueueMinThresholdForYellow.name: csOrionQueueMinThresholdForYellow
csOrionQueueMinThresholdForYellow.description: Min threshold to start discarding the yellow packet. Represented as the percentage of the queue size, 256KB.

csOrionQueueMinThresholdForGreen.name: csOrionQueueMinThresholdForGreen
csOrionQueueMinThresholdForGreen.description: Min threshold to start discarding the green packet. Represented as the percentage of the queue size, 256KB.

csOrionQueueMaxRandomForRed.name: csOrionQueueMaxRandomForRed
csOrionQueueMaxRandomForRed.description: The max_random for red puts a cap on the random number generated by hardware Represented in .

csOrionQueueMaxRandomForYellow.name: csOrionQueueMaxRandomForYellow
csOrionQueueMaxRandomForYellow.description: The max_random for yellow puts a cap on the random number generated by hardware Represented in .

csOrionQueueMaxRandomForGreen.name: csOrionQueueMaxRandomForGreen
csOrionQueueMaxRandomForGreen.description: The max_random for green puts a cap on the random number generated by hardware Represented in .

csOrionQueueMaxThreshold.name: csOrionQueueMaxThreshold
csOrionQueueMaxThreshold.description: Max threshold to discarding packets (red, yellow and green). Represented as the percentage of the queue size, 256KB.

csOrionQueuePacketCount.name: csOrionQueuePacketCount
csOrionQueuePacketCount.description: Total number of packets counted so far.

csOrionQueueAverageSize.name: csOrionQueueAverageSize
csOrionQueueAverageSize.description: Average Queue Size at the present moment

csOrionBladeInfoEnd.name: csOrionBladeInfoEnd
csOrionBladeInfoEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionAccessListTable.name: csOrionAccessListTable
csOrionAccessListTable.description: A list of Access List Entries.

csOrionAccessListEntry.name: csOrionAccessListEntry
csOrionAccessListEntry.description: An entry containing filtering information used to classify packets.

csOrionAccessListId.name: csOrionAccessListId
csOrionAccessListId.description: An identifier for this Access List Entry.

csOrionAccessListPoolId.name: csOrionAccessListPoolId
csOrionAccessListPoolId.description: The NAT Pool that is used when NAT is performed on packets matching this access list.

csOrionAccessListStatus.name: csOrionAccessListStatus
csOrionAccessListStatus.description: This object is used to create/delete entries in this table.

csOrionGenAclTable.name: csOrionGenAclTable
csOrionGenAclTable.description: A list of Access List Entries. This is the table used by all the services (other than NAT) provided by Orion.

csOrionGenAclEntry.name: csOrionGenAclEntry
csOrionGenAclEntry.description: An entry containing filtering information used to classify packets.

csOrionGenAclId.name: csOrionGenAclId
csOrionGenAclId.description: An identifier for this Access List Entry.

csOrionGenAclProt.name: csOrionGenAclProt
csOrionGenAclProt.description: The Protocol ID that a packet must contain to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclTos.name: csOrionGenAclTos
csOrionGenAclTos.description: The Type of Service that a packet must contain to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclStartSrcPort.name: csOrionGenAclStartSrcPort
csOrionGenAclStartSrcPort.description: The beginning of a range of ports that a packet's source port must satisfy to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclEndSrcPort.name: csOrionGenAclEndSrcPort
csOrionGenAclEndSrcPort.description: The end of a range of ports that a packet's source port must satisfy to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclStartDstPort.name: csOrionGenAclStartDstPort
csOrionGenAclStartDstPort.description: The beginning of a range of ports that a packet's destination port must satisfy to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclEndDstPort.name: csOrionGenAclEndDstPort
csOrionGenAclEndDstPort.description: The end of a range of ports that a packet's destination port must satisfy to match this access list entry. The value -1 represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter.

csOrionGenAclStatus.name: csOrionGenAclStatus
csOrionGenAclStatus.description: This object is used to create/delete entries in this table.

csOrionGenAclSrcAddressList.name: csOrionGenAclSrcAddressList
csOrionGenAclSrcAddressList.description: The name of the address-list representing all source addresses For the GAL to be operational there should be at least one entry in the csOrionAddressListTable table with its csOrionAddressListName attribute being equal to the value of this attribute

csOrionGenAclDstAddressList.name: csOrionGenAclDstAddressList
csOrionGenAclDstAddressList.description: The name of the address-list representing all destination addresses For the GAL to be operational there should be at least one entry in the csOrionAddressListTable table with its csOrionAddressListName attribute being equal to the value of this attribute

csOrionGenAclSrcPortList.name: csOrionGenAclSrcPortList
csOrionGenAclSrcPortList.description: The name of the numeric-list representing all source ports. For the GAL to be operational there should be at least one entry in the csOrionNumericListTable table with its csOrionNumericListName attribute being equal to the value of this attribute.

csOrionGenAclDstPortList.name: csOrionGenAclDstPortList
csOrionGenAclDstPortList.description: The name of the numeric-list representing all source ports. An empty string represents a wildcard for this General Access List parameter. For the GAL to be operational there should be at least one entry in the csOrionNumericListTable table with its csOrionNumericListName attribute being equal to the value of this attribute.

csOrionGenAclTableEnd.name: csOrionGenAclTableEnd
csOrionGenAclTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionAddressListTable.name: csOrionAddressListTable
csOrionAddressListTable.description: This table stores named lists of IP addresses. An address is specified as an IP address and mask. Each table entry constitutes a single address.

csOrionAddressListEntry.name: csOrionAddressListEntry
csOrionAddressListEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a single address

csOrionAddressListName.name: csOrionAddressListName
csOrionAddressListName.description: The name of the address-list. A name shall only contain alphanumeric characters and hyphens.

csOrionAddressListIpAddress.name: csOrionAddressListIpAddress
csOrionAddressListIpAddress.description: The IP address for this entry.

csOrionAddressListRowStatus.name: csOrionAddressListRowStatus
csOrionAddressListRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add/delete rows from this table.

csOrionAddressListTableEnd.name: csOrionAddressListTableEnd
csOrionAddressListTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionNumericListTable.name: csOrionNumericListTable
csOrionNumericListTable.description: This table stores named lists of integers. A numeric-list is a named list that includes discreet integers or integer ranges. A numeric-list is typed: Initally a single type has been identified for using numeric-lists to represent port-lists.

csOrionNumericListEntry.name: csOrionNumericListEntry
csOrionNumericListEntry.description: Each entry specifies a single numeric specification: a discreet integer or a range of contiguous integers.

csOrionNumericListType.name: csOrionNumericListType
csOrionNumericListType.description: The match type for this entry: port: this numeric list represents a list of ports.

csOrionNumericListName.name: csOrionNumericListName
csOrionNumericListName.description: The name of the numeric-list. A name shall contain only alphanumeric characters and hyphens (-).

csOrionNumericListValue.name: csOrionNumericListValue
csOrionNumericListValue.description: The integer for this entry. This value shall always be used.

csOrionNumericListUpperLimit.name: csOrionNumericListUpperLimit
csOrionNumericListUpperLimit.description: The integer representing the upper boundary of a range. This attribute shall only be used when `includeRange'is specified in the csOrionNumericListMatchType attribute.

csOrionNumericListRowStatus.name: csOrionNumericListRowStatus
csOrionNumericListRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table. This is used to add/delete rows from this table.

csOrionAccessListInfoEnd.name: csOrionAccessListInfoEnd
csOrionAccessListInfoEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionFwInsideIfTable.name: csOrionFwInsideIfTable
csOrionFwInsideIfTable.description: This contains the list of all the interfaces on the inside, or trusted, side of the firewall. NOTE: This table is no longer in use.

csOrionFwInsideIfIf.name: csOrionFwInsideIfIf
csOrionFwInsideIfIf.description: The identifier of the 'inside' virtual interface.

csOrionFwInsideIfAddr.name: csOrionFwInsideIfAddr
csOrionFwInsideIfAddr.description: The Ip address of the 'inside' virtual interface.

csOrionFwInsideIfMask.name: csOrionFwInsideIfMask
csOrionFwInsideIfMask.description: The Ip Mask of the 'inside' virtual interface.

csOrionFwInsideIfRowStatus.name: csOrionFwInsideIfRowStatus
csOrionFwInsideIfRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table.

csOrionFwDmzIfTable.name: csOrionFwDmzIfTable
csOrionFwDmzIfTable.description: This contains the list of all the interfaces on the DmzIf side of the firewall. NOTE: This table is no longer in use.

csOrionFwDmzIf.name: csOrionFwDmzIf
csOrionFwDmzIf.description: The identifier of a 'Dmz' virtual interface.

csOrionFwDmzIfAddr.name: csOrionFwDmzIfAddr
csOrionFwDmzIfAddr.description: The Ip address of a 'Dmz' virtual interface.

csOrionFwDmzIfMask.name: csOrionFwDmzIfMask
csOrionFwDmzIfMask.description: The Ip Mask of a 'Dmz' virtual interface.

csOrionFwDmzIfRowStatus.name: csOrionFwDmzIfRowStatus
csOrionFwDmzIfRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table.

csOrionFwNwGroupTable.name: csOrionFwNwGroupTable
csOrionFwNwGroupTable.description: This contains definitions of all the network groups referred to in other parts of the Firewall configuration. NOTE: This table is no longer in use.

csOrionFwNwGroupName.name: csOrionFwNwGroupName
csOrionFwNwGroupName.description: The Name assigned to this Network Group.

csOrionFwNwGroupAddr.name: csOrionFwNwGroupAddr
csOrionFwNwGroupAddr.description: The Ip address of this member of this Network Group.

csOrionFwNwGroupMask.name: csOrionFwNwGroupMask
csOrionFwNwGroupMask.description: The Ip Mask assigned to this member of this Network Group.

csOrionFwNwGroupInterface.name: csOrionFwNwGroupInterface
csOrionFwNwGroupInterface.description: The Interface from which this member of this Network Group can be reached.

csOrionFwNwGroupRowStatus.name: csOrionFwNwGroupRowStatus
csOrionFwNwGroupRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this table.

csOrionFwEvLogTable.name: csOrionFwEvLogTable
csOrionFwEvLogTable.description: A table for Event Logging Control for FIREWALL.

csOrionFwEvLogEntry.name: csOrionFwEvLogEntry
csOrionFwEvLogEntry.description: Each entry contains the event logging level for the FIREWALL module on a virtual router.

csOrionFwEvLogLevel.name: csOrionFwEvLogLevel
csOrionFwEvLogLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of details for event logs for FIREWALL.

csOrionFwGenCfgTable.name: csOrionFwGenCfgTable
csOrionFwGenCfgTable.description: A table for Configuration Control for FIREWALL.

csOrionFwGenCfgEntry.name: csOrionFwGenCfgEntry
csOrionFwGenCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains the generic configuration for the FIREWALL module on a virtual router.

csOrionFwAccCfgFlag.name: csOrionFwAccCfgFlag
csOrionFwAccCfgFlag.description: This object is used to set the access configuration flag for FIREWALL.

csOrionFwGenProxyTable.name: csOrionFwGenProxyTable
csOrionFwGenProxyTable.description: This table specifies various configuration parameters for each applicable proxy.

csOrionFwGenProxyEntry.name: csOrionFwGenProxyEntry
csOrionFwGenProxyEntry.description: Each entry specifies a set of configuration parameters for a single proxy.

csOrionFwGenProxyId.name: csOrionFwGenProxyId
csOrionFwGenProxyId.description: The proxy to which this entry applies.

csOrionFwGenProxyChildLimit.name: csOrionFwGenProxyChildLimit
csOrionFwGenProxyChildLimit.description: The maximum number of child processes that each of this proxy's daemon allows to run at a given time. If this option is set to zero, each daemon allows an unlimited number of child processes to run at any given time. Note, this is not applicable to the smtp proxy.

csOrionFwGenProxyStatus.name: csOrionFwGenProxyStatus
csOrionFwGenProxyStatus.description: This is used to enable/disable a specific proxy.

csOrionFwGenProxyActiveSessions.name: csOrionFwGenProxyActiveSessions

csOrionFwSmtpPolicyLogRelay.description: Indicates if normal or no logging is to be done.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTable.description: A table for IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapEntry.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapEntry
csOrionIKECryptoMapEntry.description: Each entry contains a specific set of IKE Crypto Map for use by a Security Association.

csOrionIKECryptoMapName.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapName
csOrionIKECryptoMapName.description: An index for the IKE Crypto Map Table.

csOrionIKECryptoMapNumber.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapNumber
csOrionIKECryptoMapNumber.description: An index for the IKE Crypto Map Table.

csOrionIKECryptoMapFlag.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapFlag
csOrionIKECryptoMapFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables a specific feature within the Crypto Map. Below is a list of the features and their corresponding bits identifiers. feature bit ------------------------------------------------------ pfs 0 pfs-identify 1 sa-per-net 5 -- note, sa-per-host & sa-per-net sa-per-host 6 -- are mutually exclusive sa-per-protocol 7 sa-per-port 8 main-mode 10 -- main-mode and aggressive-mode aggressive-mode 11 -- are mutually exclusive copy-df 21 dont-verify-padding 22 always-plain 29 passby 30 deny 31 end of description. NOTE: default value varies depending on csOrionIKECryptoMapType. 'isakmp' - default is 1056 (0x420 main-mode and sa-per-net) 'isakmpDialup' - default is 1088 (0x440 main-mode and sa-per-host).

csOrionIKECryptoMapMatchAddress.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapMatchAddress
csOrionIKECryptoMapMatchAddress.description: Access List ID used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapPfsGroup.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapPfsGroup
csOrionIKECryptoMapPfsGroup.description: If one of the pfs features is enabled in csOrionIKECryptoMapFlags, this object is used to identify the Diffie-Helman group used for this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet1.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet1
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet1.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet2.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet2
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet2.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet3.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet3
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet3.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet4.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet4
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet4.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet5.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet5
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet5.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet6.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet6
csOrionIKECryptoMapTransformSet6.description: A transform set used by this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapPolicy.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapPolicy
csOrionIKECryptoMapPolicy.description: The IKE Policy used by this Crypto Map. This references an entry in csOrionIKEPolicyTable.

csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentity.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentity
csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentity.description: The Local IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format).

csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftSec.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftSec
csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftSec.description: The soft rekey interval lifetime in seconds used by this IKE Crypto Map Entry. This defines the period of time that elapses between ISAKMP phase II rekeys. This object is deprecated because its value is derived from csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardSec and is really not negotiated.

csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftKbytes.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftKbytes
csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeSoftKbytes.description: The soft rekey interval lifetime in kilobytes used by this IKE Crypto Map Entry. This defines the maximum amount of data transferred between ISAKMP phase II rekeys. This object is deprecated because its value is derived from csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardKbytes and is really not negotiated.

csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardSec.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardSec
csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardSec.description: The number of seconds that elapse before the SA is completely deleted. If this occurs on an active connection, a new ISAKMP negotiation starting at phase I takes place and a new SA is initiated. 0 is a special value and indicates that this particular Lifetime parameter is not to be conveyed to the remote side in any proposal that might be sent.

csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardKbytes.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardKbytes
csOrionIKECryptoMapSaLifetimeHardKbytes.description: The number of kilobytes transferred before the SA is completely deleted. 0 is a special value and indicates that this particular Lifetime parameter is not to be conveyed to the remote side in any proposal that might be sent.

csOrionIKECryptoMapStatus.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapStatus
csOrionIKECryptoMapStatus.description: A row status type for the IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKECryptoMapType.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapType
csOrionIKECryptoMapType.description: This object indicates if this IKE Crytomap is used as a regular crytomap or for dial-up. Its value is only set during creation. Therefore, it must not be modified once created.

csOrionIKECryptoMapIdleTimeout.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapIdleTimeout
csOrionIKECryptoMapIdleTimeout.description: The idle timeout in seconds of the dialup connection. This will be used only when the csOrionIKECryptoMapType is 'isakmpDialup' otherwise its value is zero. Setting this object to 0 will turn the timer off. The minimum valid timeout value for a dialup connection is 60, i.e., 1 minute.

csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentityType.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentityType
csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentityType.description: The Local IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapLocalIdentity.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity1.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity1
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity1.description: The remote IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format). In the case of IP address, the format is 'a.b.c.d/w.x.y.z', where a.b.c.d is the ip address and w.x.y.z is the address mask. If address mask is not specified, it is assumed to be 255.255.255.255. This is used by IKE to differentiate the remote end so as to determine which crypto map with the unique map priority is to be used. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType1.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity2.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity2
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity2.description: The remote IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format). In the case of IP address, the format is 'a.b.c.d/w.x.y.z', where a.b.c.d is the ip address and w.x.y.z is the address mask. If address mask is not specified, it is assumed to be 255.255.255.255. This is used by IKE to differentiate the remote end so as to determine which crypto map with the unique map priority is to be used. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType2.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity3.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity3
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity3.description: The remote IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format). In the case of IP address, the format is 'a.b.c.d/w.x.y.z', where a.b.c.d is the ip address and w.x.y.z is the address mask. If address mask is not specified, it is assumed to be 255.255.255.255. This is used by IKE to differentiate the remote end so as to determine which crypto map with the unique map priority is to be used. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType3.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity4.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity4
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity4.description: The remote IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format). In the case of IP address, the format is 'a.b.c.d/w.x.y.z', where a.b.c.d is the ip address and w.x.y.z is the address mask. If address mask is not specified, it is assumed to be 255.255.255.255. This is used by IKE to differentiate the remote end so as to determine which crypto map with the unique map priority is to be used. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType4.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity5.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity5
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity5.description: The remote IKE Identity for this Crypto Map entry. This can be either a hostname or an IP address (in dotted decimal format). In the case of IP address, the format is 'a.b.c.d/w.x.y.z', where a.b.c.d is the ip address and w.x.y.z is the address mask. If address mask is not specified, it is assumed to be 255.255.255.255. This is used by IKE to differentiate the remote end so as to determine which crypto map with the unique map priority is to be used. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType5.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType1.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType1
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType1.description: The remote IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity1.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType2.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType2
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType2.description: The remote IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity2.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType3.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType3
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType3.description: The remote IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity3.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType4.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType4
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType4.description: The remote IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity4.

csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType5.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType5
csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentityType5.description: The remote IKE Identity type for this Crypto Map entry. This has to be set together with csOrionIKECryptoMapRemoteIdentity5.

csOrionIKECryptoMapAddressPool.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapAddressPool
csOrionIKECryptoMapAddressPool.description: This specifies whether IP address assignment is necessary for the remote dialup host and, if it is, how to obtain the address assignment. The following string values can be set: 'NONE' - means IP address assignment is not required for the remote dialup host 'AAA' - means the IP address is to be requested from an authentication or authorization server for the remote private IP address assignment - use the IP address in this address pool for the remote private IP address assignment; this name corresponds to csOrionIpLocalAddrPoolName, so the corresponding entry in csOrionIpLocalAddrPoolTable must have already existed. Applicable to ipsec-dialup crypto map only.

csOrionIKECryptoMapDynamicRouteAdd.name: csOrionIKECryptoMapDynamicRouteAdd
csOrionIKECryptoMapDynamicRouteAdd.description: If this object is set to true, IKE will dynamically load a static route when an SA is loaded. This static route will be used to route outgoing data packets to the tunnel VI for encryption to be sent to the remote ISDN network branches. IKE will also delete the route when the ISDN network SA pair is deleted. Note: This is implemented specifically for an ISDN network dialup. For the isakmp site-to-site tunnel, regular dialup tunnel and DSL dialup tunnel configurations, static routes for routing data packets to tunnel VI must be created manually instead of using this dynamic route addition capability, since this will degrade the IKE performance significantly, especially for regular and DSL dialup cases.

csOrionIKEPolicyTable.name: csOrionIKEPolicyTable
csOrionIKEPolicyTable.description: A table for IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKEPolicyEntry.name: csOrionIKEPolicyEntry
csOrionIKEPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains a specific set of IKE Crypto Map for use by a Security Association.

csOrionIKEPolicyName.name: csOrionIKEPolicyName
csOrionIKEPolicyName.description: The name assigned to this set of IKE Policies.

csOrionIKEPolicyPriority.name: csOrionIKEPolicyPriority
csOrionIKEPolicyPriority.description: The priority assigned to this IKE Policy Entry.

csOrionIKEPolicyHash.name: csOrionIKEPolicyHash
csOrionIKEPolicyHash.description: The Hash algorithm employed by this IKE Policy Entry.

csOrionIKEPolicyEncryption.name: csOrionIKEPolicyEncryption
csOrionIKEPolicyEncryption.description: The Encryption algorithm employed by this IKE Policy Entry.

csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeSoftSec.description: The soft rekey interval lifetime in seconds used by this IKE Crypto Map Entry. This defines the period of time that elapses between ISAKMP phase II rekeys. This object is deprecated because its value is derived from csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardSec and is really not negotiated.

This defines the maximum amount of data transferred between ISAKMP phase II rekeys. This object is deprecated because its value is derived from csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardKbytes and is really not negotiated.

csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardSec.name: csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardSec
csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardSec.description: The number of seconds that elapse before the SA is completely deleted. If this occurs on an active connection, a new ISAKMP negotiation starting at phase I takes place and a new SA is initiated. 0 is a special value and indicates that this particular Lifetime parameter is not to be conveyed to the remote side in any proposal that might be sent.

csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardKbytes.name: csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardKbytes
csOrionIKEPolicySaLifetimeHardKbytes.description: The number of kilobytes transferred before the SA is completely deleted. 0 is a special value and indicates that this particular Lifetime parameter is not to be conveyed to the remote side in any proposal that might be sent.

csOrionIKEPolicyAuthentication.name: csOrionIKEPolicyAuthentication
csOrionIKEPolicyAuthentication.description: The Authentication algorithm employed by this Policy entry.

csOrionIKEPolicyPfsGroup.name: csOrionIKEPolicyPfsGroup
csOrionIKEPolicyPfsGroup.description: If one of the pfs features is enabled in csOrionIKECryptoMapFlags, this object is used to identify the Diffie-Helman group used for this IKE Crypto Map.

csOrionIKEPolicyStatus.name: csOrionIKEPolicyStatus
csOrionIKEPolicyStatus.description: A row status type for the IKE Policy Entry.

csOrionIKEPolicyAuthorizationTypeFlag.name: csOrionIKEPolicyAuthorizationTypeFlag
csOrionIKEPolicyAuthorizationTypeFlag.description: Each bit within this object specifies the type of authorization to be enabled for IKE phase 1. options bit ------------------------------------------------------ certificate-presence 0 user-exists 1 enterprise-ID 2

csOrionIKECertEntry.name: csOrionIKECertEntry
csOrionIKECertEntry.description: Each entry contains a specific certificate.

csOrionIKECertName.name: csOrionIKECertName
csOrionIKECertName.description: The name assigned to this set of IKE Certificates.

csOrionIKECertMapName.name: csOrionIKECertMapName
csOrionIKECertMapName.description: The IKE Crypto Map referred to by this Cert entry.

csOrionIKECertFlag.name: csOrionIKECertFlag
csOrionIKECertFlag.description: Each bit within this object enables a specific feature within the Cert Table. Below is a list of the features and their corresponding bits identifiers. feature bit ------------------------------------------------------ no-crl 0 (more descriptions will follow).

csOrionIKECertStatus.name: csOrionIKECertStatus
csOrionIKECertStatus.description: A row status type for the IKE Cert Entry.

csOrionIKESvrParamTable.name: csOrionIKESvrParamTable
csOrionIKESvrParamTable.description: A table of IKE Server Parameters in every VR.

csOrionIKESvrParamEntry.name: csOrionIKESvrParamEntry
csOrionIKESvrParamEntry.description: Each entry contains parameter settings of an IKE server.

csOrionIKESvrParamMapName.name: csOrionIKESvrParamMapName
csOrionIKESvrParamMapName.description: The map name for this server.

csOrionIKESvrParamFlag.name: csOrionIKESvrParamFlag
csOrionIKESvrParamFlag.description: Each bit within this object specifies the compatibility options that the server uses by default. Below is a list of the features and their corresponding bits identifiers. options bit ------------------------------------------------------ old-pk-encryption-prf-key 0 old-payload-padding 1 old-message-padding 2 old-da-padding 3 old-id-in-hash 4 ignore-cert-request-payload 5 old-cr-format 6 use-zero-spi 7 End of description.

csOrionIKESvrParamIpAddress.name: csOrionIKESvrParamIpAddress
csOrionIKESvrParamIpAddress.description: The address of the IKE server.

csOrionIKESvrParamPort.name: csOrionIKESvrParamPort
csOrionIKESvrParamPort.description: The UDP port that the server is listening to.

csOrionIKESvrParamRetryLimit.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRetryLimit
csOrionIKESvrParamRetryLimit.description: Limits the number of ISAKMP packet transmission retries. The server retries the transmission if it does not receive a response in csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimer seconds.

csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimer.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimer
csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimer.description: The amount of time, in seconds, that the server gives the remote end to reply to the sent request, before it will send the packet again. Fraction of a second must be specified in csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimerMicroSec.

csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimerMaximum.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimerMaximum
csOrionIKESvrParamRetryTimerMaximum.description: Specifies the maximum value, in seconds, for the retry timer.

csOrionIKESvrParamExpireTimer.name: csOrionIKESvrParamExpireTimer
csOrionIKESvrParamExpireTimer.description: Specifies the maximum time, in seconds, that the IKE server allows a negotiation to continue.

csOrionIKESvrParamSecretRecreate.name: csOrionIKESvrParamSecretRecreate
csOrionIKESvrParamSecretRecreate.description: A local secret recreation timer expressed in seconds.

csOrionIKESvrParamSPISize.name: csOrionIKESvrParamSPISize
csOrionIKESvrParamSPISize.description: A compatibility flag that specifies the number of bytes of zero that can be used when the security parameter index (SPI) of an ISAKMP security association is sent to the remote end.

csOrionIKESvrParamMaxKeyLength.name: csOrionIKESvrParamMaxKeyLength
csOrionIKESvrParamMaxKeyLength.description: The maximum length of an encryption key, specified in bytes, that is accepted by the local end.

csOrionIKESvrParamMaxSACount.name: csOrionIKESvrParamMaxSACount
csOrionIKESvrParamMaxSACount.description: Limits the maximum number of ISAKMP SA entries.

csOrionIKESvrParamLocalSecretSize.name: csOrionIKESvrParamLocalSecretSize
csOrionIKESvrParamLocalSecretSize.description: The length of the local secrets, specified in bits.

csOrionIKESvrParamTokenHashType.name: csOrionIKESvrParamTokenHashType
csOrionIKESvrParamTokenHashType.description: A reference to an algorithm configuration block that defines the anti-clogging token hash algorithm.

csOrionIKESvrParamRowStatus.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRowStatus
csOrionIKESvrParamRowStatus.description: A row status type for the IKE Server.

csOrionIKESvrParamAuthenticationList.name: csOrionIKESvrParamAuthenticationList
csOrionIKESvrParamAuthenticationList.description: The name of the authentication server list that IKE uses for authentication services. If no listname is provided, the default authentication list of this VR will be used.

csOrionIKESvrParamAuthorizationList.name: csOrionIKESvrParamAuthorizationList
csOrionIKESvrParamAuthorizationList.description: The name of the authorization server list that IKE uses for authorization services. If no listname is provided, the default authorization list of this VR will be used.

csOrionIKESvrParamAccountingList.name: csOrionIKESvrParamAccountingList
csOrionIKESvrParamAccountingList.description: The name of the accounting server list that IKE uses for accounting services. If no listname is provided, the default accounting list of this VR will be used.

csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority1
csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.description: Specifies the preferred user information to include in the RADIUS Accounting-Request User-Name attribute. Choices are: xauthUserId - xauth user login ID subjectAltName - subject alternative name from certificate distinguishedName - DN from certificate If the selected information is not available, IKE will try the type specified in csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority2.

csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority2
csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.description: Specifies the user information to include in the RADIUS Accounting-Request User-Name attribute if the type specified in csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority1 is not available: xauthUserId - xauth user login ID subjectAltName - subject alternative name from certificate distinguishedName - DN from certificate If the selected information is not available, IKE will try the type specified in csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority3.

csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.name: csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority3
csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePrio.description: Specifies the user information to include in the RADIUS Accounting-Request User-Name attribute if neither types specified in csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority1 and csOrionIKESvrParamRadiusAcctUserTypePriority2 are available: xauthUserId - xauth user login ID subjectAltName - subject alternative name from certificate distinguishedName - DN from certificate If the selected information is not available, IKE will include the assigned IP address in the user-name attribute.

csOrionIpSecEvLogTable.name: csOrionIpSecEvLogTable
csOrionIpSecEvLogTable.description: A table for Event Logging Control for IPSEC/IKE. NOTE: this table has been moved to {csOrionEncryptInfo 13} since it should be under VI level instead of VR level.

csOrionIpSecEvLogEntry.name: csOrionIpSecEvLogEntry
csOrionIpSecEvLogEntry.description: Each entry contains the event logging level and area for the IPSEC/IKE module on a virtual router.

csOrionIpSecStatsAhCurrentOutboundSAs.name: csOrionIpSecStatsAhCurrentOutboundSAs

csOrionIpSecStatsEspCryptoCepEstablishOk.description: The number of crypto ceps that are ESP encrypted sucessfully established in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIpSecStatsEspCryptoCepEstablishFa.description: The number of crypto ceps that are ESP encrypted failed to establish in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIpSecStatsAhCryptoCepEstablishOk.name: csOrionIpSecStatsAhCryptoCepEstablishOk

csOrionIpSecStatsAhCryptoCepEstablishFai.description: The number of crypto ceps that are AH encrypted failed to establish in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIpSecStatsEspDecryptPktsOk.name: csOrionIpSecStatsEspDecryptPktsOk

csOrionIpSecStatsAhEncryptPktsOk.name: csOrionIpSecStatsAhEncryptPktsOk

csOrionIpSecStatsAhDecryptPktsOk.name: csOrionIpSecStatsAhDecryptPktsOk
csOrionIpSecStatsAhDecryptPktsOk.description: The number of good AH decrypted packets in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIpSecStatsAhDecryptPktsBad.description: The number of bad AH decrypted packets in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsEntry.name: csOrionIKEStatsEntry
csOrionIKEStatsEntry.description: An entry containing IKE statistics information for this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase1Negotiations.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase1Negotiations
csOrionIKEStatsPhase1Negotiations.description: The number of IKE phase 1 negotiations in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase1NegotiationsFailed.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase1NegotiationsFailed
csOrionIKEStatsPhase1NegotiationsFailed.description: The number of Failed IKE phase 1 negotiations in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPkts.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPkts
csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPkts.description: The number of IKE phase 1 packets received in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPktsRejected.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPktsRejected
csOrionIKEStatsPhase1InPktsRejected.description: The number of rejected IKE phase 1 packets received in this Virtual Interface.
