csOrionIKEStatsPhase1OutPkts.description: The number of IKE phase 1 packets transmitted this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase2Negotiations.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase2Negotiations
csOrionIKEStatsPhase2Negotiations.description: The number of IKE phase 2 negotiations in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase2NegotiationsFailed.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase2NegotiationsFailed
csOrionIKEStatsPhase2NegotiationsFailed.description: The number of Failed IKE phase 2 negotiations in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPkts.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPkts
csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPkts.description: The number of IKE phase 2 packets received in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPktsRejected.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPktsRejected
csOrionIKEStatsPhase2InPktsRejected.description: The number of rejected IKE phase 2 packets received in this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStatsPhase2OutPkts.name: csOrionIKEStatsPhase2OutPkts
csOrionIKEStatsPhase2OutPkts.description: The number of IKE phase 2 packets transmitted this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStateEntry.name: csOrionIKEStateEntry
csOrionIKEStateEntry.description: An entry containing IKE state information for this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIKEStateSAIndex.name: csOrionIKEStateSAIndex
csOrionIKEStateSAIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA.

csOrionIKEStateLocalAddress.name: csOrionIKEStateLocalAddress
csOrionIKEStateLocalAddress.description: The local IP address of this SA.

csOrionIKEStateRemoteAddress.name: csOrionIKEStateRemoteAddress
csOrionIKEStateRemoteAddress.description: The remote IP address of this SA.

csOrionIKEStateInitRespondFlag.name: csOrionIKEStateInitRespondFlag
csOrionIKEStateInitRespondFlag.description: Indicates if this SA is an initiator or a responder.

csOrionIKEStateAuthenticationType.name: csOrionIKEStateAuthenticationType
csOrionIKEStateAuthenticationType.description: The authentication type of this SA. It could be a certificate or a pre-shared key.

csOrionIKEStateCreationTime.name: csOrionIKEStateCreationTime
csOrionIKEStateCreationTime.description: The creation time of this SA.

csOrionIKEStateExpirationTime.name: csOrionIKEStateExpirationTime
csOrionIKEStateExpirationTime.description: The expiration time of this SA.

csOrionIKEStateNegotiations.name: csOrionIKEStateNegotiations
csOrionIKEStateNegotiations.description: The number of phase 1 ISAKMP/IKE negotiations for this SA.

csOrionIKEStateLastUsed.name: csOrionIKEStateLastUsed
csOrionIKEStateLastUsed.description: The last time this SA was used.

csOrionIKEStateBytesTransferred.name: csOrionIKEStateBytesTransferred
csOrionIKEStateBytesTransferred.description: The number of bytes transferred by this SA.

csOrionIKEStateCryptoAlgorithm.name: csOrionIKEStateCryptoAlgorithm
csOrionIKEStateCryptoAlgorithm.description: The name of the crypto algorithm for this SA.

csOrionIKEStateHashAlgorithm.name: csOrionIKEStateHashAlgorithm
csOrionIKEStateHashAlgorithm.description: The name of the hash algorithm for this SA.

csOrionIKEStatePrfAlgorithm.name: csOrionIKEStatePrfAlgorithm
csOrionIKEStatePrfAlgorithm.description: The name of the PRF algorithm for this SA.

csOrionIKEStateRetryLimit.name: csOrionIKEStateRetryLimit
csOrionIKEStateRetryLimit.description: The limit of retry counts for this SA.

csOrionIKEStateRetryTimer.name: csOrionIKEStateRetryTimer
csOrionIKEStateRetryTimer.description: The retry interval in seconds. It indicates the duration from one retry to next retry for this SA. Fraction of a second must be specified in csOrionIKEStateRetryTimerMicroSec.

csOrionIKEStateMaxRetryDuration.name: csOrionIKEStateMaxRetryDuration
csOrionIKEStateMaxRetryDuration.description: The maximum total retry duration for this SA. Fraction of a second must be specified in csOrionIKEStateMaxRetryDurationMicroSec.

csOrionIKEDialupConnTable.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnTable
csOrionIKEDialupConnTable.description: A table of IKE dialup connection table.

csOrionIKEDialupConnEntry.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnEntry
csOrionIKEDialupConnEntry.description: Each entry contains a specific IKE dialup connection.

csOrionIKEDialupConnIndex.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnIndex
csOrionIKEDialupConnIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the IKE dialup connection table.

csOrionIKEDialupConnRemIpAddress.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnRemIpAddress
csOrionIKEDialupConnRemIpAddress.description: IP address of the remote IpSec tunnel.

csOrionIKEDialupConnUserId.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnUserId
csOrionIKEDialupConnUserId.description: Login ID of the dialup user, if the user uses Xauth. If Xauth is skipped, this will be an empty string.

csOrionIKEDialupConnDistinguishName.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnDistinguishName
csOrionIKEDialupConnDistinguishName.description: X.509 Distinguish Name of the dialup user, if the user uses certificates. For connection that does not use certificate, this will be an empty string.

csOrionIKEDialupConnRowStatus.name: csOrionIKEDialupConnRowStatus
csOrionIKEDialupConnRowStatus.description: This object allows for deletion of a connection if it is set to 'destroy'. 'active' is not a valid value to set. Get on this object will always yield 'active'.

csOrionIpSecStateEntry.name: csOrionIpSecStateEntry
csOrionIpSecStateEntry.description: An entry containing IPSEC state information for this Virtual Interface.

csOrionIpSecStateSAIndex.name: csOrionIpSecStateSAIndex
csOrionIpSecStateSAIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA.

csOrionIpSecStateSpi.name: csOrionIpSecStateSpi
csOrionIpSecStateSpi.description: The SPI is an arbitray 32-bit value that, in combintation with the destination IP address and security protocol(AH), uniquely identified the Security Association for this datagram.

csOrionIpSecStateSAFlag.name: csOrionIpSecStateSAFlag
csOrionIpSecStateSAFlag.description: A flag Containing info regarding this SA. The value of the flag is the combination of the following values: tunnel-only (1), transport-only (2), esp-rfc1827 (8), ah-rfc1826 (16), esp-rfc2045 (32), ah-rfc1828 (64), ah-rfc2202 (128) Giving an example: the value 33 represents tunnel + esp-rfc2045

csOrionIpSecStateProtocol.name: csOrionIpSecStateProtocol
csOrionIpSecStateProtocol.description: The protocol being used by this SA. This value is connected to General Access list protocol.

csOrionIpSecStatePort.name: csOrionIpSecStatePort
csOrionIpSecStatePort.description: The port number of the protocol; this value is connected to General Access list port number.

csOrionIpSecStateCreatorType.name: csOrionIpSecStateCreatorType
csOrionIpSecStateCreatorType.description: The creator type of this SA.

csOrionIpSecStateRemoteGateway.name: csOrionIpSecStateRemoteGateway
csOrionIpSecStateRemoteGateway.description: The IP address of remote gateway.

csOrionIpSecStateLocalGateway.name: csOrionIpSecStateLocalGateway
csOrionIpSecStateLocalGateway.description: The IP address of local gateway.

csOrionIpSecStateRemoteEndPoint.name: csOrionIpSecStateRemoteEndPoint
csOrionIpSecStateRemoteEndPoint.description: The IP address of remote end point.

csOrionIpSecStateLocalEndPoint.name: csOrionIpSecStateLocalEndPoint
csOrionIpSecStateLocalEndPoint.description: The IP address of local end point.

csOrionIpSecStateAlgorithmType.name: csOrionIpSecStateAlgorithmType
csOrionIpSecStateAlgorithmType.description: The algorithm type of this SA.

csOrionIpSecStateExpire.name: csOrionIpSecStateExpire
csOrionIpSecStateExpire.description: Indicate when this SA will be dropped.

csOrionIpSecStateLastUsed.name: csOrionIpSecStateLastUsed
csOrionIpSecStateLastUsed.description: The last time this SA was used.

csOrionIpSecStateDirection.name: csOrionIpSecStateDirection
csOrionIpSecStateDirection.description: The sending and receiving direction of this SA.

csOrionIpSecStateEncryptionAlgorithm.name: csOrionIpSecStateEncryptionAlgorithm
csOrionIpSecStateEncryptionAlgorithm.description: The name of the encryption algorithm for this SA.

csOrionIpSecStateHashAlgorithm.name: csOrionIpSecStateHashAlgorithm
csOrionIpSecStateHashAlgorithm.description: The name of the hash algorithm for this SA.

csOrionIpSecEventLogTable.name: csOrionIpSecEventLogTable
csOrionIpSecEventLogTable.description: A table for Event Logging Control for IPSEC/IKE.

csOrionIpSecEventLogEntry.name: csOrionIpSecEventLogEntry
csOrionIpSecEventLogEntry.description: Each entry contains the event logging level and area for the IPSEC/IKE module on a virtual router.

csOrionIpSecEventLogLevel.name: csOrionIpSecEventLogLevel
csOrionIpSecEventLogLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of details for event logs for IPSEC/IKE.

csOrionIpSecEventLogArea.name: csOrionIpSecEventLogArea
csOrionIpSecEventLogArea.description: This object is used to set the area of event logs for IPSEC/IKE.

csOrionEncryptInfoEnd.name: csOrionEncryptInfoEnd
csOrionEncryptInfoEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionVrNbnsConfigTable.name: csOrionVrNbnsConfigTable
csOrionVrNbnsConfigTable.description: This table contains NBNS configuration parameters.

csOrionVrNbnsConfigEntry.name: csOrionVrNbnsConfigEntry
csOrionVrNbnsConfigEntry.description: Each entry represents the NBNS configuration parameters for a single VR.

csOrionVrPrimaryNbnsServer.name: csOrionVrPrimaryNbnsServer
csOrionVrPrimaryNbnsServer.description: The primary NBNS server for this VR.

csOrionVrSecondaryNbnsServer.name: csOrionVrSecondaryNbnsServer
csOrionVrSecondaryNbnsServer.description: The secondary NBNS server for this VR.

csOrionNBNSInfoEnd.name: csOrionNBNSInfoEnd
csOrionNBNSInfoEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionAAAServerConfigTable.name: csOrionAAAServerConfigTable
csOrionAAAServerConfigTable.description: This table contains AAA server configuration parameters.

csOrionAAAServerConfigEntry.name: csOrionAAAServerConfigEntry
csOrionAAAServerConfigEntry.description: Each entry represents the configuration parameters for a single AAA server in this VR.

csOrionAAAServerName.name: csOrionAAAServerName
csOrionAAAServerName.description: Name given for this AAA server. Name has to be unique regardless of csOrionAAAServerType.

csOrionAAAServerPort.name: csOrionAAAServerPort
csOrionAAAServerPort.description: Port on which this AAA server is listening for messages. Radius client uses the default port 1812 for AA requests. Ldap client uses the default port 389 for AA requests. For rows where csAAAServerType is local, this object has no meaning.

csOrionAAAServerRetransmit.name: csOrionAAAServerRetransmit
csOrionAAAServerRetransmit.description: The number of times a AAA Server will be queried before moving to the next AAA Server in the list identified by csOrionAAAServerList. This object cannot be set for LDAP server, which is subject to TCP retransmission constraint and cannot be modified. TCP retries 12 times; the first timeout is 1.5 seconds, the subsequent retry timeout is twice as the previous one but no more than 64 seconds.

csOrionAAAServerTimeout.name: csOrionAAAServerTimeout
csOrionAAAServerTimeout.description: The amount of time (in seconds) to wait for a response from this AAA Server before timing out. This object cannot be set for LDAP server, which is subject to TCP timeout constraint and cannot be modified. TCP retries 12 times; the first timeout is 1.5 seconds, the subsequent retry timeout is twice as the previous one but no more than 64 seconds.

csOrionAAAServerRadiusKey.name: csOrionAAAServerRadiusKey
csOrionAAAServerRadiusKey.description: The authentication and encryption key shared between the Radius client and this Radius Server. Applicable only if the server is of radius type.

csOrionAAAServerLdapUsername.name: csOrionAAAServerLdapUsername
csOrionAAAServerLdapUsername.description: Distinguished Name of the LDAP user. Applicable only if the server is of ldap type.

csOrionAAAServerLdapPassword.name: csOrionAAAServerLdapPassword
csOrionAAAServerLdapPassword.description: Password of the LDAP user. Applicable only if the server is of ldap type.

csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchBase.name: csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchBase
csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchBase.description: Starting point in the directory hierarchy to perform search operations. Applicable only if the server is of ldap type.

csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchFilter.name: csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchFilter
csOrionAAAServerLdapSearchFilter.description: A filter that defines the conditions that must be fulfilled in order for the search to match a given entry. This must conform to RFC 2254 LDAP Search Filter String Representation. Applicable only if the server is of ldap type.

csOrionAAAServerRowStatus.name: csOrionAAAServerRowStatus
csOrionAAAServerRowStatus.description: Used to create a row (createAndGo) or destroy a row. Once the row is created, get on this object will always yield active(1).

csOrionAAAServerConfigTableEnd.name: csOrionAAAServerConfigTableEnd
csOrionAAAServerConfigTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionAAAServerListConfigTable.name: csOrionAAAServerListConfigTable
csOrionAAAServerListConfigTable.description: This table contains AAA server list configuration parameters. An AAA server list is a prioritized collection of AAA servers as defined in csOrionAAAServerConfigTable.

csOrionAAAServerListConfigEntry.name: csOrionAAAServerListConfigEntry
csOrionAAAServerListConfigEntry.description: Each entry points to a single AAA server as defined in csOrionAAAServerConfigTable. This server has a unique priority within the list.

csOrionAAAServerListType.name: csOrionAAAServerListType
csOrionAAAServerListType.description: This object defines the kind of AAA servers that are contained in this list. If this object has a value of authentication(1), then all servers in this list are to be used for authentication purposes. If the server is of radius type, then it is also used for authorization. If this object has a value of authorization(2), then all servers in this list are to be used for authorization purposes. Note that only ldap servers can be added to this list. If this object has a value of accounting(4), then all servers in this list are to be used for accounting purposes. Note that only radius servers can be added to this list.

csOrionAAAServerListName.name: csOrionAAAServerListName
csOrionAAAServerListName.description: The name given to the collection of AAA servers. An application refers to this name when specifying which group of servers to use for AAA purposes. This object has to be set during creation.

csOrionAAAServerListPriority.name: csOrionAAAServerListPriority
csOrionAAAServerListPriority.description: The relative priority of the server in this list. Lower number means higher priority.

csOrionAAAServerListSvrName.name: csOrionAAAServerListSvrName
csOrionAAAServerListSvrName.description: The name of the AAA server as defined in csOrionAAAServerConfigTable. A value of 'local' for this object means that the authentication is done locally.

csOrionAAAServerListSvrType.name: csOrionAAAServerListSvrType
csOrionAAAServerListSvrType.description: The type of AAA server. undefined(-1) means the corresponding AAA server is not yet defined, i.e., no entry in csOrionAAAServerConfigTable with a name as defined in csOrionAAAServerListSvrName. local(3) means that authentication is to be done locally.

csOrionAAAServerListRowStatus.name: csOrionAAAServerListRowStatus
csOrionAAAServerListRowStatus.description: Used to create a row (createAndGo) or destroy a row. When setting this object to createAndGo, csOrionAAAServerListSvrName must also be set. Once the row is created, get on this object will always yield active(1).

csOrionAAAServerListConfigTableEnd.name: csOrionAAAServerListConfigTableEnd
csOrionAAAServerListConfigTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionAAAServerListAdminTable.name: csOrionAAAServerListAdminTable
csOrionAAAServerListAdminTable.description: This table contains a RowStatus object to destroy an AAA server list defined in csOrionAAAServerListConfigTable. This provides a quick way to destroy the list without having to destroy each csOrionAAAServerListConfigEntry.

csOrionAAAServerListAdminEntry.name: csOrionAAAServerListAdminEntry
csOrionAAAServerListAdminEntry.description: Each entry represents an AAA server list.

csOrionAAAServerListAdminRowStatus.name: csOrionAAAServerListAdminRowStatus
csOrionAAAServerListAdminRowStatus.description: Setting this object to destroy(6) will destroy the whole AAA service list with {type, name} specified in {csOrionAAAServerListConfigType, csOrionAAAServerListConfigName}.

csOrionAAAServiceInfoEnd.name: csOrionAAAServiceInfoEnd
csOrionAAAServiceInfoEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionVrSpfConfTable.name: csOrionVrSpfConfTable
csOrionVrSpfConfTable.description: This table contains SPF configuration parameters.

csOrionVrSpfConfEntry.name: csOrionVrSpfConfEntry
csOrionVrSpfConfEntry.description: This table specifies a set of configurable parameters for the SPF module within each VR.

csOrionVrSpfConnTblSize.name: csOrionVrSpfConnTblSize
csOrionVrSpfConnTblSize.description: This Size puts an upper limit on the total number of sessions (inclusive of TCP and UDP) that this VR will accept, connections beyond this number will be dropped.

csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTblSize.name: csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTblSize
csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTblSize.description: This Size puts an upper limit on the number of TCP sessions that can remain in the SYN state at any given time, this limits the ability to accept new TCP connections simultaneously.

csOrionVrSpfUdpInitTblSize.name: csOrionVrSpfUdpInitTblSize
csOrionVrSpfUdpInitTblSize.description: This Size puts an upper limit on the number of UDP sessions that can remain in the unmatched state at any given time, this limits the ability to accept new UDP connections simultaneously.

csOrionVrSpfTcpSeqCheck.name: csOrionVrSpfTcpSeqCheck
csOrionVrSpfTcpSeqCheck.description: If enabled, the tcp packets will be checked for validity of sequence number, this is done at init time, established state and close time.

csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTimeout.name: csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTimeout
csOrionVrSpfTcpInitTimeout.description: This time out value decides how long a TCP session can remain in SYN state without the session establishment process reaching completion, the session is deleted after the expiry of this period.

csOrionVrSpfTcpIdleTimeout.name: csOrionVrSpfTcpIdleTimeout
csOrionVrSpfTcpIdleTimeout.description: This timeout value decides how long a TCP session can hang around without any activity(or Idle), such entries are deleted after the expiry of this period and end peers reset.

csOrionVrSpfTcpCloseTimeout.name: csOrionVrSpfTcpCloseTimeout
csOrionVrSpfTcpCloseTimeout.description: This decides the lifetime of the TIME_WAIT state in the TCP session closure sequence.

csOrionVrSpfUdpIdleTimeout.name: csOrionVrSpfUdpIdleTimeout
csOrionVrSpfUdpIdleTimeout.description: This is the Idle timeout period for UDp sessions.

csOrionVrSpfIcmpIdleTimeout.name: csOrionVrSpfIcmpIdleTimeout

csOrionFRoIPConfTable.description: This table contains general FRoIP Configuration parameters.

csOrionFRoIPConfEntry.name: csOrionFRoIPConfEntry
csOrionFRoIPConfEntry.description: Each entry represents a set of FRoIPconfiguration for a Virtual Router. There is only one instance of FRoIP on a Virtual Router. An entry is created with IP address and default values for all the other objects when a VR is created. Creation of row by Network Management Stations is not allowed.

csOrionFRoIPConfDefaultServiceSlot.name: csOrionFRoIPConfDefaultServiceSlot
csOrionFRoIPConfDefaultServiceSlot.description: This object identifies the slot that all new transports created off this base inherit.

csOrionFRoIPTransportTable.name: csOrionFRoIPTransportTable
csOrionFRoIPTransportTable.description: This table contains transport related objects of FRoIP.

csOrionFRoIPTransportEntry.name: csOrionFRoIPTransportEntry
csOrionFRoIPTransportEntry.description: Each entry represents a set of transport related objects of FRoIP on a Virtual Router.

csFRoIPCircuitTable.name: csFRoIPCircuitTable
csFRoIPCircuitTable.description: A table containing information about virtual circuits corresponding to FRoIP Transports..

csFRoIPCircuitEntry.name: csFRoIPCircuitEntry
csFRoIPCircuitEntry.description: The information regarding a single Data Link Connection. Discontinuities in the counters contained in this table are indicated by the value in csFrCircuitCreationTime.

csFRoIPCircuitDlci.name: csFRoIPCircuitDlci
csFRoIPCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit. Note, this impelemtation supports only values between 16 and 1023 (inclusive).

csFRoIPCircuitState.name: csFRoIPCircuitState
csFRoIPCircuitState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational. In the absence of a Data Link Connection Management Interface, virtual circuit entries (rows) may be created by setting virtual circuit state to 'active', or deleted by changing Circuit state to 'invalid'. Whether or not the row actually disappears is left to the implementation, so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time. It is also legal to set the state of a virtual circuit to 'inactive' to temporarily disable a given circuit. The use of 'invalid' is deprecated in this SNMP Version 2 MIB, in favor of csFRoIPCircuitRowStatus.

csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFECNs.name: csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFECNs
csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating forward congestion since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the remote DTE sets the FECN flag, or when a switch in the network enqueues the frame to a trunk whose transmission queue is congested.

csFRoIPCircuitReceivedBECNs.name: csFRoIPCircuitReceivedBECNs
csFRoIPCircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating backward congestion since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the remote DTE sets the BECN flag, or when a switch in the network receives the frame from a trunk whose transmission queue is congested.

csFRoIPCircuitSentFrames.name: csFRoIPCircuitSentFrames
csFRoIPCircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

csFRoIPCircuitSentOctets.name: csFRoIPCircuitSentOctets
csFRoIPCircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created. Octets counted are the full frame relay header and the payload, but do not include the flag characters or CRC.

csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFrames.name: csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFrames
csFRoIPCircuitReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

csFRoIPCircuitReceivedOctets.name: csFRoIPCircuitReceivedOctets
csFRoIPCircuitReceivedOctets.description: Number of octets received over this virtual circuit since it was created. Octets counted include the full frame relay header, but do not include the flag characters or the CRC.

csFRoIPCircuitCreationTime.name: csFRoIPCircuitCreationTime
csFRoIPCircuitCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the virtual circuit was created, whether by the Data Link Connection Management Interface or by a SetRequest.

csFRoIPCircuitLastTimeChange.name: csFRoIPCircuitLastTimeChange
csFRoIPCircuitLastTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when last there was a change in the virtual circuit state

csFRoIPCircuitCommittedBurst.name: csFRoIPCircuitCommittedBurst
csFRoIPCircuitCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

csFRoIPCircuitExcessBurst.name: csFRoIPCircuitExcessBurst
csFRoIPCircuitExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will attempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

csFRoIPCircuitThroughput.name: csFRoIPCircuitThroughput
csFRoIPCircuitThroughput.description: Throughput is the average number of 'Frame Relay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement interval. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both non-zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=csFRoIPCircuitCommittedBurst/csFRoIPCircuitThroughput. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=csFRoIPCircuitExcessBurst/ifSpeed.

csFRoIPCircuitMulticast.name: csFRoIPCircuitMulticast
csFRoIPCircuitMulticast.reference: Frame Relay PVC Multicast Service and Protocol Description Implementation: FRF.7 Frame Relay Forum Technical Committe October 21, 1994
csFRoIPCircuitMulticast.description: This indicates whether this VC is used as a unicast VC (i.e. not multicast) or the type of multicast service subscribed to

csFRoIPCircuitType.name: csFRoIPCircuitType
csFRoIPCircuitType.description: Indication of whether the VC was manually created (static), or dynamically created (dynamic) via the data link control management interface.

csFRoIPCircuitDiscards.name: csFRoIPCircuitDiscards
csFRoIPCircuitDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames dropped because of format errors, or because the VC is inactive.

csFRoIPCircuitReceivedDEs.name: csFRoIPCircuitReceivedDEs
csFRoIPCircuitReceivedDEs.description: Number of frames received from the network indicating that they were eligible for discard since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the remote DTE sets the DE flag, or when in remote DTE's switch detects that the frame was received as Excess Burst data.

csFRoIPCircuitSentDEs.name: csFRoIPCircuitSentDEs
csFRoIPCircuitSentDEs.description: Number of frames sent to the network indicating that they were eligible for discard since the virtual circuit was created. This occurs when the local DTE sets the DE flag, indicating that during Network congestion situations those frames should be discarded in preference of other frames sent without the DE bit set.

csFRoIPCircuitRowStatus.name: csFRoIPCircuitRowStatus
csFRoIPCircuitRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention. Writable objects in the table may be written in any RowStatus state.

csFRoIPCircuitOperStatus.name: csFRoIPCircuitOperStatus
csFRoIPCircuitOperStatus.description: The operational status of this circuit.

csFRoIPCircuitFwdLink.name: csFRoIPCircuitFwdLink
csFRoIPCircuitFwdLink.description: The forwarding link of this DLCI. This is a switching parameters for intra blade and inter-blade switching. It takes the following format: byte #0 to #3 : Slot number (csFRoIPDlcmiSlot) byte #4 to #7 : Port number (csFRoIPDlcmiPort) byte #8 to #11 : Channel number (csFRoIPDlcmiChannel, zero for unchannelized blade) byte #12 to #15: DLCI number (csFRoIPCircuitDlci) NOTE: all zero indicates that this DLCI is not connected to any link.

csFRoIPCircuitTableEnd.name: csFRoIPCircuitTableEnd
csFRoIPCircuitTableEnd.description: End of this group. value undefined

csOrionL2tpConfigTable.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTable
csOrionL2tpConfigTable.description: This table contains general L2TP configuration parameters. IMPORTANT : Tunnels and session parameters are established using the parameters in this table. That means, changing the value of an object in this table will not affect existing tunnels and session. It will be applied for the tunnels and session that are to be established.

csOrionL2tpConfigEntry.name: csOrionL2tpConfigEntry
csOrionL2tpConfigEntry.description: Each entry represents a single L2TP object for a Virtual Router. Only a single instance of this object is created upon creation of a VR.

csOrionL2tpConfigServiceIf.name: csOrionL2tpConfigServiceIf
csOrionL2tpConfigServiceIf.description: This object defines the VI over which communication will occur with peers. This object can be set only when there is no tunnel.

csOrionL2tpConfigMaxTunnels.name: csOrionL2tpConfigMaxTunnels
csOrionL2tpConfigMaxTunnels.description: This object defines the maximum number of L2TP tunnels that can be established.

csOrionL2tpConfigMaxSessionsPerTunnel.name: csOrionL2tpConfigMaxSessionsPerTunnel
csOrionL2tpConfigMaxSessionsPerTunnel.description: This object defines the maximum sessions that can be established per tunnel.

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelAuthentication.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelAuthentication
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelAuthentication.description: This object controls the tunnel authentication. If set to Enable, a challenge will be sent to the peer during tunnel creation. The tunnel will be torn down if the peer does not send a valid response. Regardless of the setting, if the peer sends a challenge during tunnel creation, a response will be sent.

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelHelloInterval.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelHelloInterval
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelHelloInterval.description: This object defines the interval (in seconds) in which HELLO (or keep-alive) packets are to be sent to the tunnel peer. Setting this to 0 disables sending of HELLO packets

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmission.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmissions
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmission.description: This object defines the number of retransmissions which the tunnel will attempt before assuming that the peer is no longer responding.

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmission.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmissionTimeout
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelMaxRetransmission.description: This object defines the maximum retransmission timeout interval in seconds which the tunnel will wait before retransmitting a control packet that has not been acknowledged.

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelRWS.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelRWS
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelRWS.description: This object defines the control channel receive window size. It specifies the maximum number of packets the tunnel peer can send without waiting for an acknowledgement from this peer.

csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeou.name: csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeout
csOrionL2tpConfigTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeou.description: This object controls the time interval in seconds after which an alive but empty tunnel (i.e. a tunnel without sessions) will be torn down. Setting this to 0 will allow the empty tunnel to continue to exist until either the peer stops responding or the the tunnel is torn down by peer or the administrator.

csOrionL2tpConfigSessionFlowControl.name: csOrionL2tpConfigSessionFlowControl
csOrionL2tpConfigSessionFlowControl.description: This object will be used to control whether the peer will be requested to flow control its transmissions. Note that regardless of the setting, if the peer requests that this peer flow control its transmissions, that request will be honored. Session Flow Control was part of draft specifications but not part of the RFC. This object should be set to Enable only if all the peers are using draft implementations.

csOrionL2tpConfigSessionRWS.name: csOrionL2tpConfigSessionRWS
csOrionL2tpConfigSessionRWS.description: This object controls the size of the session receive window. It will be advertised to the peer during session setup if csOrionL2tpConfigSessionFlowControl is set to Enable. The value 0 has special significance. It indicates that the peer must include sequence numbers in payload packets but the peer need not flow control its transmissions. This can be used to force a peer that is non-RFC compliant to include sequence numbers in payload packets.

csOrionL2tpConfigSessionTxQueueSize.name: csOrionL2tpConfigSessionTxQueueSize
csOrionL2tpConfigSessionTxQueueSize.description: This object controls the size of the session-specific transmit queue. If the peer has requested flow control and the peer's session receive window is full, packets to be sent to that peer will be held in a queue waiting for the peer's receive window to open.

csOrionL2tpConfigSessionPacketSequencing.name: csOrionL2tpConfigSessionPacketSequencing
csOrionL2tpConfigSessionPacketSequencing.description: This object determines whether or not session payload packets will be requested to be sent with sequence numbers from the tunnel peer.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppConfigReqRetransmiss.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppConfigReqRetransmission
csOrionL2tpConfigPppConfigReqRetransmiss.description: This object is identical to csOrionPppIfConfigReqRtx.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppRestartTimeout.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppRestartTimeout
csOrionL2tpConfigPppRestartTimeout.description: This object is identical to csOrionPppIfTimeout.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppTermReqRetransmissio.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppTermReqRetransmission
csOrionL2tpConfigPppTermReqRetransmissio.description: This object is identical to csOrionPppIfTerminateReqRtx.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppAuthProtocol.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppAuthProtocol
csOrionL2tpConfigPppAuthProtocol.description: This object is identical to csOrionPppIfConfigAuth.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppReauthPeriod.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppReauthPeriod
csOrionL2tpConfigPppReauthPeriod.description: This object is identical to csOrionPppIfReauth.

csOrionL2tpConfigPppIpPoolName.name: csOrionL2tpConfigPppIpPoolName
csOrionL2tpConfigPppIpPoolName.description: The name of this address pool. This is used to identify a specific address pool.

csOrionL2tpTunnelTable.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelTable
csOrionL2tpTunnelTable.description: The entries in this table are the L2TP tunnels that have been established with various peers.

csOrionL2tpTunnelEntry.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelEntry
csOrionL2tpTunnelEntry.description: Each entry represents a single L2TP tunnel established with a peer.

csOrionL2tpTunnelLocalId.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelLocalId
csOrionL2tpTunnelLocalId.description: Each tunnel is assigned a random locally unique identifier when the tunnel is created. The tunnel identifier can be used as an index for the tunnel table.

csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxSessions.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxSessions
csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxSessions.description: This object defines the maximum sessions that can be established in this tunnel. NOTE : Not used at this time.

csOrionL2tpTunnelAuthentication.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelAuthentication
csOrionL2tpTunnelAuthentication.description: This object controls the tunnel authentication. If set to Enable, a challenge will be sent to the peer during tunnel creation. The tunnel will be torn down if the peer does not send a valid response. Regardless of the setting, if the peer sends a challenge during tunnel creation, a response will be sent.

csOrionL2tpTunnelHelloInterval.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelHelloInterval
csOrionL2tpTunnelHelloInterval.description: This object defines the interval (in seconds) in which HELLO (or keep-alive) packets are to be sent to the tunnel peer. The value 0 indicates that sending of HELLO packets is disabled

csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissions.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissions
csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissions.description: This object defines the number of retransmission's which the tunnel will attempt before assuming that the peer is no longer responding.

csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissionTimeou.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissionTimeout
csOrionL2tpTunnelMaxRetransmissionTimeou.description: This object defines the maximum retransmission timeout interval in seconds which the tunnel will wait before retransmitting a control packet that has not been acknowledged.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRWS.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRWS
csOrionL2tpTunnelRWS.description: This object defines the control channel receive window size. It specifies the maximum number of packets the tunnel peer can send without waiting for an acknowledgement from this peer.

csOrionL2tpTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeout.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeout
csOrionL2tpTunnelEmptyTunnelTimeout.description: This object controls the time interval in seconds after which an alive but empty tunnel (i.e. a tunnel without sessions) will be torn down. The value 0 indicates that the empty tunnel will continue to exist until either the peer stops responding or the the tunnel is torn down by peer or the administrator.

csOrionL2tpTunnelUpTime.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelUpTime
csOrionL2tpTunnelUpTime.description: This object indicates the number of seconds this tunnel has been up since it was established.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteIpAddress.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteIpAddress
csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteIpAddress.description: This index identifies the IP Address of the peer.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteTunnelId.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteTunnelId
csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteTunnelId.description: This object is the identifier assigned to the tunnel by the peer. This identifier is unique only for a given peer.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteUdpPort.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteUdpPort
csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteUdpPort.description: This object identifies the UDP port that the peer is using for communication.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteRWS.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteRWS
csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteRWS.description: This is the control receive window size advertised by the peer during tunnel creation. It specifies the number of control packets that can be sent to the peer without waiting for an acknowledgement.

csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteHostname.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteHostname
csOrionL2tpTunnelRemoteHostname.description: This is the name that the peer used to identify itself during tunnel creation

csOrionL2tpTunnelActiveSessionsCount.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelActiveSessionsCount
csOrionL2tpTunnelActiveSessionsCount.description: This is the number of sessions that are currently present within this tunnel

csOrionL2tpTunnelStatus.name: csOrionL2tpTunnelStatus
csOrionL2tpTunnelStatus.description: The row status for this table. Used only for deleting this tunnel. IMPORTANT: (1) entries on this table are created when a tunnel is established by the peer. Therefore, creation of entry thru SNMP SET request is not allowed. (2) tunnel is usually torn down by the peer.

csOrionL2tpSessionTable.name: csOrionL2tpSessionTable
csOrionL2tpSessionTable.description: The entries in this table are the L2TP sessions established in a specific tunnel.

csOrionL2tpSessionEntry.name: csOrionL2tpSessionEntry
csOrionL2tpSessionEntry.description: Each entry represents a single session object in a specific tunnel.

csOrionL2tpSessionLocalId.name: csOrionL2tpSessionLocalId
csOrionL2tpSessionLocalId.description: Each session is assigned a random locally unique tunnel-specific identifier when it is created. The session identifier can be used as an index to identify a particular session in a tunnel.

csOrionL2tpSessionFlowControl.name: csOrionL2tpSessionFlowControl
csOrionL2tpSessionFlowControl.description: This object will be used to control whether the peer will be requested to flow control its transmissions. Note that regardless of the setting, if the peer requests that this peer flow control its transmissions, that request will be honored. Session Flow Control was part of draft specifications but not part of the RFC. This object should be set to Enable only if all the peers are using draft implementations.

csOrionL2tpSessionRWS.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRWS
csOrionL2tpSessionRWS.description: This object controls the size of the session receive window. It will be advertised to the peer during session setup if csOrionL2tpConfigSessionFlowControl is set to Enable. The value 0 has special significance. It indicates that the peer must include sequence numbers in payload packets but the peer need not flow control its transmissions. This can be used to force a peer that is non-RFC compliant to include sequence numbers in payload packets.

csOrionL2tpSessionTxQueueSize.name: csOrionL2tpSessionTxQueueSize
csOrionL2tpSessionTxQueueSize.description: If the peer has requested flow control and the peer's session receive window is full, packets to be sent to that peer will be held in a queue waiting for the peer's receive window to open. This object controls the size of the session-specific transmit queue.

csOrionL2tpSessionPacketSequencing.name: csOrionL2tpSessionPacketSequencing
csOrionL2tpSessionPacketSequencing.description: This object determines whether or not session payload packets will be requested to be sent with sequence numbers from the tunnel peer.

csOrionL2tpSessionUpTime.name: csOrionL2tpSessionUpTime
csOrionL2tpSessionUpTime.description: This object indicates the number of seconds this session has been up since established.

csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteCallId.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteCallId
csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteCallId.description: This object is the identifier assigned to the session by the peer. This identifier is unique only for a given peer in a specific tunnel.

csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteFlowControl.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteFlowControl
csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteFlowControl.description: This object indicates whether flow control is requested by the peer or not.

csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteRWS.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteRWS
csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteRWS.description: This is the session receive window size advertised by the peer during session creation. It specifies the number of payload packets that can be sent to the peer without waiting for an acknowledgement. If this is non-zero it means that the peer has requested flow control.

csOrionL2tpSessionUsername.name: csOrionL2tpSessionUsername
csOrionL2tpSessionUsername.description: This is the name of the user on whose behalf the session was created.

csOrionL2tpSessionRowStatus.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRowStatus
csOrionL2tpSessionRowStatus.description: The row status for this table. Used only for deleting this session. IMPORTANT: (1) entries on this table are created when a session is established by the peer. Therefore, creation of entry thru SNMP SET request is not allowed. (2) the peer usually tears down the session.

csOrionL2tpSessionLocalIpAddress.name: csOrionL2tpSessionLocalIpAddress
csOrionL2tpSessionLocalIpAddress.description: The IP address for this sesssion. It is dynamically assigned form the csOrionL2tpConfigPppIpPoolName.

csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteIpAddress.name: csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteIpAddress
csOrionL2tpSessionRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address on the other side of this sesssion.

csOrionL2tpSessionCallType.name: csOrionL2tpSessionCallType
csOrionL2tpSessionCallType.description: This object indicates the type of call and the role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, lacIncoming(1) indicates that this tunnel peer is acting as a LAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the LNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both LAC and LNS simultaneously.

csOrionL2tpSessionState.name: csOrionL2tpSessionState
csOrionL2tpSessionState.description: This object determines the current state of the session or call.

csOrionLnsConfigTable.name: csOrionLnsConfigTable
csOrionLnsConfigTable.description: This table contains general L2TP Network Server (LNS) configuration parameters.

csOrionLnsConfigEntry.name: csOrionLnsConfigEntry
csOrionLnsConfigEntry.description: Each entry represents a single LNS object for a Virtual Router. There is only one instance of LNS on a Virtual Router. This object is created along with an L2TP object when a VR is created.

csOrionLnsConfigAdminStatus.name: csOrionLnsConfigAdminStatus
csOrionLnsConfigAdminStatus.description: Setting this object to 'disable' causes all tunnels to be immediately disconnected and no further tunnels to be either initiated or accepted. Setting this object to 'drain' will prevent any new tunnels and/or sessions to be either initiated or accepted but does NOT disconnect any active tunnels/sessions.

csOrionLacConfigTable.name: csOrionLacConfigTable
csOrionLacConfigTable.description: This table contains general L2TP Network Server (LNS) configuration parameters.

csOrionLacConfigEntry.name: csOrionLacConfigEntry
csOrionLacConfigEntry.description: Each entry represents a single LAC object for a Virtual Router. There is only one instance of LAC on a Virtual Router. This object is created along with an L2TP object when a VR is created.

csOrionLacConfigAdminStatus.name: csOrionLacConfigAdminStatus
csOrionLacConfigAdminStatus.description: Setting this object to 'disable' causes all tunnels to be immediately disconnected and no further tunnels to be either initiated or accepted. Setting this object to 'drain' will prevent any new tunnels and/or sessions to be either initiated or accepted but does NOT disconnect any active tunnels/sessions.

csOrionTunnelSwitchClientName.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchClientName
csOrionTunnelSwitchClientName.description: This object identifies the client name of the originating tunnel.

csOrionTunnelSwitchMode.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchMode
csOrionTunnelSwitchMode.description: This object determines the switching action.

csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetIpAddress.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetIpAddress
csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetIpAddress.description: This object identifies the IP address of the destination LNS.

csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetPriority.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetPriority
csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetPriority.description: This object determines the priority of this target address. Priority value 1 being the highest.

csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetMaxSession.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetMaxSession
csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetMaxSession.description: This object determines the maximum number of sessions that can be handled by this target address.

csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetSessionCount.name: csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetSessionCount
csOrionTunnelSwitchTargetSessionCount.description: This object keeps the count of the active sessions on this target address.

csOrionL2tpStatsTable.name: csOrionL2tpStatsTable
csOrionL2tpStatsTable.description: The L2TP Status and Statistics table.

csOrionL2tpStatsEntry.name: csOrionL2tpStatsEntry
csOrionL2tpStatsEntry.description: An L2TP Stats entry. An entry in this table may correspond to a single endpoint or a group of tunnel endpoints.

csOrionL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.name: csOrionL2tpStatsTotalTunnels
csOrionL2tpStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels that have successfully reached the established state.

csOrionL2tpStatsFailedTunnels.name: csOrionL2tpStatsFailedTunnels
csOrionL2tpStatsFailedTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that failed to reach the established state.

csOrionL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications.name: csOrionL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications
csOrionL2tpStatsFailedAuthentications.description: This object returns the number of failed tunnel connection attempts because the tunnel peer failed authentication.

csOrionL2tpStatsActiveTunnels.name: csOrionL2tpStatsActiveTunnels
csOrionL2tpStatsActiveTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that are currently active.

csOrionL2tpStatsTotalSessions.name: csOrionL2tpStatsTotalSessions
csOrionL2tpStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions that have successfully reached the established state.

csOrionL2tpStatsFailedSessions.name: csOrionL2tpStatsFailedSessions
csOrionL2tpStatsFailedSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state.

csOrionL2tpStatsActiveSessions.name: csOrionL2tpStatsActiveSessions
csOrionL2tpStatsActiveSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that are currently active.

csOrionL2tpStatsDrainingTunnels.name: csOrionL2tpStatsDrainingTunnels
csOrionL2tpStatsDrainingTunnels.description: This object indicates if this L2TP is draining off sessions from all tunnels. This object will return no(2) when the domain is not draining sessions or after the last L2TP session has disconnected when the domain is in the draining state.

csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets
csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets received. NOTE : This is not currently supported. It will just return zero. [Alan 10/12/2000]

csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets
csOrionL2tpStatsControlRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets received.

csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendOctets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendOctets
csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints. NOTE : This is not currently supported. It will just return zero. [Alan 10/12/2000]

csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendPackets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendPackets
csOrionL2tpStatsControlSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints.

csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets
csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were received.

csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.name: csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets
csOrionL2tpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were received.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterTable.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterTable
csOrionVrDsByteFilterTable.description: This table specifies a set of acl's to be applied to packets received by (and sent from) this virtual router. The first entry whose acl matches a packet causes the DS Byte field of the packet to be set to the value specified in the table entry. If no entry's acl matches the packet, the DS Byte field of the packet will be set to the value specified in csOrionVPNVRouterIpDsByte.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterEntry.description: Each entry specifies whether packets satisfying a specific access list entry will have their DS Byte field set to the value indicated in the table entry.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterAclId.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterAclId

csOrionVrDsByteFilterAction.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterAction
csOrionVrDsByteFilterAction.description: The action performed by this filter.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterValue.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterValue
csOrionVrDsByteFilterValue.description: This object defines the values to be placed in the TypeOfService octet of each IP packet sent out or forwarded by the VR. The valid range covers both 7-bit configurations recommended in RFC 1349 (Precedence and TOS bits) and 6-bit configurations recommended in RFC 2474 (Differentiated Services). If the value selected is 256, the DsByte is not changed and packets are forwarded with their existing TypeOfService byte value.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterDirection.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterDirection
csOrionVrDsByteFilterDirection.description: The direction of packets on which this filter is applied.

csOrionVrDsByteFilterRowStatus.name: csOrionVrDsByteFilterRowStatus
csOrionVrDsByteFilterRowStatus.description: A row status type for this Table entry.

csOrionViDsByteFilterTable.name: csOrionViDsByteFilterTable

The first entry whose acl matches a packet causes the DS Byte field of the packet to be set to the value specified in the table entry. If no entry's acl matches the packet, the DS Byte field of the packet will be set to the value specified in csOrionVPNVRouterIpDsByte.
