csOrionPowerSupplyOutputPowerState.description: A power supply's output power state.

csOrionFanEntry.name: csOrionFanEntry
csOrionFanEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to fans.

csOrionFanIndex.name: csOrionFanIndex
csOrionFanIndex.description: An index for a fan table.

csOrionFanSpeed.name: csOrionFanSpeed
csOrionFanSpeed.description: A fan speed (in RPS: Revolutions Per Second).

csOrionPowerSupplyHWRevision.name: csOrionPowerSupplyHWRevision
csOrionPowerSupplyHWRevision.description: The hardward revision information of the power supply controller.

csOrionPowerSupplyFWMajorRevision.name: csOrionPowerSupplyFWMajorRevision
csOrionPowerSupplyFWMajorRevision.description: The major firmware revision information of the power supply controller.

csOrionPowerSupplyFWMinorRevision.name: csOrionPowerSupplyFWMinorRevision
csOrionPowerSupplyFWMinorRevision.description: The minor firmware revision information of the power supply controller.

csOrionPowerSupplyFWRelease.name: csOrionPowerSupplyFWRelease
csOrionPowerSupplyFWRelease.description: The firmware release of the power supply controller.

csOrionPowerSupplyFWReleaseDate.name: csOrionPowerSupplyFWReleaseDate
csOrionPowerSupplyFWReleaseDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the firmware release.

csOrionPowerSupplyEventTrapGeneration.name: csOrionPowerSupplyEventTrapGeneration
csOrionPowerSupplyEventTrapGeneration.description: This object is used to enable/disable the generation of events and traps of the power supply.

csOrionFanTrayControlTable.name: csOrionFanTrayControlTable
csOrionFanTrayControlTable.description: There is a controller for each of the fan tray. This table contains entries of the hardware and firmware revision information and entries used to enable/disable the event/trap generation.

csOrionFanTrayControlEntry.name: csOrionFanTrayControlEntry
csOrionFanTrayControlEntry.description: An entry containing PIC H/W and F/W Revision information applicable to fan tray controllers.

csOrionFanTray.name: csOrionFanTray
csOrionFanTray.description: Identifies the upper or lower fan tray.

csOrionFanTrayFWMajorRevision.name: csOrionFanTrayFWMajorRevision
csOrionFanTrayFWMajorRevision.description: Fan tray's firmware major Revision information.

csOrionFanTrayFWMinorRevision.name: csOrionFanTrayFWMinorRevision
csOrionFanTrayFWMinorRevision.description: Fan tray's firmware minor Revision information.

csOrionFanTrayFWRelease.name: csOrionFanTrayFWRelease
csOrionFanTrayFWRelease.description: The firmware release of the fan tray controller.

csOrionFanTrayFWReleaseDate.name: csOrionFanTrayFWReleaseDate
csOrionFanTrayFWReleaseDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the firmware release.

csOrionFanTrayEventTrapGeneration.name: csOrionFanTrayEventTrapGeneration
csOrionFanTrayEventTrapGeneration.description: Fan tray's firmware minor Revision information.

csOrionFanTempSensorEntry.name: csOrionFanTempSensorEntry
csOrionFanTempSensorEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to fans.

csOrionFanTempSensorState.name: csOrionFanTempSensorState
csOrionFanTempSensorState.description: the temperature sensor's operational status of a fan.

csOrionFanTempSensorTemperature.name: csOrionFanTempSensorTemperature
csOrionFanTempSensorTemperature.description: A temperature (in Fahrenheit or Celsius) of the Fan.

csOrionTempAirFlowCardTable.name: csOrionTempAirFlowCardTable
csOrionTempAirFlowCardTable.description: A table for temperature air flow card.

csOrionTempAirFlowCardEntry.name: csOrionTempAirFlowCardEntry
csOrionTempAirFlowCardEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to temperature air flow card.

csOrionAirFlowCardIndex.name: csOrionAirFlowCardIndex
csOrionAirFlowCardIndex.description: Identifies the temperature air flow card.

csOrionAirFlowCardHWRevision.name: csOrionAirFlowCardHWRevision
csOrionAirFlowCardHWRevision.description: The air flow card's hardward Revision information.

csOrionAirFlowCardFWMajorRevision.name: csOrionAirFlowCardFWMajorRevision
csOrionAirFlowCardFWMajorRevision.description: The air flow card's firmwar major Revision information.

csOrionAirFlowCardFWMinorRevision.name: csOrionAirFlowCardFWMinorRevision
csOrionAirFlowCardFWMinorRevision.description: The air flow card's firmware minor Revision information.

csOrionAirFlowCardFWRelease.name: csOrionAirFlowCardFWRelease
csOrionAirFlowCardFWRelease.description: The air flow card's firmware release information.

csOrionAirFlowCardFWReleaseDate.name: csOrionAirFlowCardFWReleaseDate
csOrionAirFlowCardFWReleaseDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the firmwre release.

csOrionAirFlowCardTempState.name: csOrionAirFlowCardTempState
csOrionAirFlowCardTempState.description: An inlet air flow temperature sensor operational state.

csOrionAirFlowCardEventTrapGeneration.name: csOrionAirFlowCardEventTrapGeneration
csOrionAirFlowCardEventTrapGeneration.description: The air flow card's trap/event generation status.

csOrionStatusPanelHWRevision.name: csOrionStatusPanelHWRevision
csOrionStatusPanelHWRevision.description: The hardward revision information of the status panel controller.

csOrionStatusPanelFWMajorRevision.name: csOrionStatusPanelFWMajorRevision
csOrionStatusPanelFWMajorRevision.description: The major firmware revision information of the status panel controller.

csOrionStatusPanelFWMinorRevision.name: csOrionStatusPanelFWMinorRevision
csOrionStatusPanelFWMinorRevision.description: The minor firmware revision information of the status panel controller.

csOrionStatusPanelFWRelease.name: csOrionStatusPanelFWRelease
csOrionStatusPanelFWRelease.description: The firmware release of the power supply controller.

csOrionStatusPanelFWReleaseDate.name: csOrionStatusPanelFWReleaseDate
csOrionStatusPanelFWReleaseDate.description: A textual string containing information about the date of the firmware release.

csOrionSnmpGenTable.name: csOrionSnmpGenTable
csOrionSnmpGenTable.description: This table controls the activation of the snmp agent on a particular Virtual Router. Note, only one agent instance can be enabled at a time.

csOrionSnmpGenEntry.name: csOrionSnmpGenEntry
csOrionSnmpGenEntry.description: Each entry represents a single Virtual Router.

csOrionSnmpGenStatus.name: csOrionSnmpGenStatus
csOrionSnmpGenStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the snmp server on this Virtual Router. If this object is disabled, the snmp server will not respond to any snmp requests and it won't send any traps.

csOrionSnmpCommTable.name: csOrionSnmpCommTable
csOrionSnmpCommTable.description: This table contains all the community strings recognized by the snmp server on this device.

csOrionSnmpCommEntry.name: csOrionSnmpCommEntry
csOrionSnmpCommEntry.description: Each entry represents a single community string.

csOrionSnmpCommString.name: csOrionSnmpCommString
csOrionSnmpCommString.description: This object identifies one community string recognized by the snmp server on this device.

csOrionSnmpCommAddr.name: csOrionSnmpCommAddr
csOrionSnmpCommAddr.description: This object identifies the Ip Address of a manager allowed to use this community string.

csOrionSnmpCommPriv.name: csOrionSnmpCommPriv
csOrionSnmpCommPriv.description: This object indicates the privilege level of this community string. If the value of this object is readOnly(1), this snmp server will respond only to GET, GETNEXT, and GETBULK requests from snmp managers using this community string. If this value of this object is readWrite(2), this snmp server will respond to any requests from snmp managers using this community string.

csOrionSnmpCommRowStatus.name: csOrionSnmpCommRowStatus
csOrionSnmpCommRowStatus.description: A row status type for the Snmp Community Table.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorTable.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorTable
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorTable.description: This table keeps track of the errors that happened when a NMS node tried to a SET operation. Since standard error codes returned by the SNMP response PDU was not comprehensive enough to indicate the actual problem, this table evolved. The NMS node has to keep the request-id field and the UDP port of the SET PDU that is being sent to the Orion SNMP agent. If the response-PDU corresponding to that SET returns an error, NMS node can browse this table with the saved request-id of the failed SET-PDU to get more information about the error.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorEntry.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorEntry
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorEntry.description: Each entry represent an error associated with a set operation by a management station. The Orion SNMP agent keeps track of the last 25 instances of such errors. Older entries give way for new entries.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsIpAddress.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsIpAddress
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsIpAddress.description: IP address of the management station which made an unsuccessful SET operation.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsPort.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsPort
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsPort.description: The UDP port of the SNMP SET request which resulted in an error.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsRequestId.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsRequestId
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorNmsRequestId.description: The requst-id field of the SNMP SET request which resulted in an error.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorCode.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorCode
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorCode.description: The error code set when the SNMP SET request resulted in an error.

csOrionSnmpAgentErrorMsg.name: csOrionSnmpAgentErrorMsg
csOrionSnmpAgentErrorMsg.description: Error message corresponding to the SET operation.

csOrionSnmpTrapTable.name: csOrionSnmpTrapTable
csOrionSnmpTrapTable.description: This table controls the generation of traps by this Virtual Router.

csOrionSnmpTrapEntry.name: csOrionSnmpTrapEntry
csOrionSnmpTrapEntry.description: Each entry represents a single Virtual Router.

csOrionSnmpTrapStatus.name: csOrionSnmpTrapStatus
csOrionSnmpTrapStatus.description: This object is used to control the trap function for the snmp server on this device. If the value of this object is enable(1), the snmp server will send traps. If the value is disable(2), the snmp server will not send traps.

csOrionTrapReceiverTable.name: csOrionTrapReceiverTable
csOrionTrapReceiverTable.description: The trap receiver table (0 to 25 entries). This table lists the addresses of stations that should receive trap messages from this entity when an exception condition occurs.

csOrionTrapReceiverComm.name: csOrionTrapReceiverComm
csOrionTrapReceiverComm.description: Community string used for trap messages to this trap receiver.

csOrionTrapReceiverRowStatus.name: csOrionTrapReceiverRowStatus
csOrionTrapReceiverRowStatus.description: A row status type for the Trap Receiver Table. This object is used to add or remove entries from this table.

csOrionTrapReceiverPort.name: csOrionTrapReceiverPort
csOrionTrapReceiverPort.description: UDP port number for trap receiver. By default, all traps are sent to Port 162.

csOrionTrapReceiverTrapType.name: csOrionTrapReceiverTrapType
csOrionTrapReceiverTrapType.description: The trap type, which the Receiver wish to receive from this managed entity. By default, v2 inform request type is used to notify traps.

csOrionVpnAcctTable.name: csOrionVpnAcctTable
csOrionVpnAcctTable.description: This table contains composite stats for each of the VPNs in this Orion.

csOrionVpnAcctEntry.name: csOrionVpnAcctEntry
csOrionVpnAcctEntry.description: Each entry contains composite stats for a single VPN.

csOrionVrAcctTable.name: csOrionVrAcctTable
csOrionVrAcctTable.description: This table contains composite stats for each of the VRs in this Orion.

csOrionVrAcctEntry.name: csOrionVrAcctEntry
csOrionVrAcctEntry.description: Each entry contains composite stats for a single VPN.

csDot1dBaseBridgeTable.name: csDot1dBaseBridgeTable
csDot1dBaseBridgeTable.description: A list of Virtual Bridges, configured for the Virtual Router.

csDot1dBaseBridgeEntry.name: csDot1dBaseBridgeEntry
csDot1dBaseBridgeEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a bridged VI of a VR.

csDot1dBaseBridgeAddress.name: csDot1dBaseBridgeAddress
csDot1dBaseBridgeAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this. However it is only required to be unique. When concatenated with dot1dStpPriority a unique BridgeIdentifier is formed which is used in the Spanning Tree Protocol. Note: This is used as the MAC address for this VB.

csDot1dBaseNumPorts.name: csDot1dBaseNumPorts
csDot1dBaseNumPorts.description: The number of ports controlled by this bridging entity.

csDot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards.name: csDot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards
csDot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards.description: The total number of Forwarding Database entries, which have been or would have been learnt, but have been discarded due to a lack of space to store them in the Forwarding Database. If this counter is increasing, it indicates that the Forwarding Database is regularly becoming full (a condition which has unpleasant performance effects on the subnetwork). If this counter has a significant value but is not presently increasing, it indicates that the problem has been occurring but is not persistent.

csDot1dTpAgingTime.name: csDot1dTpAgingTime
csDot1dTpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in seconds for aging out dynamically learned forwarding information. 802.1D-1990 recommends a default of 300 seconds.

csDot1dBaseBridgeEntryRowStatus.name: csDot1dBaseBridgeEntryRowStatus
csDot1dBaseBridgeEntryRowStatus.description: A row status type for the csDot1dBaseBridge Table.

csDot1dTpFdbTable.name: csDot1dTpFdbTable
csDot1dTpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about unicast entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

csDot1dTpFdbEntry.name: csDot1dTpFdbEntry
csDot1dTpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

csDot1dTpFdbAddress.name: csDot1dTpFdbAddress
csDot1dTpFdbAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

csDot1dTpFdbPort.name: csDot1dTpFdbPort
csDot1dTpFdbPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address (e.g. in the dot1dStaticTable). Implementors are encouraged to assign the port to this object whenever it is learned even addresses for which the corresponding value of dot1dTpFdbStatus is not learned(3).

csDot1dTpFdbSubPort.name: csDot1dTpFdbSubPort
csDot1dTpFdbSubPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the subport on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress has been seen.

csDot1dTpFdbStatus.name: csDot1dTpFdbStatus
csDot1dTpFdbStatus.description: The status of this entry. The meanings of the values are: other(1) : none of the following. This would include the case where some other MIB object (not the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort, nor an entry in the dot1dStaticTable) is being used to determine if and how frames addressed to the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress are being forwarded. invalid(2) : this entry is not longer valid (e.g., it was learned but has since aged-out), but has not yet been flushed from the table. learned(3) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort was learned, and is being used. self(4) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress one of the bridge's addresses. The corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbPort indicates which of the bridge's ports has this address. mgmt(5) : the value of the corresponding instance of dot1dTpFdbAddress is also the value of an existing instance of dot1dStaticAddress.

csDot1dPortEntry.name: csDot1dPortEntry
csDot1dPortEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and (or) filtering information.

csDot1dPortRemoteEnd.name: csDot1dPortRemoteEnd
csDot1dPortRemoteEnd.description: This object is used to identify the entity to which this Virtual Interface maps. That is, the remote end of this Virtual Interface. The format used for this ascii-string valued object is as follows: 'V|L|P|T VPNID|SlotID/VRID|PortID/VIID/ConnID/TLSID|LLID' Where 'V' indicates the other end of this Virtual Interface is another Virtual Interface. 'L' indicates this Virtual Interface maps to a Logical Link. P indicates pseudo wire. T indicates TLS. 'VPNID' is a Virtual Private Network ID. 'SlotID' identifies a specific slot on the Orion Box. 'VRID' is a Virtual Router ID for the VPN specified by VPNID. 'PortID' identifies a specific Port on the blade installed in the previously identified slot. 'VIID' is a Virtual Interface on the VR identified by VRID. ConnID refers to pseudo wire connection ID. TLSID refers to the TLS domain ID for pseudo wires. 'LLID' is a Logical Link ID on PortID. For example, if this Virtual Interface maps to another Virtual Interface (VI number 1 on VR 1.2.3.4 on VPN 4), this object might be set to this value: 'V 4/1.2.3.4/1' If this Virtual Interface maps to Logical Link 100 on Port 2 of Slot 2, this object might be set to this value: 'L 2/2:100' If this Virtual Interface maps to pseudo wire 100 on VPN 4 VR 1.2.3.4: P 4/1.2.3.4/100 If this Virtual Interface maps to TLS 100 on VPN 4 VR 1.2.3.4: T 4/1.2.3.4/100

csOrionRadiusAcctFlush.name: csOrionRadiusAcctFlush
csOrionRadiusAcctFlush.description: This object is used to flush the contents of the csOrionRadiusAcctTable. To flush the table, set the value of this object to 1.

csOrionRadiusAcctTable.name: csOrionRadiusAcctTable
csOrionRadiusAcctTable.description: This table contains composite stats for each of the VRs in this Orion.

csOrionRadiusAcctEntry.name: csOrionRadiusAcctEntry
csOrionRadiusAcctEntry.description: Each entry contains composite stats for a single VPN.

csOrionRadiusAcctIndex.name: csOrionRadiusAcctIndex
csOrionRadiusAcctIndex.description: The index of this radius accounting entry. The values will increase monotonically, even after the entries have been flushed.

csOrionRadiusAcctTimestamp.name: csOrionRadiusAcctTimestamp
csOrionRadiusAcctTimestamp.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was created.

csOrionRadiusAcctVpnId.name: csOrionRadiusAcctVpnId
csOrionRadiusAcctVpnId.description: The Id of the VPN that originated this radius accounting entry.

csOrionRadiusAcctVrId.name: csOrionRadiusAcctVrId
csOrionRadiusAcctVrId.description: The Id of the VR that originated this radius accounting entry.

csOrionRadiusAcctInfo.name: csOrionRadiusAcctInfo
csOrionRadiusAcctInfo.description: Information describing the creation or termination of a dynamic connection to a virtual router. The information is presented in standard radius accounting format.

csTelnetSvrConfTable.name: csTelnetSvrConfTable
csTelnetSvrConfTable.description: A table of telnet server configuration parameters.

csTelnetSvrConfEntry.name: csTelnetSvrConfEntry
csTelnetSvrConfEntry.description: Each entry contains a set of configuration paramters for telnet server in a VR. Note, that only a single instance of telnet server is enabledat a time.

csTelnetSvrConfAdminStatus.name: csTelnetSvrConfAdminStatus
csTelnetSvrConfAdminStatus.description: Enable/Disable the use of telnet server.

csTelnetSvrConfTimeout.name: csTelnetSvrConfTimeout
csTelnetSvrConfTimeout.description: A user configurable telnet timeout value in minutes.

csTelnetSvrConfNumOfSessions.name: csTelnetSvrConfNumOfSessions
csTelnetSvrConfNumOfSessions.description: User configurable number of simultaneous client sessions supported.

csTelnetConnTable.name: csTelnetConnTable
csTelnetConnTable.description: Table lists all the currently active telnet connection.

csTelnetConnEntry.name: csTelnetConnEntry
csTelnetConnEntry.description: Each entry lists one currently active telnet connection.

csTelnetConnId.name: csTelnetConnId
csTelnetConnId.description: Connection Id of this particular telnet session.

csTelnetConnIpAddr.name: csTelnetConnIpAddr
csTelnetConnIpAddr.description: The remote peer's ip address of this telnet session.

csTelnetConnPort.name: csTelnetConnPort
csTelnetConnPort.description: The remote peer's port number of this telnet session.

csTelnetConnRowStatus.name: csTelnetConnRowStatus
csTelnetConnRowStatus.description: The admin status type for this entry in the connection table.

csOrionSyslogdTable.name: csOrionSyslogdTable
csOrionSyslogdTable.description: This table controls the activation of the syslogd client on a particular Virtual Router. Note, only one client can be enabled at a time.

csOrionSyslogdEntry.name: csOrionSyslogdEntry
csOrionSyslogdEntry.description: Each entry represents a single Virtual Router.

csOrionSyslogdStatus.name: csOrionSyslogdStatus
csOrionSyslogdStatus.description: This object is used to enable/disable the syslogd client on this Virtual Router. If this object is disabled, the syslogd client will not forward any ev_log messages to a syslogd server.

csOrionSyslogdLevel1.name: csOrionSyslogdLevel1
csOrionSyslogdLevel1.description: Mapping to syslogd Level from evlog level 1

csOrionSyslogdLevel2.name: csOrionSyslogdLevel2
csOrionSyslogdLevel2.description: Mapping to syslogd Level from evlog level 2

csOrionSyslogdLevel3.name: csOrionSyslogdLevel3
csOrionSyslogdLevel3.description: Mapping to syslogd Level from evlog level 3

csOrionSyslogdLevel4.name: csOrionSyslogdLevel4
csOrionSyslogdLevel4.description: Mapping to syslogd Level from evlog level 4

csOrionSyslogdLevel5.name: csOrionSyslogdLevel5
csOrionSyslogdLevel5.description: Mapping to syslogd Level from evlog level 5

csOrionTemperatureEvent.name: csOrionTemperatureEvent
csOrionTemperatureEvent.description: A fan event. Note that the first four event types apply to analog temperature sensors (for example, those used to measure inlet and outlet air flow temperature), and the last two apply to digital temperature sensors (for example, those in the power supplies).

csOrionFanSpeedThreshold.name: csOrionFanSpeedThreshold
csOrionFanSpeedThreshold.description: The fan speed threshold (in revolutions per second).

csOrionTemperature.name: csOrionTemperature
csOrionTemperature.description: The temperature reported by a temperature sensor.

csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtCurrentEndpoi.name: csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtCurrentEndpointSlot
csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtCurrentEndpoi.description: Current slot number of the primary-to-protection endpoint.

csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtPreviousEndpo.name: csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtPreviousEndpointSlot
csOrionPacketRingPrimToProtPreviousEndpo.description: Previous slot number of the primary-to-protection endpoint.

csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimCurrentEndpoi.name: csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimCurrentEndpointSlot
csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimCurrentEndpoi.description: Current slot number of the protection-to-primary endpoint.

csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimPreviousEndpo.name: csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimPreviousEndpointSlot
csOrionPacketRingProtToPrimPreviousEndpo.description: Previous slot number of the protection-to-primary endpoint.

csOrionTempAirFlowCard.name: csOrionTempAirFlowCard
csOrionTempAirFlowCard.description: The temperature/airflow sense card for which we are resporting an event. Note there is only one temperature/airflow sense card on 3500 chassis.

csOrionI2CDevicePresent.name: csOrionI2CDevicePresent
csOrionI2CDevicePresent.description: Indicates whether a given I2C device is present or not.

csOrionTrapPowerSupplyIndex.name: csOrionTrapPowerSupplyIndex
csOrionTrapPowerSupplyIndex.description: An index for the power supply to be used in power supply trap.

cbrFileType.name: cbrFileType
cbrFileType.description: The kind of file that is being copied from master to standby control blade: bootcfg(1) - boot configuration file config(2) - configuration file password(3) - password file

cbrFileName.name: cbrFileName
cbrFileName.description: Name of the file that is being copied from master to standby control blade.

cbrFileErrorType.name: cbrFileErrorType
cbrFileErrorType.description: Type of error that occurred during a file copy operation from master to standby control blade: cantOpenConfig(-6) - unable to open/create config file on standby control blade cantSaveConfig(-5) - unable to save config file on standby control blade cantChangeDirConfig(-4) - unable to change directory when updating config file on standby control blade cantWritePassword(-3) - unable to write into the password file on a standby control blade cantOpenPassword(-2) - unable to open/create password file on standby control blade cantChangeDirPassword(-1) - unable to change directory when updating password file on standby control blade savedBootcfg(1) - boot config file is saved successfully on standby control blade savedConfig(2) - configuration file is saved successfully on standby control blade savedPassword(3) - password file is saved successfully on standby control blade.

cbrFileErrorCode.name: cbrFileErrorCode
cbrFileErrorCode.description: pHILE+ error code associated with the file copy operation from master to standby control blade. Please consult the pSOS Manual for the possible values and the meanings of the error code.

csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimitEvent.name: csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimitEvent
csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimitEvent.description: Indicates the following events: maximum prefix limit reached exceeds maximum prefix exceeds maximum prefix limit - idling neighbor exceeds maximum prefix limit - discarding additional routes maximum prefix limit threshold reached.

csOrionStatusPanelPortTable.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortTable
csOrionStatusPanelPortTable.description: A table containing information about the Status Panel ports.

csOrionStatusPanelPortEntry.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortEntry
csOrionStatusPanelPortEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular Status Panel port.

csOrionStatusPanelPortIndex.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortIndex
csOrionStatusPanelPortIndex.description: An index for a Status Panel port.

csOrionStatusPanelPortBaudRate.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortBaudRate
csOrionStatusPanelPortBaudRate.description: The baud rate of a Status Panel port.

csOrionStatusPanelPortLoopback.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortLoopback
csOrionStatusPanelPortLoopback.description: The loopback state of a Status Panel port.

csOrionStatusPanelPortModemStatus.name: csOrionStatusPanelPortModemStatus
csOrionStatusPanelPortModemStatus.description: Whether or not a modem is connect to this Status Panel port.

csOrionBladeRemoved.name: csOrionBladeRemoved
csOrionBladeRemoved.description: A orionBladeRemoved trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the one of the existing Blade was removed from it's slot.

csOrionBladeInserted.name: csOrionBladeInserted
csOrionBladeInserted.description: A csOrionBladeInserted trap signifies that SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the one of the Blade was inserted in the empty slot.

csOrionBladeStateChange.name: csOrionBladeStateChange
csOrionBladeStateChange.description: A csOrionBladeStateChange signifies that the SNMPv2 entity acting in an agent role, has detected that a Blade has changed states. A description of the Blade as well as the entered state is identified in this trap.

csOrionFanStatusChange.name: csOrionFanStatusChange
csOrionFanStatusChange.description: A csOrionFanStatusChange trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected a change in the status of a fan.

csOrionConfigChange.name: csOrionConfigChange
csOrionConfigChange.description: A csOrionConfigChange trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that Configuration was changed. The Trap PDU for this csOrionConfigChange, also carries each of the modified object's OID followed by the changed value. In effect, there are one or more VarBinds follows the csOrionNumConfigChanges object of the Trap PDU. Since these OIDs are the member of one of the table defined in this MIB, type information of the value shall be got from the OID. If the csOrionConfigChangeType is delete, the VarBind that follows the csOrionNumConfigChanges contains the Index(es) of the entry which was deleted. If the csOrionConfigChangeType is addModify, then the VarBind contains all the changed OID-Value pairs followed by the index(es).

csOrionTempStatusChange.name: csOrionTempStatusChange
csOrionTempStatusChange.description: This trap indicates that the temperature status of the Orion system has changed states. If the value of csOrionSystemTempStatus is tempRisingAboveUpperCriticalThreshold(1), the given sensor has detected a transition from the normal temperature range to the hot range. If the value of csOrionSystemTempStatus is tempFallingBelow- UpperCriticalThreshold (2), the given sensor has detected a transition from the 'hot' range back down to the normal range.

csOrionPowerSupplyStatusChange.name: csOrionPowerSupplyStatusChange
csOrionPowerSupplyStatusChange.description: This trap indicates one of the power supplies has changed state. The following events are reported: supplyModuleInserted (1) supplyModuleRemoved (2) inputVoltageRisingAbovePastLowerCriticalThreshold (3) inputVoltageFallingBelowLowerCriticalThreshold (4) outputVoltageRisingAboveLowerCriticalThreshold (5) outputVoltageFallingBelowLowerCriticalThreshold (6) outputCurrentRisingAboveUpperCriticalThreshold (7) outputCurrentFallingBelowUpperCriticalThreshold (8) auxVoltageRisingAboveLowerCriticalThreshold (9) auxVoltageFallingBelowLowerCriticalThreshold (10) temperatureRisingAboveUpperCriticalThreshold (11) temperatureFallingBelowUpperCriticalThreshold (12) currentShareRisingAboveLowerCriticalThreshold (13) currentShareFallingBelowLowerCriticalThreshold (14)

csOrionLogLinkDown.name: csOrionLogLinkDown
csOrionLogLinkDown.description: This trap indicates that a Logical Link on the Orion is about to enter the down state.

csOrionLogLinkUp.name: csOrionLogLinkUp
csOrionLogLinkUp.description: This trap indicates that a Logical Link on the Orion is about to enter the up state.

csOrionVIfDown.name: csOrionVIfDown
csOrionVIfDown.description: A csOrionVIfDown trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the csOrionVIfOperStatus object for one of its communication links is about to enter the down state from some other state (but not from the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of csOrionVIfOperStatus.

csOrionVIfUp.name: csOrionVIfUp
csOrionVIfUp.description: A csOrionVIfUp trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links left the down state and transitioned into some other state (but not into the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of ifOperStatus.

csOrionOspfIfStateChange.name: csOrionOspfIfStateChange
csOrionOspfIfStateChange.description: An csOspfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPF interface. This trap should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Dr to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point, DR Other, Dr, or Backup).

csOrionOspfVirtIfStateChange.name: csOrionOspfVirtIfStateChange
csOrionOspfVirtIfStateChange.description: A csOspfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPF vir- tual interface. This trap should be generated when the inter- face state regresses (e.g., goes from Point- to-Point to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point).

csOrionOspfNbrStateChange.name: csOrionOspfNbrStateChange
csOrionOspfNbrStateChange.description: A csOspfNbrStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non- virtual OSPF neighbor. This trap should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., 2-Way or Full). When an neighbor transitions from or to Full on non-broadcast multi-access and broadcast networks, the trap should be gen- erated by the designated router. A designated router transitioning to Down will be noted by csOspfIfStateChange.

csOrionOspfVirtNbrStateChange.name: csOrionOspfVirtNbrStateChange
csOrionOspfVirtNbrStateChange.description: An csOspfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPF vir- tual neighbor. This trap should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., Full).

csOrionOspfIfConfigError.name: csOrionOspfIfConfigError
csOrionOspfIfConfigError.description: An csOspfIfConfigError trap signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual in- terface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's confi- guration parameters. Note that the event op- tionMismatch should cause a trap only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

csOrionOspfVirtIfConfigError.name: csOrionOspfVirtIfConfigError
csOrionOspfVirtIfConfigError.description: An csOspfConfigError trap signifies that a pack- et has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a trap only if it prevents an ad- jacency from forming.

csOrionOspfIfAuthFailure.name: csOrionOspfIfAuthFailure
csOrionOspfIfAuthFailure.description: An csOspfIfAuthFailure trap signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual in- terface from a router whose authentication key or authentication type conflicts with this router's authentication key or authentication type.

csOrionOspfVirtIfAuthFailure.name: csOrionOspfVirtIfAuthFailure
csOrionOspfVirtIfAuthFailure.description: An csOspfVirtIfAuthFailure trap signifies that a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose authentication key or au- thentication type conflicts with this router's authentication key or authentication type.

csOrionOspfIfRxBadPacket.name: csOrionOspfIfRxBadPacket
csOrionOspfIfRxBadPacket.description: An csOspfIfRxBadPacket trap signifies that an OSPF packet has been received on a non-virtual interface that cannot be parsed.

csOrionOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket.name: csOrionOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket
csOrionOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket.description: An csOspfRxBadPacket trap signifies that an OSPF packet has been received on a virtual interface that cannot be parsed.

csOrionOspfTxRetransmit.name: csOrionOspfTxRetransmit
csOrionOspfTxRetransmit.description: An csOspfTxRetransmit trap signifies than an OSPF packet has been retransmitted on a non- virtual interface. All packets that may be re- transmitted are associated with an LSDB entry. The LS type, LS ID, and Router ID are used to identify the LSDB entry.

csOrionOspfVirtIfTxRetransmit.name: csOrionOspfVirtIfTxRetransmit
csOrionOspfVirtIfTxRetransmit.description: An csOspfTxRetransmit trap signifies than an OSPF packet has been retransmitted on a virtual interface. All packets that may be retransmit- ted are associated with an LSDB entry. The LS type, LS ID, and Router ID are used to identify the LSDB entry.

csOrionOspfOriginateLsa.name: csOrionOspfOriginateLsa
csOrionOspfOriginateLsa.description: An csOspfOriginateLsa trap signifies that a new LSA has been originated by this router. This trap should not be invoked for simple refreshes of LSAs (which happesn every 30 minutes), but instead will only be invoked when an LSA is (re)originated due to a topology change. Addi- tionally, this trap does not include LSAs that are being flushed because they have reached MaxAge.

csOrionOspfMaxAgeLsa.name: csOrionOspfMaxAgeLsa
csOrionOspfMaxAgeLsa.description: An csOspfMaxAgeLsa trap signifies that one of the LSA in the router's link-state database has aged to MaxAge.

csOrionOspfLsdbOverflow.name: csOrionOspfLsdbOverflow
csOrionOspfLsdbOverflow.description: An csOspfLsdbOverflow trap signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link-state data- base has exceeded csOspfExtLsdbLimit.

csOrionOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow.name: csOrionOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow
csOrionOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow.description: An csOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow trap signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link- state database has exceeded ninety percent of csOspfExtLsdbLimit.

csOrionCustomerVrUp.name: csOrionCustomerVrUp
csOrionCustomerVrUp.description: A csOrionCustomerVrUp trap signifies that a Virtual Router which services a customer network has has come up.

csOrionCustomerVrDown.name: csOrionCustomerVrDown
csOrionCustomerVrDown.description: A csOrionCustomerVrDown trap signifies that a Virtual Router which services a customer network has gone down.

csOrionServiceProviderVrUp.name: csOrionServiceProviderVrUp
csOrionServiceProviderVrUp.description: A csOrionServiceProviderVrUp trap signifies that a Virtual Router which is designated as a service provider VR has has come up.

csOrionServiceProviderVrDown.name: csOrionServiceProviderVrDown
csOrionServiceProviderVrDown.description: A csOrionServiceProviderVrDown trap signifies that a Virtual Router which is designated as a service provider VR has gone down.

csOrionControlVrUp.name: csOrionControlVrUp
csOrionControlVrUp.description: A csOrionControlVrUp trap signifies that a Virtual Router which is designated as a control VR has come up. If a csOrionBladeRemoved Trap precedes this trap and if that blade is the master control blade then this trap might be from the control VR of the new master blade.

csOrionControlVrDown.name: csOrionControlVrDown
csOrionControlVrDown.description: A csOrionControlVrDown trap signifies that a Virtual Router which is designated as a control VR has gone down.

csOrionServiceProviderVIfUp.name: csOrionServiceProviderVIfUp
csOrionServiceProviderVIfUp.description: A csOrionServiceProviderVIfUp trap signifies that a Virtual Interface on a Service Provider VR has come up.

csOrionServiceProviderVIfDown.name: csOrionServiceProviderVIfDown
csOrionServiceProviderVIfDown.description: A csOrionServiceProviderVIfDown trap signifies that a Virtual Interface on a Service Provider VR has gone down.

csOrionLossOfSignal.name: csOrionLossOfSignal
csOrionLossOfSignal.description: A csOrionLossOfSignal trap signifies that a physical port on a blade experiencing loss of signal(LOS) on the line. Applicable to both DS3 and E3.

csOrionLossOfFrame.name: csOrionLossOfFrame
csOrionLossOfFrame.description: A csOrionLossOfFrame trap signifies that a physical port on a blade experiencing loss of Frame(LOF) on the line. Applicable to both DS3 and OC3.

csOrionDs3AlarmIndication.name: csOrionDs3AlarmIndication
csOrionDs3AlarmIndication.description: A csOrionAlarmIndication trap signifies that a physical port on a blade generates an alarm (AIS) that indicates a failure in upstream far end.

csOrionLossOfClock.name: csOrionLossOfClock
csOrionLossOfClock.description: A csOrionLossOfClock trap signifies that a physical port on a blade experiencing loss of Clock(LOC) on the line. Applicable to both DS3 and OC3.

csOrionBladeRestore.name: csOrionBladeRestore
csOrionBladeRestore.description: A csOrionBladeRestore trap signifies that a blade had been restored successfully or not. The VarBind that follow contains the list of VPN/VRs affected.

csOrionDs3PortIdle.name: csOrionDs3PortIdle
csOrionDs3PortIdle.description: A csOrionDs3PortIdle trap signifies that a physical port on a blade received an IDLE signal from the far end indicating it is unequipped to handle any data transfer.

csOrionAlarmClear.name: csOrionAlarmClear
csOrionAlarmClear.description: A csOrionAlarmClear trap signifies that a physical port on a blade, which had sent an alarm earlier, indicates that the previous alarm is cleared. Applicable to DS3.

csOrionOc3Alarm.name: csOrionOc3Alarm
csOrionOc3Alarm.description: A csOrionOc3Alarm trap signifies that an OC3 physical port on a blade, which had sent an alarm.

csOrionOc3AlarmClear.name: csOrionOc3AlarmClear
csOrionOc3AlarmClear.description: A csOrionOc3AlarmClear trap signifies that an OC3 physical port on a blade, which had sent an alarm earlier, indicates that the prvious alarm is cleared.

csOrionPacketRingStatusChange.name: csOrionPacketRingStatusChange
csOrionPacketRingStatusChange.description: A csOrionPacketRingStatusChange trap signifies that the packet ring status of the chassis has changed. If both endpoints change from zero to r[1,26], that means the status has changed to protection ring. If both endpoints change from r[1,26] to zero, that means the status has changed to no protection ring. If one/both endpoints change from r[1,26] to different r[1,26], that means the topology has changed but not ring status.

csOrionInletAirTempStatusChange.name: csOrionInletAirTempStatusChange
csOrionInletAirTempStatusChange.description: This trap indicates that the inlet air temperature has changed states. If the value of csOrionSystemTempStatus is tempRisingAboveUpperCriticalThreshold(1), the given sensor has detected a transition from the normal temperature range to the hot range. If the value of csOrionSystemTempStatus is tempFallingBelowUpperCriticalThreshold (2), the given sensor has detected a transition from the 'hot' range back down to the normal range.

csOrionDevicePresent.name: csOrionDevicePresent
csOrionDevicePresent.description: This trap indicates that a given I2C device is present. This trap will occur on 9500 and 3500 chassis only.

csOrionPowerSupplyMonitorStatusChange.name: csOrionPowerSupplyMonitorStatusChange
csOrionPowerSupplyMonitorStatusChange.description: This trap indicates a power supply monitor event. The following events are reported: redundancyRegained (1) redundancyLost (2) auxVoltageRisingAboveLowerCriticalThreshold (3) auxVoltageFallingBelowLowerCriticalThreshold (4)

csOrionFarEndReceiveFailure.name: csOrionFarEndReceiveFailure
csOrionFarEndReceiveFailure.description: A csOrionFarEndReceiveFailure trap signifies that the physical port on the remote end is receiving an alarm. Applicable to DS3.

csOrionCBRFileError.name: csOrionCBRFileError
csOrionCBRFileError.description: This trap reports on the status of the copy operation of a system file from master to standby control blade. Generated only if there is control blade redundancy (cbr).

csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimit.name: csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimit
csOrionBgpMaxPfxLimit.description: This trap reports that max-prefix limit has been reached for the given neighbor

csOrionBgpNbrMaxPfxLimit.name: csOrionBgpNbrMaxPfxLimit
csOrionBgpNbrMaxPfxLimit.description: This trap reports that max-prefix limit has been reached for the given neighbor
